title: dream dessert
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb cake dessert
directions: In bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, put rhubarb, jello, sugar and marshmallows.
Make cake mix according to directions on package and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle soup mix over rice in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Add mixture of mushroom soup, milk and water.
Save a little to pour over top of chicken.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice. Put a little pat of butter or margarine on each piece of chicken. Pour over reserved soup mixture.
Cook, covered, 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
Stir rice occasionally.
One half hour before done, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: bonnie-jo salsa
directions: Chop the first 4 ingredients finely.
Add the rest and stir. Serve with corn or tortilla chips.
Makes 2 quarts.
Good for gifts.

title: homemade cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll out thawed bread dough.
Spread with lots of butter; sprinkle on brown sugar.
Sprinkle on lots of the cinnamon.
Roll up and slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Lay flat in a well buttered pan.
Let rise.
Put on lower shelf of oven and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: southwest chicken wraps
directions: Combine chicken, salsa, chili powder, and garlic powder in a large skillet.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add 3/4 c. cheese and can of black beans. Mix well.
Wrap tortillas in a kitchen towel and microwave on high for one minute.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Layer ingredients in large bowl.

title: jean's hot dog chili
directions: Brown meat and onion. Drain, then add tomato paste, salt, water and spices. Bring to a boil and simmer for 2 hours.

title: puppy pile cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients in medium saucepan.
Bring to a full boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Mix in vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Spoon on wax paper and let cool.

title: preacher's corn flakes
directions: Pour bowl 1/2 full of Kellogg's corn flakes.
Sprinkle liberally with Uncle Sam cereal and lightly with wheat germ.
Now top with fresh fruit (bananas, strawberries, peaches, etc.). Sprinkle on sweetener as desired.
Add 1 tablespoon nondairy creamer, all the skim milk you desire and eat with relish!
Low in fat and sodium.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pour rice into a greased baking dish.
Mix chicken soup and water.
Place raw chicken on top of rice and pour soup mixture over it.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, uncovered.
Yields 4 servings.

title: baked french onion soup
directions: Simmer onions in butter for 30 minutes, covered.
Add broth, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes longer.

title: yeast corn bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water and stir until dissolved.
Stir in remaining ingredients and beat until blended.
(This is a stiff batter.)
Turn into two greased 8-inch round pans or two greased 8 1/2-inch loaf pans.
(I usually make one of each.
I cut the round into wedges to serve warm and slice the loaf to serve buttered or for sandwich bread or breakfast toast.)
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: beatnik cake
directions: Melt chocolate in a saucepan and cool.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a tube pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: german pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Spray pie dish with cooking spray.
Add 3 teaspoons margarine to pie dish.
Cover dish with foil and heat in oven.
Mix flour, milk and eggs.
Pour into hot pie dish and bake 13 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar or spread fruit spread on top.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Add first 3 ingredients into a saucepan.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add last three ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients together.
Cream together sugar, butter and eggs, then add bananas and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and cream cheese. Gradually add sugar, creaming until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Fold in sifted flour a little at a time.
Add flavorings.
Beat well. Bake in a 350° oven 1 hour and 20 minutes. Bake in tube pan.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, egg and oil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the top of the baked cake.
Bake an additional 45 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Saute the onion in the margarine.
Combine all but the stuffing mix.
Place in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican corn pudding
directions: Shake 1/2 cup of the milk and the flour in tightly covered container.
Mix milk mixture, remaining milk and the remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches. Cook uncovered in 350° oven until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: fresh raspberry pie
directions: In a medium bowl, crush enough raspberries to make 1 cup. In medium saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch. Add crushed berries and water. Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly. Cool. Add remaining berries to cooled pie shell. Pour cooked berry mixture over the top. Refrigerate 3 hours or until set.

title: fudgy peanut butter bar
directions: In a bowl, combine first 3 ingredients; cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Press firmly into a greased 13 x 9 x

2 inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, in a saucepan, heat milk, vanilla, 1 cup chocolate chips, stirring until smooth. Pour over crust. Sprinkle with nuts, coconut, peanut butter chips and remaining chocolate chips. Press down firmly. Bake for 18-20 minutes. Yields 3 dozen.

title: beatrice cagle's frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Stir first three ingredients together.
Chill for 2 hours. Drain.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Stir and mix together thoroughly. Put in freezer containers.
Freeze.
(No need to keep frozen while in use, but keep refrigerated.)

title: taco ring
directions: Brown meat, drain grease.
Add taco seasoning as directed on package.
Set aside.
Arrange crescent rolls flat in the shape of a ring.
Fill with meat, top with cheese.
Fold the edges of the rolls over the filling.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
May be served with cream cheese, salsa, lettuce, tomatoes, and/or sour cream if desired.

title: bean salad
directions: Rinse beans gently in cold water.
Combine ingredients (except celery and bacon).
Pour over beans; mix slightly.
Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Mix lightly once or twice while chilling.

title: eye of round roast
directions: Make slits in roast and place garlic in slits (scatter the slits). Rub roast with oil, salt, pepper and rosemary.
Place roast in baking pan or dish with about 1/2 cup or so of water in bottom.
Keep moist.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: texas corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, combine corn meal, salt and baking powder.
In medium bowl, with a fork, beat together two eggs, corn, buttermilk and bacon drippings.
Pour all ingredients together and stir until moistened.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with cheese and peppers; top with remaining batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes, until golden.
Serve warm.

title: corn and bean veggie dip
directions: Mince garlic, chop onion and pepper. Drain all canned vegetables.
Combine all ingredients with Italian salad dressing. Cover and let flavors blend from 2 to 24 hours.
Spoon vegetables into a serving bowl with a slotted spoon to drain liquids.
Serve with wide tortilla chips to scoop up dip.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Chop peppers and put in blender with vinegar.
Add sugar and mix well.
Bring mixture to rolling boil; strain.
Return to stove and again bring to rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add Certo and food coloring.
Pour into 6 (1/2 pint) jars and seal.
Good spooned over a block of cream cheese with Ritz crackers.

title: quick winter soup
directions: Microwave water and vegetables on High for 12 minutes.
Stir after 6 minutes.
Stir in ham and cheese.
Cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted and soup is heated thoroughly.

title: chili sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook the sauce until it is thick (it takes about 2 hours).
Pour hot sauce into scalded jars.
Do not cover while cooking.
Makes 5 pints.
Freezes well.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together and pour into greased and floured bread pans (2). Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
As soon as you take it out, pour glaze over it.

title: salmon mix
directions: Drain salmon, remove bones.
Mix all ingredients and season. Blend in cheese.
Place in a large bowl surrounded with potato chips, crackers or toast.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: creme de menthe balls
directions: Combine crumbs, nuts, 1 cup sugar, syrup and creme de menthe with a fork to make a stiff dough. Form into balls. Roll in the rest of sugar. Chill overnight and store in an airtight container.

title: old fashion potato soup
directions: In 2 or 3 quart pan boil potatoes until tender (20 to 25 minutes).
Add a little chopped onion while cooking.
(Salt as would when cooking any potato).
Do not drain, use water as broth. Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Drain and add to potatoes when they are done.
Keep water boiling and add noodles.
Cook until tender.
Eat with buttered crackers and enjoy.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature.
Mix together and shape into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: sausage ring
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place mixture in mold.
Bake ring at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Drain the fat after 15 minutes of cooking. Invert ring on platter and fill center with 8 scrambled eggs. Serves 6.

title: mexican succotash
directions: Dice the zucchini without peeling.
Cut the kernels from the ears of corn with a sharp knife and then, using the dull side of the knife blade, scrape off any remaining pulp and the milk.
Peel and dice the tomatoes.
Saute the onion in butter until just barely golden.
Add the other ingredients and blend with large spoon.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat 30 minutes, stirring from time to time.
Uncover and let any accumulated liquid cook away.
Season to taste. Goes well with any main dish.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except the baking soda and popcorn in a 1 1/2 or 2-quart dish (glass).
Bring to a boil in microwave. Then cook on High for 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir in baking soda.
Pour over popcorn that's placed in a large brown paper bag.
Close bag and shake.
Cook in bag on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake and cook on High for 1 1/2 more minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet.

title: mocha shake
directions: In blender, whirl the coffee, ice, malted milk powder, sugar, honey and cocoa powder for 1 minute or until smooth.
Add milk and blend just until combined.
Serves 2.

title: beans and sausage
directions: Chop onions and bell peppers.
Cook slowly in butter until onions look clear.
Add water and steam about 10 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and cook slowly on medium heat for 45 minutes. You can serve this over rice for a main course.

title: coconut island cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg, coffee and cooled chocolate. Beat well.
Add the sour cream alternately with flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes in 350° oven.

title: brickle bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with tinfoil.
Lay saltines on bottom of pan. Melt butter or margarine; add sugar.
Cook on stove, stirring until it is thick and comes to a boil.
Pour over saltines and bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips (or any flavor).
Spread when melted.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts.
Freeze 2 hours and peel off foil and break into pieces.

title: peanut crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line 11 x 15-inch pan with parchment paper. Score graham crackers and place on parchment paper. In a saucepan, melt the oleo and butter. Add the brown sugar and bring to a boil; boil 2 minutes. Add the nuts.
Pour over graham crackers.
Put in oven and bake 10 minutes. Remove from heat and cool. Break at seam.

title: squash pickles
directions: Wash squash and slice thin; chop onions and peppers.
Mix squash and salt; let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar and spices; bring to a boil.
Add squash mixture and heat just to boiling point.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal while hot.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Cut up cabbage into bite size pieces.
In a large Dutch oven, put tomatoes, beans and cabbage. Cover with water.
Drain hamburger and onions and pour into Dutch oven.
Mix together.
Simmer until cabbage is tender.
Serve with hot cornbread.

title: blueberry oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine biscuit mix, brown sugar, oatmeal and cinnamon.
Mix eggs, milk and butter.
Add dry ingredients all at once and stir just until blended; fold in blueberries.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pans and place on rack to cool.
Makes about 18 muffins.

title: five hour stew
directions: Put first five ingredients into a large roasting pan.
Mix next four ingredients, sprinkle on top of the meat and vegetables. Do not mix.
Pour V-8 juice over the stew.
Bake 5 hours at 250°.

title: maggie's dish
directions: Put a layer or two of raw potatoes in casserole dish or 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass cake pan.
Sprinkle chopped onions over potatoes. Add a layer of ground beef.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Continue doing layers until desired quantity.
Keep layers 1/2 inch below top of dish.
Dilute 1 can soup with 3/4 can water. Pour over potatoes and meat.
Bake covered at least 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until potatoes are done.
Place casserole dish on an edged cookie sheet to catch drippings.
Let dish set in oven for 15 minutes before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Drain can of Veg-All and combine with chicken and cream of chicken soup. Pour mixture into one of the pie shells, cover with the other pie shell.
Make slits in top pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In large iron skillet, bring water, sugar and syrup to a boil. Cook to real hard crack stage, then place raw peanuts in skillet and cook until peanuts are done or start popping.
Remove from stove and add 1/2 teaspoon soda, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon
margarine.
Stir and pour onto buttered foil.
Let cool and peel off foil and break into pieces.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Grate 1/2 teaspoon peel from lemon and squeeze 1 tablespoon juice.
In a nonstick frying pan heat 1 tablespoon oil over high heat.
Add onions and carrots and cook, stirring until tender, about 4 minutes.
Add zucchini and garlic.
Cook about 4 minutes longer.
Add cumin, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and 1 teaspoon oil.
Add the lemon peel and juice.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar together.
Spread in square cake pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Let this cool for 10 minutes.
Beat cream cheese and 1 cup sugar until well blended. Add container of Cool Whip to cream cheese and sugar and mix. Pour mixture over crust.
Dissolve jello with hot water.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until thick.
Pour over cream cheese mixture and refrigerate until set, 1 hour.

title: french toast hawaiian style
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Brown the margarine; remove from heat and cool. Mix pineapple, sugar and flour. Add the pineapple mixture to the margarine in the skillet. Stir in the eggs and mix. Place 1/2 the bread in the bottom of a 9-inch square pan. Cover with the pineapple mixture and top with remaining bread. Bake 35 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer 1:
Mix together refried beans and bean dip.
Spread in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: overnight roast
directions: Place the roast in a roaster pan.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour the roast.
Cover with foil and cook 7 to 8 hours or overnight at 225°.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add vanilla and eggs.
Mix flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda into creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Roll into balls and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 6 minutes at 375°.
Makes 10 to 12 dozen.

title: frypan fruit balls
directions: Turn frypan control to 220°.
Melt butter; add dates.
Cream eggs and sugar; add to dates and butter in frypan.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add fruit nuts, Rice Krispies and flavoring.
Form into balls.
Roll in coconut and store in tin in refrigerator.
Will keep for a month.

title: soup with tiny meatballs
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together thoroughly and shape into small meatballs, about the size of marbles.
Next bring broth to a boil; add soup pasta and little meatballs.
Cook gently about 7 minutes, or until pasta is cooked to your liking.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: dutch potatoes(1883)
directions: Cut off the least bit of each end of potato (to stand up). Make the cut in half crosswise.
Scrape out the insides and mash with eggs, cream, salt and pepper. Return to shells.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over them and to each shell add a bit of butter the size of a hazelnut. Brown in hot oven.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix brown sugar, shortening and milk. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: oyster stew
directions: Drain oysters reserving liquid.
In medium saucepan, combine oysters, 2 tablespoons liquid from oysters, butter and Worcestershire.
Cook over low heat until edges of oysters begin to curl; remove from heat.
Meanwhile, heat remaining liquid from oysters to boiling.
In separate saucepan, heat milk and cream until bubbles form around edge of pan, then combine oysters, oyster liquid and milk mixture.
Season with salt, pepper and celery salt.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: ho-cakes
directions: Stir all together; let sit for 5 minutes.
Cook on skillet (like pancakes) over low heat.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Add sugar gradually to stiffly beaten egg whites.
Melt butter; add to egg mixture.
Add nuts.
Add salt and cinnamon to taste.
Stir well to coat all nuts.
Spread in a jelly roll pan or a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring after the first 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put 1 cup berries in baked pie shell.
Cook 1 cup berries, water, sugar and cornstarch.
Pour over the other berries.
When cold, spread with whipped cream.

title: tuna roll
directions: Drain tuna well and mix with grated onion and apple.
Mix in the Mock Cream Cheese.
Roll tuna mixture in powdered Melba toast. Refrigerate until ready to serve and serve well chilled.
One tuna roll makes 4 servings.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook water and raisins together until water is gone.
Add applesauce, oil, soda, vanilla, eggs, sweetener, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip fork into sugar and press cookie flat.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt, melted butter and syrup with wire wisk or rotary beater.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is set.
Put something under, as it might drip.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon into 12 greased muffin cups. Bake 15 minutes at 425°.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute celery, onion and mushrooms in butter.
Cook as directed on package of broccoli; drain well.
Add mushroom soup to other ingredients in double boiler.
Combine all in chafing dish to serve.

title: bread-n-butter pickles
directions: Soak sliced cucumbers and onion in salted ice water for 3 hours.
Bring other ingredients to boil; add drained vegetables. Bring back to a simmer.
(Do not boil.)
Pack in jars.
Makes about 4 1/2 quarts.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together; bake in a casserole dish for 50 minutes at 350°. Serve with your favorite crackers or chips.

title: penuche
directions: Butter a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine sugar, milk, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring continuously, until sugar is dissolved.
Cook, stirring occasionally, to 234° with candy thermometer (or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball which flattens when removed from water).
Remove from heat.
Add butter.
Cool mixture to 120° without stirring.
Bottom of pan will be lukewarm.
Add vanilla; beat vigorously and continuously for 5 to 10 minutes with wooden spoon until candy is thick and is no longer glossy.
Quickly stir in nuts.
Spread mixture evenly in buttered pan.
Cool until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 32 (1-inch) squares.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all and chill.

title: lo-cal casserole
directions: Place cabbage in greased casserole.
Cover with browned beef, onion, rice, salt and pepper.
Pour on mixed soup and water. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy italian dressing
directions: Blend
all of the ingredients except oil and vinegar in a blender at the highest speed.
Add to the above vinegar all at once
and
the
oil
gradually
in blender and blend until mixed. Remove to a
container and store in refrigerator until thick.

title: broiled scallops
directions: Dip scallops in French dressing using a fork and then dip them into bread crumbs, coating them evenly.
Place on greased baking dish or sheet in a preheated broiler (550°) and cook for about 15 minutes or until the scallops are browned.
Turn occasionally. Serves 4.

title: salmon duff
directions: Combine beaten eggs, liquid from salmon and salmon, broken into chunks.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish in hot (450°) oven about 20 minutes or until firm.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onion Put in a glass jar.
Mix all ingredients and pour over cuke and onion.
Put in refrigerator. Will keep for months.

title: tamale pie
directions: Combine oil, tomatoes, corn and corn meal.
Cook until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Blend water, onion, Soyagen powder and salt together in blender and combine with corn meal mixture.
Add olives and Vegeburger.
Bake in an oiled casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; set aside.
Prepare tortillas, (dip in heated butter or moisten in microwave).
Prepare sauce as directed.
Place filling in tortillas, roll up and place in baking dish with cover.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4-inch thick. Lightly sprinkle green tomatoes with salt; drain on paper towels at least 30 minutes. Combine cornmeal, cheese, flour, garlic salt, oregano and pepper in pie plate. Dip each tomato slice into egg, then in cornmeal mixture. Heat oil in skillet on medium-high. Fry a few at a time about 2 minutes on each side, until golden brown. Drain on paper towel-lined wire rack. Serve immediately. Serves 4 to 6.

title: blueberry-oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats and buttermilk; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Combine oat mixture, egg and oil; stir well.
Add to well of dry ingredients.
Stir until just moist.
Stir in blueberries. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
16 muffins.

title: baker beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp and remove to drain.
Brown onion in bacon grease, then add hamburger and brown; drain.
Mix catsup, salt, dry mustard, brown sugar and vinegar.
Add to pan and warm thoroughly after adding pork and beans, lima beans and kidney beans.
Put in baking pan, crumble bacon over top and bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Bring to boil syrup and sugar.
Add peanut butter; stir well. Stir in cornflakes.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Add and mix well the next 5 ingredients.
Chill dough before rolling.
Roll 1/4-inch thick. Cut in desired shapes.
Raisins may be put in center; sprinkle with sugar or decorate.

title: texas casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper in 2 tablespoons of seasoning. Add paste, sauce and water.
Layer in pan with noodles, corn and meat mix.
Ten minutes before done, sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake at 275° to 300° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: spaghetti chop chop
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook and stir ground beef and pork bulk sausage until light brown, 15 to 20 minutes. Drain. Slice 3 rings from green pepper.
Reserve rings for garnish. Chop remaining ingredients except cheese into meat.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes. Top with green pepper rings.
Bake 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Brown beef.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and tomato sauce.
Simmer about 15 minutes (will look skimpy).
In bowl, mix onion, sour cream and cottage cheese.

title: curry salad
directions: Cut up first 3 ingredients and then mix together in large salad bowl.
Fry crisp bacon and crumble.
Mix bacon, mayonnaise, cheese and sugar and "ice" salad as you would a cake.
Cover completely with the dressing and refrigerate and it will stay fresh several hours.
Stir to mix vegetable with dressing to serve.

title: crock-pot sirloin beef cubes
directions: Put steak cubes in crock-pot and pour mixture of rest of ingredients over top.
Cook on high 6 to 8 hours.
If you want more gravy, mix up package of brown gravy mix and add.
Good over noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: sugar-cinnamon pecans
directions: In medium small bowl, beat egg whites to frothy.
Put pecans in froth; mix well and let soak 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 250°.

title: beef and tater casserole
directions: Crumble meat in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook in oven on high for 45 minutes (until beef is no longer pink).
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain.
Top with Tater Tots.
Mix soups together and pour over Tater Tots.
Bake in oven on high 10 minutes.
Turn dish halfway through cooking time.

title: sponge cake(dessert)
directions: Beat egg yolks; gradually add sugar, beating until thick and light in color.
Stir in lemon juice and rind.
Beat egg whites and salt until stiff, but not dry.
Pile on top of the egg yolk mixture.
Sift flour, mixed with baking powder, over egg whites and fold in carefully.
Turn into a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° (170°C) for 50 minutes or until browned and free from sides of pan. Invert and let cool.

title: limpa rye bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm water.
Stir in molasses, sugar, salt, shortening and rye flour and beat till smooth.
Mix in enough white flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead dough about 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover; let rise till double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch dough down and let rise again. Divide into 3 parts.
Shape into round slightly flat loaf.
Let rise till almost double, about 1 hour.
Brush loaves with slightly beaten egg before putting in oven.
Makes 3 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti sauce(crock-pot)
directions: Brown pork chops; cut up with sausage.
Put in with spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce.
Cook in a large crock-pot on low all day or high for 4 or 5 hours.
Serve over desired spaghetti.

title: beef noodles and mushroom casserole
directions: Saute meat in oil.
Saute mushrooms, pepper and tomatoes separately, and then add browned meat.
Add beef stock to meat mixture.
Cook noodles in boiling salt water.
Drain and add to meat mixture.
Season and pour in greased casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 275° until cheese is melted.

title: hocus pecos dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix until all ingredients are incorporated. Chill for at least 2 hours before serving to allow flavors to blend. Serve with tortilla chips and/or fresh vegetables.

title: cold raspberry soup
directions: Put raspberries through a fine sieve to remove seeds.
Add sour cream and sugar.
Stir well.
Add ice water and wine.
Put mixture in blender and blend until well mixed.
Chill overnight.
Shake well before serving.
Serve ice cold.
(I serve in demitasse cups so that one can sip it.)
Serves 6 to 12 in demitasse cups.

title: quiche
directions: Place eggs, onion, half and half, cheese and vegetables into a blender.
Blend for 1 minute. Pour mixture into an unbaked pie crust. Sprinkle pepper and Parmesan cheese on top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Mix
meal and salt.
Stir boiling water into meal until it
is very
thick.
Then
make
out
into
balls and flatten slightly. Fry
in
deep
fat	until golden brown.
Or you may make
into a "pone" and bake in hot oven until slightly brown. Good either way.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar well until light.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add pumpkin and juice; blend well.
Stir in dry ingredients until mixture is moistened.
Gently fold in nuts and raisins. Pour batter into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 65 to 75 minutes, or until tester comes out clean. Makes 2 loaves.

title: oreo surprise
directions: Combine dates, water and salt in saucepan and bring to a boil, then simmer for 3 minutes.
Crush 1 dozen Oreo cookies.
Make crust in bottom of Pyrex dish (reserve approximately 2 tablespoons of crumbs to sprinkle on top).
Add the tiny marshmallows to date mixture and stir until dissolved, then add chopped pecans; stir well and pour over crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Chill, then serve in squares.
Delicious.

title: baked chicken cheese
directions: Mix 8 ounces Cheddar cheese, mushroom soup and sour cream. Pour mixture over chicken.
Place 8 ounces Cheddar cheese on top. Cook 2 hours at 275°; 1 hour at 350°.
Place foil over first 2 hours and remove last hour.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix everything in bowl.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.
May be made night before.

title: quick iced dill pickles
directions: In bottom, middle and top, pour brine over and refrigerate. Ready in 3 or 4 days.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, beaten egg yolks and sour cream. Sift dry ingredients and gradually add to creamed mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and flatten with a glass covered with a damp hankie or cloth.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: shrimp, crabmeat and tuna bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crumbs and cheese.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix beans, syrup (I use brown syrup), and onion.
Cut the bacon in half and spread the four pieces of bacon on top of beans.
Cook in oven at 400°.
Take out of oven when the bacon is brown.

title: pear and blue cheese salad
directions: To toast walnuts, heat oven to 350°. Bake in ungreased shallow pan about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until golden brown. Add to lettuce, pears and cheese. Toss with cider vinaigrette just before serving.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Prepare jello with boiling water.
When syrupy add drained pineapple and pie filling.
Let set.
Combine remaining ingredients except nuts which you sprinkle on top.
Makes a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Thaw broccoli; drain.
Mix broccoli with 2 cups of the cheese and onion in a pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth, by hand.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and bake 1 to 2 minutes longer to melt.

title: bourbon cocktail sausages
directions: Heat all ingredients thoroughly in a heavy saucepan.
Transfer to a chafing dish, on low heat.
The longer this simmers, the better it gets!

title: peanut butter crispies
directions: Melt sugar and syrup together on stove.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter and mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mix well. Pour in greased long cake pan.
Cut in squares.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Mix together the vinegar, salad oil, salt, sugar and prepared mustard.
Pour this over the potatoes which have been diced and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
To this, add chopped celery, carrots, sweet pickles, hard-boiled eggs, onion, salad dressing and cream.
After mixing, refrigerate if you are not going to serve right away.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Cool and debone.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish (save broth).
Sprinkle herb dressing over chicken.
Put 4 cups broth in pan and mix in soups and onion. Thicken with flour when mixture is almost at boiling point.
Pour over casserole.
Top with salt and pepper and sage.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned ice cream
directions: Mix milks, sugar and vanilla flavoring.
Add fruit, if desired.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Pack ice around freezer and gradually add ice and salt as it melts.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water.
Stir in pie filling in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and chill until partially set.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Gradually add lemon Jell-O; stir in undrained pineapple.
Add whipping cream (Cool Whip).
Fold in 1 cup of mini marshmallows.
Spread on top of cherry layer.
Chill until set.
Makes 12 servings.
"Delicious."

title: fish amadine
directions: Roll fillets in mixture of flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt. Pour 2 tablespoons melted butter and broil fish until done.
While broiling fish, brown almonds in 2 tablespoons melted margarine, then stir in lime juice and chili powder.
Pour over broiled fish. Wonderful with Laguna Madre speckled trout!

title: easy cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries and orange in food processor.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough boiling water to reserved juice to measure 1 cup.
Combine with gelatin in bowl, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in cranberry mixture, sugar and pecans.
Pour into mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: baked beans 1
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Top with slices of bacon and onion.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ripe plantain omelet(dominican republic style)
directions: Peel the plantains and cut in small strips.
Fry in a little oil until golden.
Drain off excess oil and chop the plantain in smaller pieces.
Beat the eggs and add salt and pieces of ham. Add this mixture to the plantain and stir well.
Cook over low heat until brown on one side.
Turn omelet onto a plate and return to frying pan by slipping omelet off the plate.
Cook
until golden.

title: velvet pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Continue mixing. Add small amounts of dry ingredients (flour, baking powder and salt sifted together) and milk alternately with dry ingredients, first and last.
Add the flavoring with the milk. Bake for about 1 hour at 325° in greased and floured stem pan with waxed paper in bottom.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast; mix well.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: broccoli rabe
directions: Heat olive oil in a large pot and saute garlic for just a few minutes until tender.
Do not allow to brown.
Add broccoli rabe and sprinkle with red pepper flakes, salt and pepper to taste. Mix to combine with garlic.
Add enough water to almost cover (about 3 to 4 cups).
Bring water to a boil, cover and let steam for about 5 to 10 minutes or until tender.

title: fudge
directions: Bring to boil over medium heat the cocoa, sugar and evaporated milk.
Take off heat.
Add butter, vanilla and 1 cup nuts.
Beat until dull.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: oven baked vegetable chowder
directions: Coat a 2-quart round casserole with vegetable cooking spray according to directions. Beat eggs and flours together in a large mixing bowl until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring to blend. Pour into casserole.
Set in pan of hot water. Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour. Spoon into soup bowls.
Serves 8.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer on a plate in this order and serve with tortilla chips.

title: fit for a king bread pudding
directions: Cut the bread into small pieces and place in a large mixing bowl.
Rinse them quickly with hot water, but do not make them soggy.
Add the raisins, nuts, 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon, 1 cup white or brown sugar and the fruit. Set aside.
In a quart pot, place the milk, half and half and margarine.
Heat over medium heat until hot, but do not boil.
Pour the hot mixture over the broken bread bits and other ingredients.
Mix it
all together.
Put into a buttered dish big enough to hold the entire mixture, 9 x 13-inches is probably best. Sprinkle the top with the 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 5 teaspoons sugar.
Place in a 400° oven.
In 40 minutes, check for doneness with toothpick into middle of pudding; must come out clean or continue to bake.
Chill and serve or serve hot.

title: skillet fried corn
directions: Cook the bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Add the vegetables to the drippings; cook.
Cook over low heat for 5 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle bacon over the top.
Yields 6 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add 1 well beaten egg. Sift together all dry ingredients (excluding oats) and add it to the first mixture.
Then add vanilla and oats.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Roll walnut size pieces by hand and place on greased cookie sheet.
Butter the bottom of a small glass, dip in granulated sugar and flatten out the pieces of dough.
Do not re-butter glass unless necessary, but use fresh sugar for each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix the flour and oil until crumbly.
Add the water and knead until smooth.
Squeeze off golf ball size pieces of dough.
Roll thin and cook on a hot, dry skillet on the stove top.
Cook both sides.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Put yeast into 1/4 cup warm water; mix.
Add Crisco and sugar. Alternate flour and milk.
Mix well and knead flour into mixture. Roll out and cut with a biscuit cutter; set aside and let rise 1/2 hour, until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Combine juice from cherries and pineapple, add water to make 2
cups.
Heat to boil and pour over Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add
Coke
and
chill.
After
partially jelled, add cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Stir well and jell. It serves well with turkey or chicken.

title: potato dish
directions: Bring milk to boil.
Add potatoes and cook until potatoes soak up milk.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Put in baking dish in layers, adding medium sharp cheese between layers.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Blend well and serve with sliced apples.
Can microwave for 1 minute.

title: vegetable bundt bread
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion together.
Mix the other ingredients together; combine with bell pepper and onion.
Put in Bundt pan.
Bake until golden brown at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serve warm.

title: walnut caramel triangles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned around edges.
Meanwhile, in heavy saucepan, combine Eagle Brand, cream and vanilla.
Over medium-high heat, cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium; cook and stir until mixture thickens, 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread evenly over prepared crust.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Garnish with Chocolate Drizzle.
Chill. Cut into triangles.
Store covered at room temperature.

title: hot tuna dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Stir gently together and heat.
Serve with Bugles.

title: my bean salad
directions: Mix all beans with celery.
Mix oil, vinegar and sugar together until sugar dissolves, then pour over vegetables.
Keep in tightly covered container in refrigerator.
Will keep for weeks.
Good for picnics.

title: candied yams
directions: Place drained yams in baking dish.
Combine syrup from yams, sugar and margarine in saucepan, stirring constantly until it begins to boil and thicken.
Pour sauce over yams.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: blender banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop walnuts and put aside.
Measure out flour, salt and baking powder and mix together with walnuts in one bowl.
Put egg, softened butter, 1/2 cup milk and sliced bananas in blender and put on stir.
When completely mixed, add sugar to mixture slowly until blended.
Spray loaf pan with Pam spray and then mix dry ingredients to banana mixture in bowl until thoroughly blended, then pour into loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix in a large mixing bowl, beat until smooth and well blended.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by rounded teaspoons onto ungreased baking sheets, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.
You can use peanut butter or butterscotch chips instead of chocolate chips.

title: swiss egg spread
directions: Grate cheese.
Chop eggs and onion very fine and add to cheese.
Blend in mayonnaise to make spreadable.
Add pinch of salt.
Serve with crackers.

title: cousin patty's frosting
directions: Over low heat, stir milk and flour until thick.
Set aside to cool.
Beat margarine and sugar until well blended and fluffy. Gradually add milk mixture while beating; add vanilla and beat until light and fluffy.
Food coloring may be added.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into container and refrigerate.

title: easy paella
directions: Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to clam liquid to make 1 1/4 cups; set aside.
In a 6-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on all sides.
Remove chicken; set aside.
Reduce heat to medium.
In hot drippings, cook onions, rice and garlic until rice is lightly browned, stirring often.
Add reserved clam liquid, broth, turmeric, pepper and chicken.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear.
Stir in clams, peas and shrimp.
Cover 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink and opaque.
Serve with lemon.
Makes 8 servings.

title: light fluffy icing
directions: Mix
first
5 ingredients in top of double boiler. Beat until mixture
stands
in
a
peak.
Remove
from heat and add flavoring.	Beat until mixture is of desired consistency.
Put coconut in it after you are through beating.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Spread rolls on a large, ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 10
minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and dressing. Spread on cooled rolls. Mix vegetables together.
Spread on cream cheese mixture.
Top with cheese and gently press into cream cheese mixture.
Chill and cut into bars to serve.

title: fruit sherbet punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Float orange sherbet on top.

title: crawfish cornbread
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in small amount of butter until onions are transparent.
Add jalapeno peppers.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients except crawfish.
Add cooked onions and peppers.
Stir in crawfish.
Pour into lightly greased pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Excellent with green salad and fruit platter.

title: teacher's appreciation luncheon cheese bread
directions: Pour yeast in cup, stir in 1/4 cup water.
Add sugar and beat until frothy.
Put flour and salt in large bowl, add yeast mixture. Add rest of the water, knead for 2 minutes.
Form into a ball, sprinkle with flour, cover, let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours until doubled.
Knead dough lightly.
Roll into rectangle.
Dot with butter.
Fold over in thirds.
Roll out to same size again. Sprinkle with cheese and chives to within 1/2 inch from sides. Roll from short end like a jelly roll.
Place into greased bread pan.
Score with sharp knife.
Let rise approximately 30 minutes. Brush with beaten egg.
Bake in 425° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rainbow ribbon dessert
directions: Dissolve 1 package Jell-O in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Pour 3/4 cup gelatin into 6-cup ring mold.
Chill until set but not firm, about 15 minutes.
Chill remaining gelatin in bowl until slightly thickened, then blend in 3 tablespoons sour cream.
Spoon over gelatin in mold.
Chill until set, but not firm, about 15 minutes.
Repeat with remaining flavors.
Chill until firm. Unmold.

title: pumpkin-pecan pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into pie shell. Arrange pecan halves on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool on a wire rack.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: kathy's pasta
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook pasta as directed on box.
Brown beef and sausage; stir in remaining ingredients.
Place in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with tinfoil.
Bake 45 minutes; uncover and add cheese to top until browned.

title: chicken with mushrooms and wild rice
directions: Thoroughly brown chicken on all sides in Crisco and olive oil in a frying pan.
Remove chicken and brown mushrooms and green peppers in same skillet.
Return chicken to pan.
Add sherry and seasoning; cook, covered, over low heat for 20 minutes.
If not enough sauce left, remove chicken.
Add water or stock (canned chicken consomme may be used) and simmer a few minutes. Meanwhile, cook rice.
Mound rice, surrounding it with chicken and pour sauce over all.

title: pecan delight pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Slowly add sugar; beat very stiff.
Stir in pecans and broken soda crackers.
Pour in buttered glass pie plate and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Cool and top with Cool Whip.
Can add nuts on top also.

title: orange aspic
directions: Drain juice from oranges and add enough orange juice to have 2 cups.
Pour juice into small sauce pan.
Heat and dissolve gelatin.
Add sherbet.
Stir.
Add mandarin oranges and pour mixture into mold.	Refrigerate until set.	Serves 8.

title: gopher's breath
directions: Mix cream cheese and onion pieces into a spread.
Spread on tortilla shells.
Roll up and chill.
Cut into pieces.
Use toothpicks to hold together.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a casserole and bake 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: avocado omelet
directions: Beat eggs. Add water.
Pour eggs into heated buttered skillet and cook on low to medium heat, gently lifting edges to let liquid run under, until all is set.
Spoon vegetables onto 1/2 of the omelet. Top with cheese and fold over.
Remove to plate and serve.

title: beef nacho dip
directions: Combine ground beef and onion in 11/2 qt. casserole. Stir in taco sauce and olives. Set aside. Spread beans in 9 x 13 dish. Spread meat mixture over beans. Spread sour cream over meat mixture and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 325 degrees until cheese melts.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk for 30 minutes after it starts boiling on low heat.
Take from stove; add butter and beat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; remove from broth and debone.
Cut in chunks; set aside.
Mix seasoning package of stuffing mix with 2 cans of soup and chicken broth.
Grease casserole dish.
Pour 1/2 of stuffing mix in bottom of dish; spread evenly, then spread 1/2 of chicken.
Cover with 1/2 of soup mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.
Serve with cranberry sauce.

title: paul newman cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 13 x 9-inch pan according to directions.
Poke holes in cake with wooden spoon handle.
Pour condensed milk into holes.
Pour caramel topping into same holes.
Put whipped topping on top.
Add butter brickle bits to top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook mushrooms until tender.
Combine with shrimp, rice, vegetables and seasonings in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour 1/2 cup of butter over.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Trim with wreath of parsley and stuffed olive slices.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mom's homemade ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add Milnot.
Stir well, then add Vitamin D milk (enough to fill freezer).

title: baked beans
directions: Bake in a deep dish for 1 1/2 hours at 325° or 350°.

title: lasagne italiano
directions: Cook meat, onion and garlic in skillet til brown.
Drain.
Add tomatoes with liquid, tomato sauce, parsley, sugar, basil, 1/2 tsp. salt, stirring occasionally.
Lower heat.
Simmer uncovered til mixture thickens, about 1 hour.
Cook noodles.
Save 1/2 cup of sauce mixture.
Mix Ricotta Cheese, 1/4 cup of Parmesan Cheese, 1 Tbsp. parsley, 1 1/2 tsp. salt and the oregano.
Layer 1/3 each of the noodles, remaining sauce mix, Mozzarella Cheese and Ricotta Cheese mix in ungreased 9 X 13 X 2 pan.
Repeat twice.
Spoon reserved sauce mix on top, sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan Cheese. Cook uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes up to 10 servings.

title: alligator steak (seminole)(modern)
directions: Cut tail into 1-inch thick steaks.
Rub lime juice on steaks. Season with salt and cayenne pepper.
Grill until done.

title: mulligan's stew
directions: Use 4-gallon stew pot. Add 2 gallons of water to start. You may add more water later if you need it. Add all veggies, except potatoes, and cook for 30 minutes on medium heat. Add pre-cooked meat and potatoes; cook another 30 minutes. Add seasoning and simmer until ready to eat.

title: chutney cheese pate
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sharp Cheddar cheese, Swiss cheese, dry sherry and curry powder. Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until blended.
Shape mixture into a 10-inch circle or a 12-inch round serving dish. Cover and chill until firm. Spread chutney over cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with green onions and garnish with red pepper strips. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes for 30 minutes only.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: ginger bread(from 100 + year old cook book)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Sift flour, salt and spices, set as side.
Cream butter and sugars, add eggs and molasses.
Mix butter milk and soda together and then add to creamed mixture and mix.
Add to creamed mixture, stir, do not over mix.
Bake in a 9x13-inch pan until done when tested.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes into casserole bowl.
Cut butter over the top of potatoes.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup of sugar over potatoes. Sprinkle cinnamon over top (lightly).
Pour over vanilla (do not mix).
Set in warm oven and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Stir after 15 minutes and cover with lid until remaining 15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: choco-nut dainties
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour and salt onto wax paper. Beat together 3/4 cup margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla in a large bowl until well mixed.
Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in 6 ounces chocolate chips.

title: baked beans
directions: Dice onion and brown.
Add hamburger; stir until brown.
Add salt, ketchup, mustard, vinegar and beans.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Combine sausage, onion, cheese and flour; mix well.
Spread in unbaked pie shell.
Beat together eggs, cream and flour.
Slowly pour over sausage mixture.
Bake on baking sheet for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Boil sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla.
Pour this over the chopped rhubarb which has been put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: celery seed salad dressing
directions: First grate onion. Use half of a 3/4 cup vinegar to mix ingredients. Use the other half of vinegar with 2 cups oil and 1/8 teaspoon celery seeds. Mix all really well. Food processor works best for blending.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Flake salmon.
Add tomatoes, onions and water in a large pot. Simmer 20 minutes.
Combine flour, milk and seasoning; cook in separate pan until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add salmon mixture and serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix butter, cheese, flour and pecans by hand.
Add pepper and mix well.
Pinch off enough to make a marble size ball.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until lightly brown.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown meat with onion.
Add seasonings to tomato sauce.
Drain meat and mix with tomato sauce.
Alternate layers of tortillas, meat sauce, beans and cheese in casserole dish.
Add water.
Cover and bake for 20 minutes.
Cut in wedges to serve.

title: maunakea snowballs
directions: Blend butter, sugar, and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add salt and flour; mix well.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on unbuttered cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven 10-12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheer and roll in additional confectioners sugar, colored sprinkles, chocolate shot, silver drops, or chopped nuts.
Place on racks to cool.
Makes about 8 dozen snowballs.

title: sweet and sour seafood stir-fry
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together sherry, vinegar, soy sauce, sesame seed oil and cornstarch.
Set aside.
In wok or large skillet, heat 1 1/2 tablespoons peanut oil over high heat.
Stir in garlic and ginger.
Add shrimp and scallops.
Stir-fry until shrimp turns pink and scallops are opaque, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Add rest of oil to skillet.
Stir in peppers, bamboo shoots and green onions.
Stir-fry 5 to 7 minutes until veggies are crisp-tender.
Return shrimp and scallops to skillet.
Add sauce. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Arrange steamed rice around edges of plates.
Spoon stir-fried rice into center.
Serves 4.

title: seven layer low-fat salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise with Equal.
Save for top.

title: wild grouse casserole
directions: Spread rice on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 package of dry soup mix.
Mix together the canned soups and cream.
Pour most of this mixture over rice.
Place grouse on top of this.
Top with remaining onion soup mix.
Cover with boil and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Serves 2 to 3. Preparation Time:
2 hours.

title: tabbouleh salad
directions: Wash bulghur; drain from water and put in a large bowl. (Let it set for 30 minutes.) Chop tomatoes, parsley, onion and mint, then add
over bulghur.
In a small bowl, blend the oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper; pour over mixture and mix well.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Combine cookies and margarine and press into 10-inch greased pie pan.
Spread softened ice cream over crust.
Pour chocolate syrup over ice cream.
Cover with Cool Whip and chopped nuts. Freeze.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: raspberry sparkle punch
directions: Process raspberries in food mill or container of electric blender.
Strain, discarding seeds.
Combine raspberry pulp, lemonade concentrate and water.
Chill.
To serve, combine raspberry mixture and lemon-lime beverage.
Stir well.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with mint sprigs, if desired.
Yield:
7 cups.

title: pailla (mexican rice)
directions: Fry rice in heated cooking oil in a large frying pan until slightly brown.
Add onion, garlic and tomato; stir over a medium flame for about 5 minutes.
Add 4 cups of water and 2 cups chicken broth; bring to a boil.
Add smoked oysters, clams and roasted peppers.
Bring to low flame.
Stir-cook for about 20 minutes or until water is dissolved.

title: joanne's pecan muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix by hand thoroughly.
Spoon into mini muffin tins that have been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 24 mini muffins.

title: melt-in-your-mouth biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Pour milk in slowly; add egg and stir well.
Knead on lightly floured surface.
Roll 1/2-inch thick. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes in 450° oven.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well and bake in 2-quart dish for 45 minutes.

title: mary's yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Soften yeast in warm water and let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour scalded milk over sugar, shortening and salt in a large bowl.
When lukewarm, stir mixture.
Add 1 cup flour and softened yeast mixture; mix well.
Add 3 cups flour, beat until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Then add enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface.
Let rest for 5 to 10 minutes, before starting to knead.
Knead dough for about 5 to 8 minutes.
Form into a large ball.
Place in large greased bowl.
Cover and let stand in a warm place until dough is doubled (about 1 hour).

title: chocolate peanut butter chip muffins
directions: Combine eggs, oil, milk and vanilla in a small bowl, mix well. In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add wet ingredients to dry and add chips.
Fold gently until just mixed.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Makes 10 medium muffins.

title: buttermilk meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup and buttermilk; form into balls.
Place in greased dish.
Combine one can of soup and one can of buttermilk until smooth.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake uncovered one hour at 350°.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and flour.
Stir well.
Add milk, vanilla, melted butter and coconut.
Pour in a 9-inch greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: irish stew(serves 4)
directions: Trim the excess fat off the meat. Cut the meat into small neat pieces and put in large pan with the onion and seasoning. Add the water. Cover with close-fitting lid and cook gently for 1 1/4 hours, shaking occasionally. Add the potatoes, carrots and celery and cook for 3/4 hour. Add the peas and cook for 10 minutes. Sprinkle the parsley on top and serve.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix cheese, dressing, pineapple, Cool Whip and pecans.
Chill until congealed.
Dissolve jello in hot water and mix in other ingredients.
Put in refrigerator and chill until ready to serve.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water on oatmeal and let stand for 20 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pepper nuts
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.
Roll in 1-inch rolls.
Slice 1/2 inch thick.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled okra
directions: Boil pints jars for 15 minutes.
Wash okra with vegetable brush.
Place okra in jars.
Bring water, salt and vinegar to a boil.
Add to each jar:
1 teaspoon dill seed, 2 garlic cloves and 1 hot pepper.
Pour boiling mixture over okra in jars.
Put lids on jars and set them in a container in which you completely cover them in water.
Let simmer for 5 minutes.
Yields 2 pints.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups cookie crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup melted margarine to make crust.
Press into 9-inch pie plate and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
In mixing bowl, beat peanut butter, cream cheese, sugar, margarine and vanilla until smooth. Fold in whipped cream.
Gently spoon into crust.
Garnish with crumbs, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: tamale balls
directions: Mix beef, corn meal and chili powder together.
Shape into cocktail size meat balls.
Brown slowly in oil. Drain and add V-8 juice and other ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, until sauce cooks down and is thick.
Serve hot with toothpicks.

title: shenandoah fresh apple cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon, beating well after each addition.
Stir in apples, nuts and butterscotch chips. (Mixture will be very thick.)
Press mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: great-grandma ridley's fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs and blend well.
Chop nuts and fruit and mix with part of the flour. Sift remaining flour and baking powder.
Fold into egg mixture. Add flavorings and mix well, then add fruit and nut mixture by hand.
Put mixture in a greased tube pan and place in a cold oven. Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Let cool in pan completely.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until tender;
drain and put in big dish.
Stir in bowl the soup, milk, butter and cheese; melt.
Then pour over potatoes, then place in oven above 325° for about 20 minutes.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in chopped apples and nuts.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan, 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp and lemon broccoli soup
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot butter, cook celery.
Stir in soup, gradually stir in milk, 1/4 cup shrimp and lemon peel.
Reduce heat to low, simmer until shrimp turn pink, stirring occasionally.
Garnish.

title: bordeau relish
directions: Mix and boil 1 hour or until tender.
Jar; seal and keep in cool dry place until used.

title: delicious cake
directions: Bake cake following directions on box in a sheet cake pan. When cake is done, immediately poke holes in cake with a wooden spoon handle; spread remaining 5 ingredients over cake.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: old fashioned peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar and Karo until mixture spins a thread.
Add peanuts.
Cook until golden brown (about 5 minutes).
Add butter chip, the size of a walnut, and baking soda.
Stir fast and pour on buttered cookie sheet.
Do not spread with a spoon.

title: open house punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Mix in punch bowl, 7-Up last.
Add drops of red food coloring (optional); stir.
Float block of ice.
Add orange and lemon slices.

title: milky way cake
directions: Combine candy bars and 1 stick butter in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Set aside. Cream 2 cups of sugar and 1 stick butter in a bowl, then beat in eggs.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange 1/2 of sliced potatoes in an 8-inch glass baking dish. Combine flour with salt.
Sprinkle half on potatoes.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Pour milk over potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake in microwave for 20 minutes or until tender.

title: top-notch brownies(easier than a mix - taste like fudge)
directions: In saucepan melt margarine over medium heat.
Remove from heat; stir in cocoa and sugar.
Add flour, salt, eggs and vanilla. Stir just until mixed.
Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch square pan. Bake at 330° for about 20 minutes until barely done.
Center will set while cooling.

title: southern dressing
directions: Crumble bread into mixing bowl.
Add boiling broth.
Cover and let set 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake 1 hour at 400°.
Serve with chicken, giblet gravy and cranberry sauce.

title: broccoli salad squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll crescent role dough; do not separate.
Roll out dough onto a rectangle stone or cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
In a bowl mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; set aside. Chop broccoli and bacon.
Cut onion into thin slices, then quarter slices.
Spread mayonnaise mixture over top of crust.
Cut into square pieces then top with ingredients.
Sprinkle with broccoli, bacon, onion, raisins and sunflower seed kernels.
Serve immediately or refrigerate up to one hour.

title: golden green beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Add Velveeta, bacon and onion to beans; mix lightly.
Place in 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Stir well before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface, and knead dough 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are golden.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl until well blended.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: manhatten clam chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon from pan and drain, reserving 2 tablespoons of drippings in the saucepan.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Saute onions, celery and green peppers in reserved drippings until tender.
Add water, potatoes, carrots, parsley, salt, thyme, pepper, tomatoes, bay leaf and the reserved liquid from the clams.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 25 to 35 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf; stir in clams.
Heat gently.
Stir frequently.
Do not boil.
Garnish each serving with crumbled bacon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crock-pot lasagna
directions: Cook beef; drain off fat. Add pizza sauce. Layer ingredients in crock-pot as follows: sauce on bottom, pasta, sauce, cheese and pepperoni. Continue layering until all ingredients are used. Cook on LOW for 3 hours.

title: sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly around edges.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: I reserve this dessert for very special guests!

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and cheese; beat well until light and smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until well blended.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with the milk to the first mixture.
Mix well.
Spoon into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine last 4 ingredients and mix with a pastry blender until mixture looks like coarse corn meal.
Sprinkle over the cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: basic white sauce
directions: In 1 quart glass measuring cup put butter, flour and salt. Microwave on
high for 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute. Gradually stir in milk.
Microwave on high for 4 to 5 1/2 minutes, stirring every minute until thick and bubbly.
For thicker sauce, use 3 Tbsp. of flour instead of two.
Makes 1 cup.
So easy and no scorching!

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini and wheat germ.
Combine dry ingredients and add to zucchini mixture, mixing well, then add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: ma jo's fried rice
directions: Boil water.
Stir in rice; remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet; cook egg.
Add onion and rice. Cook over medium heat until onion and rice are light brown, about 5 minutes.
Combine water and soy sauce; stir into rice.

title: diet blender milk shake
directions: Blend for 30 to 40 seconds.
You can substitute fresh or frozen fruit for coffee.

title: k. f. slaw
directions: Mix carrots, cabbage and onions together.
Put vinegar, sugar, mayonnaise, oil and salt in a pan and bring to a boil for 1 minute. Pour over cabbage mixture.
Let cool for a few minutes and ready to eat.

title: calico rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions. In another pan cook frozen vegetables; drain.
Combine rice and vegetables.
Mix mayonnaise, milk, ketchup and Ranch dressing.
Stir into rice mixture.
Cover and chill.
Serve in lettuce leaf lined bowl.

title: angel dessert
directions: Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, milk, sugar and egg yolks, beaten well.
Cook until creamy (it won't be very thick) and pour while hot over lemon Jell-O.
Cool, then fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Put in refrigerator until partially set. Remove and whip a little with eggbeater.
Add cream, whipped stiff. Add 3 tablespoons sugar.
Break angel food cake in large pieces. In flat dish, pour custard mixture over the pieces, pressing it down and around the cake.
Sprinkle top with pineapple, then cherries.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients over medium heat.
After it comes to a boil, continue to boil about 5 minutes or until a small ball forms if dropped in water.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and pour in buttered dish.

title: rye bread treats
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger; drain.
Mix meat and spices; simmer.
Add Velveeta cheese and simmer until melted.
Spread on cocktail rye bread.
Eat now or freeze and reheat in microwave.

title: black truffles
directions: The almonds and chocolate must both be finely ground in a blender.
Cut chocolate coarsely before grinding in blender. After grinding, mix them together in a bowl and then mix in the unbeaten egg whites.
Knead briefly in the bowl until mix holds together.
Divide into 40 pieces, using 1 tablespoon for each and place on wax paper or aluminum foil.
Roll each piece between your hands to form a ball and replace on foil or paper.

title: veggie bars
directions: Put dough on cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dry dressing.
Let set.
Spread on cool dough.
Then sprinkle "veggies" on top.

title: microwave macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
In microwave, melt cheese in a microwave-safe dish.
Set at Medium setting for 2 minutes.
Repeat, if necessary, to get cheese melted smoothly. Combine melted cheese, bread crumbs and evaporated milk, along with cooked macaroni in large bowl.
Place back in microwave for 3 to 5 minutes on High.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add flour and sugar.
Add hot milk and butter.
Add salt and red pepper (if desired).
Add corn last. Bake 30 minutes at 350°, stirring twice.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Separate eggs placing whites in a large bowl.
Let egg whites warm to room temperature about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 300°. Grease 10-inch tube pan lightly (no flour).
With mixer on high speed, beat egg yolks with shortening and margarine until well blended.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add extracts; beat until well blended.

title: asian chicken salad
directions: Marinate chicken breast with Thai Dressing for 4 hours and grill or bake in oven.

title: eggless sweet rolls(or hot rolls)
directions: Mix all ingredients and knead.
Let rise.
Roll out and spread with cinnamon, brown sugar, raisins or chocolate chips.
Roll up and cut for sweet rolls.
Let raise and bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or cut as for hot rolls and let raise and bake.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Put in casserole dish. Mix soup and cheese.
Gradually add mayonnaise, milk and egg until well blended.
Pour over broccoli. Don't stir.

title: never fail chocolate cake(old family recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Add 1 cup boiling water, mixing well.
Pour into a large bread pan which has been greased and floured.
(I use a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.)
Bake for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: mama dale's drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco
or margarine.
Add egg; beat well. Add vanilla, sifted flour and soda.
Make out in balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass dipped in water.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach well.
Add other ingredients, blending well. Chill.
Serve with nacho cheese Doritos.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in two greased and floured 9-inch pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans.
Poke cake with a fork.
Don't remove from pans.

title: pork roast with tangy sauce
directions: Rub roast with salt, pepper, garlic salt and 1/2 teaspoon chili powder.
Place in roasting pan.
Roast at 325° for 1 3/4 hours. Combine jelly, catsup, vinegar and 2 teaspoons chili powder in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 2 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine milk, sugar and flour.
Beat with mixer at high speed (not quite one minute) until smooth and completely combined. Remove beaters.
Use rubber spatula to streak the dough with 1/4 cup cheese food.
Drop batter equally between 10 paper-lined muffin wells.
Drizzle top of each with 1 teaspoon liquid margarine and dust each with a little garlic powder, plus 1 scant teaspoon additional cheese food.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Add only enough flour so batter drops from spoon.

title: finger cake
directions: Melt butter, add cocoa and water; boil.
Pour over sifted dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Use jelly roll pan.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken in a small saucepan and bring to boil; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour
sauce over chicken. Cover and bake for 45 minutes
at 350°. Uncover and bake 30 minutes more, basting occasionally. Serves 4.

title: pumpkin harvest bread
directions: Combine all ingredients together by creaming all liquid ingredients, then mixing in all dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans (4 small or 3 larger).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes (may take longer).
Bake until toothpick comes out clean.

title: tomato chili relish
directions: Bag spices.
Add all ingredients in pot.
Bring to a boil. Cook over medium heat until slightly thick, stirring often.
Take out spice bag.
Put in sterile jars and seal.
Makes approximately 4 quarts.

title: apple cake
directions: Break eggs over apples, mix with a fork.
Add sugar, nuts and oil.
Sift salt, flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add to apple mixture.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: fresh orange cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda together.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and orange rind together, until very light and fluffy.
Mix in flour mixture alternately with orange juice and then mix in nuts.
Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until golden.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat to boiling point and pour over chicken.
Place chicken in oven with sauce.
Cook until done.

title: cow patties
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in the rest of the ingredients.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in a 1/2 cup of warm water.
Heat milk; add to the sugar and salt.
Stir melted butter; add to yeast to mixture. Stir until well mixed; add flour until dough is no longer sticky. Knead dough; let rise until double in size.
Knead again; form into rolls.
Place on baking sheet; let rise again.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: marge's waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apple cubes with sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Add celery, nuts and grapes.
Fold mayonnaise into whipped cream. Gently fold into apple mixture.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taylor made navy bean soup
directions: Wash beans 2 or 3 times.
Put in water and soak overnight. Next day, put all ingredients in slow cooker and simmer for several hours, until beans are done, approximately 8 to 10 hours.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Brown ground meat; drain and add to sauce.
Mix Ricotta and Parmesan cheeses, egg and parsley.
In ungreased dish, cover bottom with sauce.
Place 4 to 5 uncooked noodles.
Cover with 1/2 cheese mix and sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Repeat, using sauce, uncooked noodles and cheese until all ingredients are used.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High for 15 minutes.
Rotate 1/4 turn.
Cook on 50% for 15 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes while preparing salad and garlic bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix rice and chicken stock; cook as usual.
Mix remaining ingredients in large casserole dish with cooked rice.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chow mein candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips over hot water. Add chow mein noodles and salted peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook lasagna noodles as directed.
Cook and mash 8 potatoes. Mix potatoes with 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Use 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Butter bottom of dish.
Place 3 noodles on bottom of pan. Put 1/2 potato mixture on top, then another layer of noodles and rest of potatoes.
Then last layer of noodles.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine and onion on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: old fashion johnny cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together and pour into round glass pie plate.
Bake in 350° preheated oven; bake until toothpick comes out clean.

title: dip for tortilla, fritos chips
directions: Fry meat and set aside.
Melt cheese in microwave. Add meat and tomatoes to cheese and mix well.
Walla!
A tasty dip.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in shortening; add other ingredients and cook for a few minutes.
Add celery just before serving.
Serve on hamburger rolls.

title: carrot-orange loaf
directions: Stir together
flour,
baking
powder, soda, salt, allspice and nutmeg; set aside.
Combine orange peel and carrots; set aside.

title: bran muffins(makes 6 dozen muffins)
directions: Combine cereals; add hot water.
Cream sugar and margarine. Add eggs and cereal mix.
Sift dry ingredients in large bowl; add dates or raisins, nuts.
Mix dry ingredients alternating with buttermilk.
Yields one gallon batter.
Store in refrigerator in airtight container for up to 6 weeks.
Bake as desired at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brownies(with frosting)
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and bring to boil.
Pour into mixing bowl.

title: pickle and cheese crackers
directions: Mix crackers and cheese thoroughly until crackers are fine. Slice pickles in half.
Spread cheese-cracker on pickles and refrigerate for 10 minutes, then serve.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter in large skillet until tender. Add soups and 1 1/2 cups cheese. Gradually add milk. Cook over medium heat until cheese melts. Stir in chicken and macaroni. Pour mixture into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated. Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: creamy rice pudding
