directions: In medium saucepan, bring rice and water to a boil.
Simmer, covered, until rice is tender and most of the water absorbed, 25 minutes.
In a small bowl, stir together cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Stir into hot rice mixture with half and half.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Take off the heat and stir in butter and vanilla.
Stir some hot rice into beaten eggs, then add to saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring often, until mixture starts to bubble.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook the noodles in salted water until tender.
Rinse the noodles and drain.

title: 30 minute chocolate cake
directions: In saucepan, put water, cocoa and margarine.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and put over flour and sugar.
Mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one. Add buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan (9 x 12-inch).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Shake in a sack with mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Place coated biscuits in tube or Bundt pan.
Boil the margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon together.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: marinade for king mackerel
directions: Marinate fish in this for 2 hours.
You won't believe it! It's so good!

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Combine eggs and milk. Add dry ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Add corn.
Stir until well mixed.
Heat 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil in a skillet. Drop dollar size tablespoonfuls into the skillet.
Fry until lightly browned.

title: spicy buffalo wings
directions: Cut wings in 2 pieces and put in a bowl.
Mix butter and hot sauce.
Pour over wings that have been sprinkled with Cajun seasoning and stir.
Cover and marinate overnight.
Fry in hot oil.

title: plum whya
directions: Place fruit in pie shell.
Mix remaining ingredients together. Pour over fruit.
Mixture should be thick.
Top with cinnamon. Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean, about 40 minutes.

title: spinach or zucchini linguini
directions: Saute garlic in butter.
Add spinach or zucchini, sour cream and Parmesan cheese.
Serve over cooked linguini.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles in water.
Boil until tender; drain water.
Mix in tuna, mushroom soup, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Eat hot or cold.

title: pancakes
directions: Whip eggs; add milk, oil, salt and sugar.
Sift flour onto wax paper with other dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Cook pancakes on hot oiled griddle or in electric frying pan.

title: wassail
directions: Tie spices in a clean cloth and steep in 2 c. of water overnight or longer.
Mix all ingredients together and add water from steeped spices.
If too tart, add sugar or Sweet 'N Low to taste.
May serve hot or cold.

title: czech sauerkraut
directions: Saute onions in margarine until soft.
Add sauerkraut and sugar.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.

title: shelly's potatoes
directions: Mix all of the ingredients, except butter.
Sprinkle 2 cups crushed cornflakes, drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Cream the 2 tablespoons butter with 8 ounces cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Add 1 egg, 2 tablespoons milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; beat until smooth.

title: great-grandma's drop cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Add milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: Pat out crescent rolls into pizza pan. Bake and cool.

title: chocolate covered strawberry freeze
directions: Blend water, ice cubes, sweetener and strawberries until mixed well, then add Hi-Energy Chocolate Supplement and mix to desired consistency.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Press rolls into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, mayo and Ranch dressing together. Spread on cooled rolls.
Chop vegetables and sprinkle on mixture. Refrigerate until cold
before cutting into squares.

title: e z lemon chess pie
directions: Blend in blender and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 350° until set, about 35 minutes.

title: irish stew(stobhach gaelach)
directions: Cut meat into fairly large pieces.
Layer meat and vegetables in a deep pan, seasoning each layer.
Place potatoes on top. Add stock.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300°.

title: brown rice
directions: Put margarine, rice and onions in frying pan.
Cook until rice is light brown, stirring frequently.
Put mixture in baking dish; add consomme, mushrooms and a little pepper.
Cook in a 400° oven about 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: coconut chicken
directions: Pound chicken lightly; set aside. Beat eggs. Combine together bread crumbs, coconut and salt. Dredge chicken in flour; dip into beaten eggs and press firmly into crumb mixture. Repeat process for remaining chicken breasts. Deep-fry chicken in oil at 350° until golden brown. Finish cooking in 350° oven until it reaches internal temperature of 165°.
Serves 4.

title: brown sugared apricots
directions: Place drained apricots in bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine the crushed Ritz crackers with the brown sugar and crumble over the fruit. Drizzle the melted butter over the fruit evenly. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat on medium heat until cheese melts. Transfer to fondue pot. Serve using toasted Italian or French bread cut in squares to dip in sauce.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions in some vegetable oil over medium heat until translucent in a large skillet; add garlic and saute for another minute.
Crumble in beef and cook about 8 minutes, stirring a few minutes, until meat loses its pink color.

Stir in flour until blended, then stir in soup mix, broth, mushrooms and parsley. Cook about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until sauce thickens. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes until mushrooms are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve over hot noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Stir in next 6 ingredients (through pepper).
Unroll one package rolls and separate into triangles.
Place in a lightly greased 10-inch pie plate, pressing edges together to form pie shell.
Separate one of the eggs.
Set yolk aside.
Beat egg white with other eggs.
Pour half of the beaten egg over pie shell.
Spoon meat mix into shell.
Arrange cheese on top.
Spread with remaining eggs.
Unroll 2nd package of rolls.
Form a 12 x 6-inch rectangle.
Place dough on top of filling; trim, seal and flute edges.
Cut slits for steam.
Brush top with remaining egg yolk.
Loosely cover edge with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover center of pie loosely with foil and bake 20 minutes longer. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Add to cornmeal.
Stir in corn, cheese, onion, peppers and oil.
Bake in 9-inch greased baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 9 servings.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Combine and beat until fluffy the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, beating in one at a time.
Add flour and whiskey.
Mix well.

title: salmon loaf (diet)
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° until brown in a loaf pan.
Also can use a Corning Ware dish.
Serves 4.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Let cake cool and break into chunks.
Drop half of cake chunks into bottom of large punch bowl.
Combine strawberries and glaze. Pour this mixture over cake.
Spread half of pudding over strawberries. Spoon half of pineapple chunks over pudding.
Layer remaining ingredients in the same order as before.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle on chopped pecans, if desired.

title: delicious salad
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts together; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Put the beans with the sugar, oil and vinegar in a bowl and refrigerate.
Next day, add 1/4 cup chopped onion, 1/2 cup celery and 1/4 cup green pepper.

title: baked broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain well. Stir into casserole dish sour cream, soup and water chestnuts. Add broccoli and pepper to taste.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Parboil peppers for a few minutes.
Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes and toast.
Saute onion and celery in butter 2 minutes.
Add beef and saute, stirring, until done.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water and add it and the tomato juice to meat mixture.
Heat thoroughly.
Fold in bread cubes.
Fill peppers with hot mixture. Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake in greased shallow dish in 350° oven for 15 minutes, then in 400° oven for 5 to 10 minutes to brown top.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish with raw broccoli spears and cover with chicken.
Cover chicken with cheese slices.
Mix soup and mayonnaise and spread over cheese.
Top with water chestnuts. Bake uncovered for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with canned onions and bake another 15 minutes.

title: shower or party punch
directions: Soften sherbet and ice cream slightly.
Mix in pineapple juice.
Pour into large punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.
Serves 30 to 40 punch cups.

title: red cabbage(czerwona kapusta; polish)
directions: Remove outer leaves.
Quarter cabbage and shred.
Core apples and slice thin. Combine cabbage, apples, salt, butter, vinegar and 1/2 cup water in large skillet.
Cover.
Cook over medium heat for 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Add raisins and nuts if desired.
Use 9 x 15-inch pan ungreased.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Toast 4 slices of rye or whole wheat bread and crumble over top.
Sprinkle with butter.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses get to room temperature.
In a large bowl, put all ingredients, except nuts.
The easiest way is to mix with your hands.
Cream together all!

title: italian frittata
directions: Melt margarine in 10-inch pie pan in oven. Combine all ingredients except the cheese.
Pour into pie pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Top with cheese.
Continue baking until melted.
Makes 6 servings.
Cool for 5 minutes.

title: mega ginger cookies
directions: In a food processor or blender, whirl ginger and 1/3 cup of sugar until the ginger is

finely ground. Pour from the container. Put butter and 1/3 cup of sugar in the food processor, or beat with mixer, in a bowl until fluffy. Add the ginger mixture, molasses and egg and whirl or beat to

mix. Mix flour soda, cinnamon and nutmeg and add to the butter mixture and blend well. Cover the dough and chill until firm to the touch, about one hour. Shape dough into 1-inch balls and coat with the remaining sugar. Place the balls 2 to 3 inches apart on nonstick or oiled baking sheets.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Pound chicken breasts between sheets of plastic wrap until about 1/4-inch thick.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and oregano and blend well.
Heat oil and butter in heavy skillet on moderate heat until bubbling lightly.
Cook chicken breasts on medium heat until lightly brown.
As you turn breasts to second side, add mushrooms. Cook about 2 more minutes.
Stir mushrooms.
When lightly browned, add wine around chicken pieces.
Cover pan and simmer gently about 10 minutes.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together cheese, cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat after each addition.
Add 6 heaping tablespoonfuls of flour alternating with 1/2 pint sour cream.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until light brown. Turn off oven.
Open oven door and leave cake in oven for 1 hour.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown ground meat until finely cooked.
Crush chips in oblong casserole pan.
Mix ground meat and taco seasoning and pour half of mixture onto chips.
Cover with cheese.
Layer chips on top of cheese.
Repeat.
Pour enchilada sauce over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Ranch style beans can
be added to meat mixture. Finish by topping with shredded lettuce and tomatoes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place all ingredients in a blender at one time and blend until mixed together.
Pour into a buttered 10-inch pie pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Crust on bottom, custard in middle and coconut on top.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, mix the first 6 ingredients.
In another bowl, combine the next 5 ingredients.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Stir liquid ingredients into dry ingredients; stir until moistened.
Add raisins and nuts if you want them.
Spoon into loaf pan.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours in a 350° oven.
Cool on wire rack in pan for 10 minutes.
Take out; completely cooling.

title: rumaki
directions: Combine all ingredients except water chestnuts.
Marinate livers in sauce mixture overnight.
Place a chestnut slice in each liver piece.
Wrap with 1/2 strip of bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Place on broiler pan in center of oven.
Broil until crisp, 30 minutes.
Place in chafing dish with a little of the marinade sauce to serve warm.

title: snickerdoodles(cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs together thoroughly. Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt; stir into moist ingredients. Roll dough into marble-sized balls. Roll each ball into mixture of 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 2 teaspoons sugar. Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: apple taffy dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except apples and chill.
Dip apple slices into mixture.
Tastes like a taffy apple.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Mix at high speed for 1 minute.
Bake on greased griddle.

title: skillet pork chops
directions: Sear pork chops in oil until brown.
Remove and place on plate.
Add onion and garlic to skillet; cook 5 minutes.
Stir in broth, barbecue sauce and beans.
Heat until boiling.
Return pork to skillet.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 50 to 60 minutes, stirring sauce and turning chops occasionally.
Can bake this in the oven at 275° while at church.

title: apple cookies
directions: Put brown sugar, spices and salt in a large bowl.
Add shortening and egg.
Blend well.
Add flour and soda (which have been sifted together) alternately with juice or milk.
Add raisins and nuts.
(You may use 1 cup of applesauce and 1 box of raisins, but then add a little more flour.)
Drop onto cookie sheet and bake at 400° until done.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease muffin cups.
Mix all ingredients well and spoon into prepared pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine bread, milk and cream.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and mix well.
Stir into bread mixture and add vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in butter and raisins.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole and set in pan of water about 1-inch deep.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Serve with sauce.

title: canned apples for pies
directions: Shell amount of limas preparing to freeze and wash in cold water.
Place in large container and cover with water.
Bring to boil and boil approximately 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and drain.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain
broccoli;
combine
soup, mayonnaise, egg, onion and chicken.
Pour
into deep dish; put cheese on top.	Spread dressing mix over mixture. Drizzle melted butter over dressing mix.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: farmers breakfast
directions: Saute onion and potatoes in large skillet, in hot margarine until potatoes are slightly browned.
Cook, covered, 15 minutes or until potatoes are almost tender.
Stir in ham cubes.
Beat eggs with salt; pour over potato mixture.
Cook over low flame, occasionally slip spatula underneath potatoes and ham to let uncooked egg flow to bottom.
When eggs are set, sprinkle with cheese; cover skillet a minute or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tex mex dip or mexican pile up
directions: Take a round pizza pan and spread bean dip over entire bottom to make first layer.
Mix taco seasoning, sour cream and mayonnaise together and spread over bean dip layer, making sure second layer comes within 1/2-inch of pan edge.
Mash avocados and add lemon juice, which becomes the third layer.
Spread over second layer within 1/2-inch of pan edge.
Top with green onions, olives, tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: homemade chili
directions: In large cooker, simmer tomato juice, beans and chili powder. The amount of chili powder depends on each person's taste.
Start with 1 teaspoon and add more gradually, until it satisfies your taste.

title: fried cabbage and noodles
directions: Shred or slice the cabbage.
Add the salt.
Put in preheated, greased skillet and cover. Stir occasionally.
Chopped onion may be added.
In separate pan, cook noodles until done. Drain and add to fried cabbage mixture.
Mix thoroughly and season with salt, pepper and butter.

title: marshmallow fudge cake(this is a luscious cake - very gooey and very chocolatey.)
directions: Combine butter and sugar; heat until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time and vanilla.
Add syrup and flour, mixing well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
While cake is hot, spread marshmallow cream over top.
Pour fudge topping over all.

title: classic tuna casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, blend soup and milk.
Stir in tuna, eggs and peas.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until hot. Stir and top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Makes 8 cups.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar. Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Add syrup.
Chill until partially set. Add cranberry mixture, pineapple, walnuts and celery. Pour into oiled 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Best to set overnight.
Cut in squares. Serve on crisp lettuce.
Or you may want to put mixture in a glass bowl.

title: hot swiss cheese spread
directions: Stir together; pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° until bubbly (20 minutes).

title: popular dessert
directions: Slowly add milk to cream cheese.
Beat until smooth; add package of pudding mix.
Beat until well blended.
Add fruit cocktail and marshmallows; mix until well blended.
Refrigerate. Ready to eat in 1 hour.

title: pumpkin raisin cake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees and grease 13X9 pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and cloves.
Mix oil, eggs and pumpkin; add to dry ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake 40-50 minutes.
While cake is cooling, mix butter, cream cheese, powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Frost cake.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk and vanilla together.
Place stick of butter in long loaf pan and melt, then pour batter over melted butter.
Place fruit over batter and bake at 350° until brown.

title: jumbleberry pie
directions: Roll out half the dough 1/8 inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Fit into 9-inch deep dish pie plate, leaving 1/2 inch overhang.
In large bowl, toss together berries, cornstarch, sugar, lemon juice, nutmeg and cinnamon until mixture is well combined and place in pie crust.
Roll out remaining dough.
You can lay crust in lattice formation over top of pie.
Bake pie on baking sheet at 425° for 20 minutes, reduce heat to 375° and bake pie for 35 to 40 minutes more.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Place crushed berries in 8-quart kettle.
Divide whole berries in 3 equal parts.
Add 1 cup sugar to crushed berries.
Cook, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
When bubbles start to appear, start counting and boil exactly 4 minutes.
Add 1/3 whole berries and 1 cup sugar, stirring until sugar dissolves.
When boiling starts, count time and boil exactly 4 minutes.
Add the second third in the same manner and the 3rd and 4th.
Gently stir if necessary to prevent scorching.
Use care not to break whole berries.
Put in glass containers and let set 10 to 12 hours.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Saute onions and tomatoes.
Add green and red chiles and Velveeta.
Melt together. Serve with chips.

title: dakota potatoes
directions: Panfry bacon until done.
Remove bacon and place on absorbent paper to drain.
Add the potatoes and onion to the bacon fat and saute for 10 minutes.
Turn gently with a spatula to distribute the fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until potatoes are tender and tomato is slightly thickened, about 20 minutes.
Break the crisp bacon in small pieces and sprinkle over top when ready to serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Mix water, tapioca and 1 cup sugar.
Let boil until clear. Mix together the dry milk, salt, 3 tablespoons vanilla and the egg yolks.
Make sure to keep the egg whites.
Mix some of the hot mixture into the dry ingredients.
Stir remaining mixtures together.
Let mixture come to a boil; let cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla to whites. When mixture has cooled, fold in egg whites and serve.

title: firecracker enchilada casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a large skillet until the meat is brown and the onion is tender.
Discard the pan drippings.
Add the chili powder, cumin and salt.
Stir well.
Cook meat mixture 10 minutes over low heat.
Spoon meat mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2- inch baking pan.
Layer beans, tortillas and cheese over the meat mixture.
Pour the tomato liquid over the cheese.
Chop the tomatoes and spread the tomatoes
and green chiles over the cheese.
Spread soup over the top of the casserole.
Cover the baking pan; refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: zucchini pizza squares
directions: Mix together and set aside Bisquick, oregano and Parmesan. Mix together and set aside zucchini, pepperoni, Cheddar and garlic.
Beat eggs; stir in oil.
Add to Bisquick mixture and blend together.
Add zucchini mixture and stir until well blended. Spread in 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until top is golden brown.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top right out of oven if desired.
Enjoy!

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: To make crust:
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Stir in cracker crumbs until moistened and then press firmly into bottom of the pan.
Chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Stir together blueberries and glaze.
Spread evenly on chilled crust.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and gradually beat in sugar, vinegar and vanilla.
Continue beating until very stiff.
Fold in pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes or until firm.
Cookies should remain light colored.
Cool on racks.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen small cookies.

title: ham and green bean bake
directions: Layer beans, ham and cheese in square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth; pour over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, until golden brown, about 45 minutes at 350°.
Recipe can be doubled; use a 13 x 9 x 2 bake pan.
Bake about one hour.

title: texas hash(very good! try it)
directions: Brown meat, onions and pepper.
Add rice; add tomatoes, seasoning, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peppers stuffed with tuna
directions: Drain tuna and flake.
Combine with next 4 ingredients and salt and pepper to taste.
If using water-packed tuna, moisten with 3 to 4 tablespoons oil.
This makes about 5 cups filling.

title: laura zorn's cherry dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, spoon pie mix, spread pineapple over cherries, next sprinkle cake mix over pineapple.
Pour melted oleo over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Layer 1:
Dissolve lime jello in 2 cups boiling water as directed on packages.
Pour into 9-inch square dish, refrigerate until firm.

title: watermelon rind pickle
directions: Soak rind in cold water and pickling lime.
Next morning, rinse several times in ice water.
Place in large pot, bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Soak again in ice water.
Drain. Cover again with cold water.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1 teaspoon ground ginger and continue cooking over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Soak in ice water.

title: no-knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Put shortening and boiling water into one bowl.
In another bowl, mix eggs, sugar, salt and cold water.
Combine these two mixtures.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water and add to mixture.
Stir and beat in about 7 cups of flour.
This dough will not be nearly as stiff as kneaded dough and will stir without too much effort.
Put dough into 2 bowls, cover and place in refrigerator.
When dough is chilled, it's ready to make into rolls.

title: corn bake
directions: Mix and pour into 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: baskin-robbins pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and condensed milk together with mixer until lumps are gone.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into 2 butter crust pie shells.
In a skillet, toast the coconut and pecans in melted margarine until brown.
Sprinkle toasted coconut and pecans over the 2 pies.
Drizzle 1/2 of Mrs. Richardson's butterscotch-caramel fudge topping on top of pies.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: imperial chicken of tomorrow
directions: Blend bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken parts in melted butter, then in blended crumb mixture, coating thoroughly.
Arrange pieces on shallow pan in single layer. Drizzle remaining butter over chicken and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until thickest pieces are fork-tender.

title: potatoes o'brien
directions: Scrub potatoes well.
Pierce with fork and cook with skins on in microwave until almost done.
Slice onions and peppers into strips.
Cut potatoes (skins on) into bite size pieces.
Melt butter or oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add potatoes, onions and peppers.
Season and stir.
Cook, covered, for about 10 minutes.
Uncover and continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are cooked.

title: pull aparts
directions: Split rolls in half.
Put ham and cheese, then put back together.
Melt margarine, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion flakes.
Pour over rolls. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: favorite pound cake "1954"
directions: In one bowl, sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add in shortening and eggs.
Mix 3 minutes with mixer.
Add in milk and vanilla.
Mix 2 minutes.
Pour batter into a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan, greased and floured.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: congealed grapefruit salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; let stand 5 minutes.
Drain grapefruit, reserving juice.
Add enough water to juice to measure 2 cups.
Combine liquid and sugar in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Remove from heat; add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Stir in grapefruit sections.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in the bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Layer ham, cheese and mushrooms on top of bread. Beat eggs; add milk, onion flakes, parsley flakes, salt and pepper. Pour over mixture in dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until puffed and brown. Serve at once. Serves 4 to 6.

title: broiled zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on broiler pan and brush with butter.
Combine cheese and Italian seasoning in bowl and sprinkle on zucchini.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.
Serve with Ranch dressing.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk until it forms a soft ball when a little is dropped into cold water.
Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Whip and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly and pour at once into a buttered pan. When firm, cut in squares.

title: wedding punch
directions: Put sherbet in large punch bowl.
Add 7-Up or Sprite.
Will make a foam on top of punch.
Serve immediately.

title: lemon pie(no calories)
directions: Mix together and put in crust.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: venison stew
directions: Marinate cubed venison in French
dressing for 12 to 14 hours. Drain off salad dressing
and
place venison in crock-pot.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover
and
cook
on low setting for 8 to 10 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dilled muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom only of 9 muffin cups.
Mix all ingredients.
Fill muffin cups about 1/2 full.
Bake until golden brown, about 15 minutes.

title: barbecued chipped ham
directions: Simmer slowly all ingredients, except chipped ham, until onions are tender.
Shake in chipped ham.
Heat through.
Serve on warm buns.

title: date nut balls
directions: Melt in pan the oleo, then add sugar, 1 beaten egg, pecans and chopped dates.
Cook these 5 ingredients
for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat; add cereal and vanilla.
Put butter on your fingers.
Pick up little "patties" of mixture and roll into balls.
Then roll balls into coconut and put into the mouth and eat.

title: chile bean dip
directions: Drain beans; save liquid.
Place drained beans liquid, vinegar and seasonings in a blender; blend until smooth.
Stir in onion and parsley.
Chill and serve.
Season to taste with more chili powder and cumin if you like.
Also good with salsa added.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Heat together about 1/2 to 3/4 hour, turning frequently.

title: cheese balls
directions: Stir all ingredients by
hand.	Use
half of the pecans in mixture.
Roll mixture
into
balls.
Cover outside of each ball with other half of pecans.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In large pan, crumble hamburger, add onion and cabbage.
Add enough water to cover and cook until cabbage is done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together twice.
Cream butter and sugar for 10 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating smooth after each addition.
Stir in flavoring. Pour into 10-inch greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven; turn on at 325° and bake 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Put 3 egg whites in a bowl.
Stir.
In separate bowl, combine 3 egg yolks and 2 cups milk.
Beat.
Add egg/milk mixture into flour mixture and stir in 1/2 cup oil.
Fold egg whites into mixture.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together until marshmallows and cream cheese dissolve. Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple and chopped pecans. Chill until firm.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until tender.
Drain and combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise and peas.
Blend soup and milk; heat thoroughly.
Add noodle mixture.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: curried broccoli dip
directions: Prepare broccoli in cheese sauce according to package directions.
In blender, place broccoli mixture, sour cream, Parmesan cheese, lemon juice, minced onion and curry powder. Cover and blend until mixture is smooth.
Chill to blend flavors. Serve with crackers or veggie dippers.

title: steamed tomato and zucchini
directions: Wash and sort pinto beans or use canned kidney beans.
For every 1 cup dried beans placed in saucepan, add 3 cups water. Bring to boil.
Simmer until tender.
Add water as needed.

title: wethani kyet - fried pork curry(origin:  burmese)
directions: Remove any bones from pork, cut away skin and cut the meat and fat into 2.5 cm (1-inch) cubes.

Put onions, garlic and ginger into container of electric blender and blend, stopping and starting motor if necessary, until onions, garlic and ginger are mushy. Turn contents of blender into a nylon strainer set over a bowl and push with the back of a spoon to extract as much liquid as possible.
Pour this liquid into a large saucepan.
Add the pork, salt, vinegar, chili powder and half the peanut oil.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer over low heat for 1 1/2 hours or until pork is almost tender.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Wrap slice of bacon around each breast.
Place layer of dried beef in bottom of baking dish.
Arrange chicken on top.
Cover with soup, sour cream and cream cheese that has been blended together.
Cover lightly with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.
Remove foil; brown slightly.
Serve on bed of rice.
Serves 6.

title: coconut cake 2
directions: Bake cake according to box.
While the cake is hot, poke holes in it.
Pour condensed milk and cream of coconut in the holes.
Let cool and top with Cool Whip and coconut.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: chicken rose
directions: *One and one-half pounds of chicken parts will yield about 8 ounces of cooked meat.

title: mardi gras punch
directions: Mix all liquid ingredients in a large punch bowl.
Stir together to blend well and thaw concentrates.
Stir in ginger ale. Add sherbet, scooped into balls.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Fry and drain hamburger meat.
Bake pie shell until light brown, about 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
While shell is baking, prepare mashed potatoes with the 6 potatoes.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Mix jello, water and raspberries.
Let dissolve.
Add applesauce and pineapple.
Mold and chill.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Make a well in mixture and add remaining ingredients; mix.
Pour into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chinese roast pork
directions: Cut pork into 3 lengthwise strips.
Combine soy sauce, beef broth, brown sugar and garlic; pour over.
Cover; refrigerate 2 hours, turning meat frequently.
Remove from marinade; place on rack in roasting pan.
Add few tablespoons water to prevent smoking.
Roast at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or well done.
Turn and baste with marinade.
Cut in thin slices.
Serve with sesame seed and Chinese mustard.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: donna's whole wheat bread
directions: In small bowl, dissolve 1 teaspoon raw honey in 1 cup very warm water.
Add yeast; stir and let sit for 15 minutes.
In very large bowl, put 6 cups water, applesauce, salt and 1/3 cup raw honey. Stir.
Add whole wheat flour and stir.
Add yeast mixture to the large bowl and stir well.
Add enough whole wheat flour until you can't stir anymore, then add white flour (high gluten bread flour) and knead.
Keep adding white flour as you knead so as to make smooth dough.

title: blackberry cream pie
directions: *After making blackberry
jelly,
I
take the seeds and pulp in jelly bag and run through a "Squeezo strainer" (or use any kind of food mill
that	will
extract the seeds, or press mashed blackberries through a strainer or sieve).

title: banana split cake
directions: With the drained pineapple juice, pat the sliced bananas in it, then drain them and add to recipe.

title: ranch macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and cool.
Mix together remaining ingredients and chill.

title: garfish patties
directions: Combine all ingredients; form mixture into patties.
Fry in oil until golden brown.

title: suzie's potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
When finished, peel and cube while hot.
Add chopped onion and mayo.
Stir in cheese.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with bacon and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: butterscotch zucchini bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, margarine, egg, water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Mix well. Stir in zucchini and nuts.
Spread in greased and floured 9-inch square or round pan.
Sprinkle with butterscotch chips. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool. Cut into bars.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: pumpkin bread bars
directions: Sift dry ingredients; set aside.
Beat eggs; add oil, sugar and pumpkin.
Add to dry mixture, beating in well.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes about 24 bars.
May be frosted with soft icing.

title: chess pie squares
directions: Mix 1 egg and 1 stick of oleo with the cake mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: strawberry ice
directions: Combine sugar and water; bring to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes. Cool slightly.
Add strawberries and lemon juice.
Pour into freezer tray; freeze.

title: carrot-nut cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat shortening, sugar and egg yolks in large bowl at high speed for 3 minutes.
Finish mixing by hand.
Stir in carrots, walnuts, orange and lemon juices.
Stir in flour mixture a little at a time.
Beat egg whites in small mixer bowl until soft peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Spoon into pan and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cake should be light golden. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Be sure all ingredients are at room temperature.
Do not preheat oven.
Cream together until fluffy the butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk starting and ending with flour (4 flour, 3 milk), beating well after each addition.
Add flavors last and beat well.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until straw comes out clean.

title: brown bottoms
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and egg. save chocolate chips until just before using. Set aside.

In Large bowl, mix remaining ingredients. Mixing by hand (about 15 strokes). Do Not Over Mix. Will be lumpy. Line miniature cupcake tins with baking papers. Now add chocolate chips to cream cheese mixture. Put 1 tablespoon of chocolate mixture into papers. Top with 1 teaspoon of cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 15-20 min.

title: my aunt rachel's banana cake
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and bananas together.
Add egg. Add wet mixture to mixture of flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nuts and mix well.
Pour batter into a 9-inch round mold that has been greased and well floured.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool completely before removing from the mold.

title: chicken with rice casserole
directions: Cut chicken breasts into thin strips.
In a greased casserole dish, mix soup, rice and water.
Stir well.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture; do not stir.
Top with butter and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Mixture should not be soupy.

title: grandma's mint sandwich cookies
directions: In a bowl, combine the frosting, extract, and food coloring if desired.
Spread over half the crackers; top with remaining crackers.
Place candy coating in microwave safe bowl.
Microwave on high for 1-2 minutes or until smooth.
Dip the cookies in coating.
Place on waxed paper until chocolate is completely set. Store in an airtight container at room temperature.
Yields:
3 dozen.

title: crowd pleasing dip
directions: Beat all ingredients in small bowl at medium speed until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with vegetables or baked potato.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy, adding sugar 1 teaspoon at a time.
Beat until very stiff.
Add vanilla and food coloring if desired.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop on cookie sheet that has been lined with foil.
Put in preheated 305° oven and turn oven off.
Leave in oven until cool or overnight.

title: chicken in the chips
directions: Mix chicken soup, sour cream and picante sauce until blended. In a 2-quart buttered casserole, place a layer of chicken.
Add a layer of cream chicken mixture, a layer of grated cheese and a layer of corn chips.
Repeat layering.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° preheated oven for 30 to 40 minutes, or until bubbly.
Garnish with additional picante sauce.
Serves 4.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain and combine with drained tuna (Bumble Bee fancy albacore in water).
Add mayonnaise, onion, green pepper and, if desired, celery.
Blend soup and milk, heating through. Chicken soup can be used instead of mushroom.
Add cheese.
If preferred, Mozzarella in the same amount can be used.
Heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add to noodle mixture and turn into 2-quart casserole.
Top with almonds, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 20 minutes.
Put under broiler to make crispy, if desired.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add pumpkin, sugar, salt and spice; mix well.
Add milk; stir thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 35 to 40 minutes, until set and browned.

title: fred's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter, then gradually add both sugars, beating well.
Beat in eggs.
Add salt and baking soda to flour. Gradually stir in flour to butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Press lightly with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(Will not look done on top.)

title: broccoli neopolitan
directions: Heat oil.
Add onion and garlic.
Stir until onion is golden. Blend in flour until smooth.
Stir in water and cook 2 minutes. Add all other ingredients, except cheese.
Stir, reduce heat and cover.
Cook on low heat until broccoli and carrots are tender. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: salsa
directions: Peel and seed tomatoes.
Seed peppers.
Chop all fresh vegetables coarsely.
Combine with chilies in bowl; mix well.
Let stand for several hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pound cake
directions: Have butter and eggs at room temperature.
Cream butter well. Beat in sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and gradually add flour.
Mix to a silken consistency.
Pour into well-greased 9 or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven for one hour or until cake springs back. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Cool completely on rack.

title: carrot cake with pineapple
directions: In a large bowl, beat the eggs.
Add sugar, carrots, oil and nuts.
Sift together
flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix with sugar mixture; add the crushed pineapple including the juice and mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for one hour at 350°.
Cool.

title: citrus baked halibut
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Thaw fish if frozen.
Arrange in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in parsley, orange peel, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Spread over fish.
Sprinkle orange and lemon juices over all.
Bake, covered, in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Spoon pan juices over fish.
Serves 4.

title: marinated steaks
directions: Sprinkle tenderizer on meat, then add remaining ingredients in Ziploc bag or in plastic bowl; seal.
Let stand 2 hours or up to 2 days.
Grill or broil in oven.

title: chicken divan crescent squares
directions: Form crust with rolls; sprinkle cheese over crust.
Spread broccoli over cheese.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Beat butter and margarine.
Add sugar, flour and oatmeal. Mix well.
Chill dough.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add seasoning. Roll ground beef mixture in leaves. Place in casserole dish. Pour tomato sauce over cabbage mixture.
Add 1 can water. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil and drain potatoes.
Add all ingredients except bacon and cheese.
Stir until blended, simmer until onions are tender and soup thickens.
Stir in bacon.
Serve soup topped with grated cheese.

title: orange glazed red beets
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt and stir in 6 tablespoons orange juice.
Pour mix over drained beets in casserole and dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, mix 1 cup sugar, flour and water.
Stir until moistened.
Add 2 cups milk and 3 egg yolks.
Place on stove and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
When thickened, add margarine, vanilla and coconut.
Cool.
Pour into baked and cooled pie shell.
Beat 4 egg whites with dash of cream of tartar until peaks form.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Put on top of pie.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: cheesy ham croissants
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread ham slices with mustard and sprinkle chives over cheese slices.
Cut each slice of ham and cheese in half.
Place 1 slice of cheese on top of 1 slice of ham. Top with second ham slice and finish with cheese.
Repeat to prepare 4 ham and cheese stacks.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cook and freeze, or can in jars and seal.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: savory rice
directions: Heat butter in a saucepan.
Add onion and cook over low heat until golden brown.
Add rice and cook until lightly brown and rice is done.

title: spectacular squash
directions: Combine stuffing mix with melted butter and press 1/2 of it into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Lightly steam squash and onion until barely cooked.
Drain thoroughly.
Combine soup, sour cream and grated carrot.
Fold in cooked squash and onion.
Gently spoon mixture over stuffing in casserole dish.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until stuffing browns and bubbles around the edges.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In large kettle, saute onions and garlic in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and 6 cups water.
Simmer covered for 2 hours.

title: potato filling balls
directions: Mix well and use ice cream dipper to form balls.
Place in baking dish.
Pour over a little additional melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes in 375° oven.
Can be made and put in freezer to use later as fresh potato balls.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs well; add salt, pepper, paprika and sugar.
Beat until light and foamy.
Add milk.
Place corn in greased baking dish.
Pour egg mixture over corn.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: layered bean dip
directions: On a round cake or sandwich plate spread the ingredients in the order given. Refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together well.
Place in baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients with enough water to form sauce.
Pour over meat loaf in pan.
Bake at 375°
for 1 hour.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Using a spoon, mix together sugar and pinto beans.
Stir in melted margarine.
Then add eggs and stir well.
Then add coconut and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: pecan pie i
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: apple relish
directions: Remove seeds from oranges.
Core apples.
Put oranges (peeling and all), apples and raisins through food grinder.
Add sugar, vinegar and spices.
Cook until tender.
Put in jars and seal.

title: doughnuts
directions: Add enough flour to roll; cut and fry in deep fat.
To sugar them, put 1/2 cup sugar in paper sack.
Put in 2 or 3 at a time and shake.

title: cream crab soup
directions: Mix together in double boiler.
Add crabmeat last.

title: what'cha call em squares(low-fat; low cholesterol)
directions: Heat oven to 350° and grease 9-inch square pan.
Mix sugar and margarine in mixer.
Add Egg Beaters and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, water, vanilla, dates and nuts.
Bake about 30 minutes until golden brown and tests clean with toothpick in center.
When cold, cut in squares.
Put swirl of maple flavored icing on top of each and place pecan piece on top of each.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine cake mix, nuts and melted butter.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: slovak chicken paprikas
directions: Brown onions lightly in the fat.
Add paprika and chicken; sprinkle with salt.
Cover and cook about 1 hour or until tender. Pour sour cream and parsley over chicken.
Heat for 1 minute only. Serve over noodles.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine and mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: meat balls with mushroom soup
directions: Toast bread; soak in chicken and rice soup. Mix all ingredients with meat. Shape meat mixture into balls and brown in fat. Put meat balls in casserole dish and cover with cream of mushroom soup mixed with 1/2 can water. Cover casserole and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: 3 bean sausage chili
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add chopped onion and pepper.
Add this and all the rest together in a slow cooker and slow cook for several hours.

title: tra-la-las(italian cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Work in flour and baking powder to make soft dough, enough to roll into small ropes and twists.
Bake at 375° until brown on bottom.
Cool and ice.

title: roast and gravy
directions: Place roast in a casserole dish.
Mix together onion soup mix, cream of mushroom soup and water.
Pour over roast.
Cook for about 3 or 4 hours at 300°.
Check with fork after 3 hours to see if tender
Makes its own gravy.

title: watergate salad(green salad)
directions: Sprinkle pudding over pineapple.
Add marshmallows, nuts and Cool Whip.
Blend.
Serve chilled.

title: scallop bake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with melted butter.
Stir in scallops, parsley, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Put in shallow casserole and top with Parmesan cheese (enough to cover top).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (15 minutes covered, 10 minutes uncovered).

title: cookie dessert
directions: Press cookie dough into 12 inch pizza pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350 for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in pan. Beat softened cream cheese, 1/2 c sugar and cocoa with electric mixer on high until well blended.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread cream cheese mixture over crust; top with strawberries and chocolate chips.
Serve or cover and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin ice cream bars
directions: Make a graham cracker crust and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Melt quart of ice cream.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients. Freeze 24 hours.
Serve frozen.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat in sour cream.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake 350 for 30 minutes. Turn off oven and leave for 1 hour. Cool 8 hours before serving. Add any topping you like.

title: chocolate icebox cake
directions: Melt chocolate bits over hot water.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in beaten egg yolks.
Fold in 1 pint whipped cream and melted chocolate bits.
Line loaf pan with ladyfingers.
Spoon over with cream mixture.
Cover top with 1/2 pint sweetened whipped cream and sprinkle with chopped nuts!

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare peppers (hull).
Wash peppers. Boil in 1 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook 5 minutes and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients; stuff peppers.
Stand upright in ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover.
Bake 45 minutes. Uncover; top with any cheese.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: lemon torte
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Cook egg yolks, sugar and lemon juice until it coats the spoon.
Add gelatin and let stand to cool.
Beat egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Whip 1/2 pint cream and fold in.

title: date cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Cream butter and cheese together.
Blend in flour and salt. Chill for several hours or until firm enough to roll.
Roll to 1/8-inch thickness on board sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Cut in 1 x 3-inch strips with pastry wheel.
Put a date in center of each strip and roll up.
Put, folded side down, on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Can sprinkle powdered sugar on each. Makes 8 dozen.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble cooled, baked cake.
Layer 1/2 cake crumbs in a punch bowl.
Top with 1/2 each of pie fillings, drained pineapple, bananas and Cool Whip.
Repeat layers, using remaining ingredients.
Garnish with coconut, cherries, nuts or whatever you wish.

title: double chocolate drops
directions: Cream shortening and cocoa.
Add next 4 ingredients; mix well. Stir in dry ingredients; mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Remove quickly.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 dozen.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix and beat eggs and sugar.
Add corn. Bread crumbs and margarine to be added on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for about an hour.
When knife is clean, casserole is done.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: french toast
directions: Take the egg and beat it until fully made into a mix.
Then take the 1 1/2 cups of milk and mix it with the egg in a bowl. Next, take 1/4 teaspoon of vanilla and put it in the mix.
Then take the bread and dunk it in the mix.
Next put the bread with the mix on it and put it in a frying pan.
Heat the bread until it is a golden brown.
When it has reached this idle point, flip the bread over.
Then, take out the bread when it is golden brown on both sides and add a touch of cinnamon and lots of powdered sugar.
The French toast can also be served with syrup.

title: shortcake
directions: Grease 9-inch round or square pan.
Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until particles are fine.
Combine milk and eggs.
Add to dry ingredients all at once; stir until all dry particles are moistened.
Spread dough into pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.
Cut in wedges; split, then fill and top with sweetened fruit and whipped cream.

title: mexican cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sharp cheese together.
Add in 1 cup of sour cream and the taco seasoning.
Beat in eggs.
Fold in chilies. Pour mixture into a spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Take out of oven and cool for 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup of sour cream to top of cheesecake, spread and bake for 5 more minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Cover and refrigerate.
Run a knife around edge of pan and remove.
Top with salsa and serve with chips as a dip.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, butter and paraffin; bring to a boil.
Add peanuts and cook on medium heat until golden brown (or approximately 20 minutes).	Stir well.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon soda.
Stir well and spread on aluminum foil while foaming.
Let cool thoroughly.
Break up and store in airtight container.

title: cheese sesame snacks
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick and softened margarine.
Stir in sesame seed and water until soft dough forms.
Drop by scant teaspoonfuls into cheese; roll in cheese to coat.
Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden, 7 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen appetizers.

title: apple muffins
directions: Grease 2 (12 hole) muffin pans; set aside.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, cream together butter, eggs and sugar. Reserve 3 tablespoons flour.
In medium bowl, combine remaining flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add vanilla to apple juice.
Alternately add apple juice and flour mixture to creamed butter and egg mixture.
Place apples in large bowl; sprinkle with reserved flour and turn gently until apples are lightly coated, then fold into batter.
Fill each muffin pan 3/4 full and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until muffins pull away from sides of pan and turn golden brown.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter; set aside.
Combine spinach and onions in a large bowl; toss well.
Combine the next 6 ingredients; mix well.
Add dressing and mushrooms to spinach mixture; toss gently.
Sprinkle salad with egg and bacon.
Yields 6 servings.

title: double-nut party mix
directions: Preheat
oven
Heat peanut butter with oil in large shallow roasting pan (about 15 x 10 x 2-inches) in oven until shiny
and	soft
(about
5 minutes).
Remove.
Stir in seasonings until
mixture is smooth.	Add Chex and nuts.
Mix until all pieces are coated.	Heat in oven 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes. Spread on absorbent paper to cool.	Makes about 9 cups.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash or zucchini and onion together for 5 minutes.
Add sour cream, chicken soup and carrots to drained squash.
Melt 1/2 cup butter or margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add herb seasoned mix.
Remove 1/2 the stuffing mix and save for the top.
Put squash mixture on top of the crumbs.
Add remaining crumb mixture on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: roast duck
directions: Fill cavity with peeled, quartered apples.
Close with skewers.
tie legs and wings close to body.
Rub with onion slice, salt and pepper.
roast, back side up, uncovered, at 325 degrees 1 to 1-1/2 hours.
Baste every 10 minutes with orange juice.
Large Ducks such as mallards will serve two.
Small ducks such as teal serve one adult.

title: jalapeno-cheese dip
directions: In medium bowl, beat cheeses until blended.
Add rest of ingredients.
Blend.
Keeps refrigerated up to 1 week.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.
Serve with crackers or corn chips.

title: cheese tea sandwiches
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add red pepper, if desired.
Set aside.
With a 1 3/4-inch cookie cutter, cut 2 rounds out of each bread slice.
Spread half of bread rounds with cheese filling.
Top with cucumber slices if desired and remaining bread rounds.
Place in shallow container and cover with plastic wrap.
Top with a damp dish towel and refrigerate 8 hours.
Yields 16 sandwiches. Sandwiches may be frozen, omitting cucumber.
Thaw in refrigerator and add cucumber before serving.
Flavored cream cheese may be substituted for the cheese filling.

title: quick and easy cherry jello(kids love it!)
directions: Prepare jello as directed.
Add cherry pie filling and let it set.
Dessert can be dotted with spray-on whipped cream, if desired.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Boil mixture of first 4 ingredients 2 minutes.
Stir in 3 cups oatmeal.
May add nuts or coconut.
Pat mixture into pan to cool. Cut into squares.

title: rocky road
directions: Butter square pan.
Melt chocolate chips over low heat.
Add milk; stir and add vanilla, nuts and marshmallows.
Pour into pan. Press down and chill.
Cut and eat.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice
green
tomatoes	into thin slices.
Dip in 1 cup milk or buttermilk, then dip into corn meal.
Season to taste. Fry until brown on both sides in small amount of vegetable oil and margarine on medium heat.
Serve warm.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour into casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Crush Ritz crackers and spread over top.
Pour melted margarine over top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal-rice krispies cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well. Add 1 cup flour, soda, vanilla, baking powder and salt.
Mix remaining flour, oatmeal, Rice Krispies and coconut together, then add to creamed mixture.

title: pull taffy
directions: In heavy saucepan, cook sugar until it dissolves.
Add remaining ingredients; cook to hard ball stage, stirring occasionally.
Pour into buttered pan; let cool.
When still warm, butter hands and pull taffy until it has a satiny finish.
Cut to desired sizes; wrap in waxed paper.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: In medium saucepan, combine powdered sugar, milk, chips and butter.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in vanilla.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut and season steak.
Roll in flour.
Heat oil in large skillet and brown steak strips on all sides.
Add onions, peppers and 1 cup water.
Simmer 10 minutes stirring occasionally.
Add tomato juice, tomatoes and sugar.
Simmer 30 minutes, covered. Serve over bed of rice.

title: fruit pie
directions: Bake 2 pie crusts; let cool.
In a large bowl mix the milk and lemon juice.
Fold in fruit, then Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into cooked pie crusts.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: jigglers
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin.
Dissolve completely.
Pour mixture slowly into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Slice zucchini paper thin and put in large mixing bowl.
Add onion.
In separate bowl, combine other ingredients and pour batter over zucchini and onion.
Stir to thinly coat zucchini with batter and pour into sprayed 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Recipe should make 4 to 5 dozen 1 to 2-inch pieces or 6 servings as an entree.

title: crockpot macaroni
directions: grease pot with Crisco. Put layers of macaroni and layers of cheese, use two layers of Velveeta as well. Mix rest of ingredients and pour over the top of macaroni and cheese. Sprinkle top with paprika. Cook on low about three hours and thirty minutes. Cheese lovers put 3 cups of sharp cheese.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix together eggs and oil; add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Then add strawberries and nuts.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Blend together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Stir in mashed bananas.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Blend into creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan or tube pan which has been coated with additional butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together and set aside 2/3 cup of batter. Press remainder into a greased 9 x 13 pan.

title: devil tuna dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough mayo and plain yogurt or sour cream to make "dippy."

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken in microwave on high ( 8 minutes per pound). Grease 9x13-inch pyrex dish.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch strips. Cut up chicken into small chunks, mix with onion, soups, milk and green chilies.
Make 2 layers of tortilla strips, chicken mixture and cheese.
Rich and Creamy!

title: meat loaves
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Form into 5 or 6 tiny oblong loaves.
Place on cookie sheet and brown under broiler for 7 to 8 minutes or until pink has disappeared.
While loaves are broiling, combine the catsup, vinegar and brown sugar.
These ingredients should form a thick glaze.
Pour mixture over meat loaves and broil for approximately 5 more minutes.

title: praline cookies(pecan crisps)
directions: Pam a jelly-roll type cookie sheet and line with graham crackers.
Break each cracker in half so there are sections of two.
Melt butter and margarine together.
Add sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil 3 minutes.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour over crackers. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cut into individual crackers while hot.

title: pizza beans
directions: Drain green beans; place in bottom of 9-inch round baking dish. Slice tomatoes over top; drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with onion, salt and oregano.
Top with cheese slices.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave for 10 minutes until heated through.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and about 1/2 cup water; bring to a boil.
Add broccoli; cook for 3 minutes.
Add rice; boil again. Remove from heat; let set for 15 minutes.
Stir in soup and cheese; top with crushed chips or bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in a large shallow dish. Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir well and pour over chicken.
Cover and marinate chicken in the refrigerator 2 hours.
Remove chicken from marinade, discarding marinade.
Grill chicken over hot coals about 8 minutes on each side.

title: chicken cornbread casserole
directions: Melt oleo and 1/2 dressing. Put in bottom of baking dish. Layer remaining ingredients in this order: chicken, sour cream, soup and milk mixed, remainder of dressing. Pour broth over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy squares
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add flour and blend.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Beat well and add lemon juice.
Put in greased 11 x 17-inch pan and spread.
Mark with knife into 40 squares.
Place 1 tablespoon pie filling in each square.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Break up angel food cake. Layer angel food cake, then strawberries, then glaze, then Cool Whip.
Repeat.
Chill about 1 hour before serving.

title: meatball casserole
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, egg and salt.
Shape into about 18 meatballs.
Brown in skillet or oven.
Drain.
In Dutch oven or deep skillet, combine browned meatballs, water, rice, carrots, green pepper and onion.
Cover and simmer about 25 minutes or until vegetables are cooked.
Add cheese and heat until melted. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening, eggs, baking soda, salt and sour cream.
Stir in flour.
Dough will be soft.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll out and cut. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: s'mores
directions: Grease pan. Heat syrup, butter and chips to boiling. Stir constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla. Pour over cereal. Toss until coated. Fold in marshmallows, one cup at a time. Press into pan lined with wax paper. Wait one hour.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Melt butter, add flour and sugar and mix.
Spread thinly on pizza pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Mix together the peanut butter, margarine, sugars and milk. Add remaining ingredients.
Form into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° in oven (on middle rack).
Take out, put a chocolate Kiss in the center and return to oven for 1 minute.

title: spicy rice casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook sausage, cumin and garlic powder, stirring often; drain.
Add onions and green peppers.
Saute until crisp tender.
Dissolve bouillon in water; add to skillet. Stir in green chilies, rice and rice seasoning packet.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered 5 to 10 minutes or until water is absorbed.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients on medium speed.
Pour in greased/floured loaf pan (glass or metal). Bake at 325 degrees for about 1 hour. Cool for 10 minutes and turn out of loaf pan.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1/2 can milk.
Spread 1/2 mixture in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Melt caramels and remaining 1/2 can milk in microwave or double boiler. Add chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour over cake mixture in pan. Top with remaining cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions.
Reserve liquid from artichoke hearts and mix with 1/3 cup mayonnaise.
Toss ingredients together.
Add reserved liquid and mayo mixture.
Refrigerate. Best served next day cold.

title: cucumber appetizer
directions: Mix all together the first three ingredients, thinning if necessary with milk.
Spread on bread slice, top with slice of cucumbers.	Garnish with slice of olive or sprinkle on dillweed.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Bring 1 cup berries, 3/4 cup sugar, 3/4 cup water and lemon rind to a boil in a saucepan.
Combine remaining sugar, water and cornstarch; stir into boiling berries.
Cook for about 1 minute or until clear and thickened.
Cool.
Place remaining fresh berries in a baked pie shell.
Cover with the cooled glaze and chill until completely set.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix with spoon (do not use mixer).
Pour into 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool cake completely before taking out of pans.

title: greek tiropetes-cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
In another bowl, mix cheese with 1/2 pound melted butter.
Add eggs and mix well.
Line an 11 x 14 x 2-inch pan with 10 buttered sheets of filo.
Add egg-cheese mixture and top with 8 buttered sheets of filo.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into small squares and serve warm.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Add apples, nuts and raisins. Stir in oil and eggs. Mix well. Pour into 9 x 13 greased pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 55 minutes.

title: apricot fluff
directions: Boil jello, water and sugar for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add cream cheese, baby food and pineapple.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix ingredients; shape into a ring.
Chill.
Fill center of ring and cover top with strawberry preserves.

title: golden lamb celery seed dressing
directions: Mix mustard, salt and sugar.
Blend in blender or food processor, onion, vinegar and sugar mixture.
With machine on, slowly add small amount of oil.
Blend in celery seed.
Serve on greens, fruit salad or shredded cabbage.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: fresh strawberry glace pie
directions: Line pie shell with berries, reserving 1 cup for glace. Simmer cornstarch, sugar and water until clear.
Add 1 cup berries and cook until colored and thick (not very long).
Add lemon juice and cool.
Slowly pour over berries in shell and chill.
Decorate border with piped whipped cream.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Brown rice and onion in butter.

Spread rice mixture in buttered pan. Add soup and broth. Place chicken on top of rice and broth mixture. Cover in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish tightly and bake for 1 hour. Remove cover. Bake 15 minutes more. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken asparagus delight
directions: Boil and cool chicken; debone and cut into bite-size pieces. Drain asparagus and spread in bottom of buttered casserole. Top with the chicken.
Mix the mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and cheese; pour over the chicken.
Mix the crackers and melted butter, then sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Boil noodles until tender and drain.
Mix soup, milk and salt; heat, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over noodles; mix well.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in hot oven (375°) in uncovered dish about 30 minutes.

title: peppered cheese
directions: Mix cheese, fines herbes, chives, Worcestershire sauce and garlic.
Scrape bowl with spatula.
With hands, shape cheese into a wheel.
On wax paper, roll the shaped cheese into the seasoned pepper.
Pepper should cover entire wheel of cheese.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush Oreos into crumbs.
Mix with Cool Whip and ice cream. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and nuts; let stand for a few minutes.
Beat eggs slightly and add oil and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add flour mixture and apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan.
Add peanut butter.
Stir. Mix in well the graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.
Melt the chocolate chips and "frost" mixture in pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Be sure to cut before chocolate gets too hard or will crack when cut.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Use muffin cups or grease cups.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
On low heat, melt margarine and honey.
Remove from heat.
Cool; add milk and egg.
Add wet to dry mixture.
Stir only until moist.
Stir in blueberries gently. Fill cups 1/2 full.
Bake 20 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine butter, oil and sugars in large mixing bowl; mix well. Add eggs and beat 1 minute until well blended.
Add vanilla; beat well.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda and cream of tartar; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Place frozen Tater Tots in bottom of casserole dish.
Place cheese slices on top of Tater Tots.
Place cooked ground meat on top of cheese.
Pour 1 can cream of mushroom soup on top of ground meat.
Cover with more cheese slices.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: french coconut pie(makes 3 pies)
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar, milk, vanilla, coconut and melted margarine.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: cherry pineapple sauce for ham
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for about 10 minutes until hot. Raisins can also be added of desired. Put in a bowl and pass at the table with slices of ham.

title: breakfast in a muffin cup
directions: Spray muffin cups with Pam. Cook bacon until partially browned. Put each bacon in a muffin cup forming in a ring.
Drop eggs into each cup. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a 350° oven until eggs are cooked and bacon is crisp. This is great when you have a crowd to feed.

title: everyday cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugars and oil.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well so oil does not separate.
Add flour, mixed with cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
St ir in rice cereal, oats, coconut and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake on lower shelf of oven for 5 to 6 minutes.
Move to middle of oven and bake until slightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Watch carefully so cookies do not become too brown.
Remove from sheet and cool.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Finely chop the first 5 ingredients.
Soak gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve in hot water and let cool.
Stir in mayonnaise. Add vegetables.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Spread over bottom of 10 x 15-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 25 minutes (350°) in oven.
Sprinkle top immediately with chocolate chips.
Spread melted chips around to cover evenly.
Sprinkle fine nut meats over top.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter flavored Crisco and sugar in a large bowl at medium speed of electric mixer.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour with baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: carne pecada con-papa(spanish; hamburger, meat and potatoes)
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion and drain.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Add diced potatoes and 1 small can of tomato sauce.
Add enough water to just cover meat and potatoes. Stir; bring to boil.
Cover and simmer until all water is absorbed.

title: southern buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix oil and milk; pour in flour and stir, forming sticky mixture.
Place on floured board, knead 5 or 6 times.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 475° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: pepperidge farm puff pastry cookies
directions: Pepperidge Farm pastry comes frozen (defrost 20 minutes before using).
Spread with thin layer of jelly
and brown sugar.
Roll both ends toward the center.
Slice and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until bottom is golden brown.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all together.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice and boil carrots until tender. Cool. Slice onions, chop pepper and mix with carrots. Combine remaining ingredients in medium bowl, to make a marinade; pour over vegetables. Cover and chill at least 6 hours. Serve cold.

title: funghi ripieni(stuffed mushrooms)
directions: Wash mushrooms; remove stems and chop them.
Heat 3 tablespoons olive oil in small saucepan and steam onion and garlic about 5 minutes.
Add bread crumbs and fry 2 to 3 minutes, until crisp.
Add parsley, mushroom stems, ham, cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Put mushrooms "cap up" in ovenproof dish.
Stuff with filling.
Add a few drops of olive oil.

title: favorite chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift cake flour together with baking powder and cocoa 2 times. Cream shortening with 2 1/4 cups sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Then alternately add dry ingredients with wets (milk and vanilla).
Then fold in egg whites, beaten to peaks and into which 3/4 cup sugar has been incorporated.
Cut waxed paper to fit bottom of 10-inch tube pan.
Grease the paper and dust with cocoa after placing in pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 to 30 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 30 minutes.
Turn out carefully.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: prime rib
directions: Place in roasting pan on rack in a 375° oven.
Cook, uncovered, with fat side up 1 hour and 15 minutes. Turn oven off and do not open for 5 hours.
Forty-five minutes before serving, add freshly ground pepper (optional).
Return to 300° oven until serving time.
Roast may be rubbed with a mixture of gourmet pepper, salt, onion powder, garlic powder and paprika before cooking, if you prefer seasoning.

title: superb slaw
directions: 1. Place shredded cabbage in bowl in layers alternating with sliced onion rings.
2. Top with sugar. Bring rest of ingredients to boil in
sauce pan. Pour this over the cabbage while still hot.
Cover and refridgerate 4-6 hours.
3. Mix and serve. Keep stored in refridgerator.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda and salt together.
Make a well in the center.
Mash strawberries well.
Add eggs and oil.
Combine with flour mixture.
Mix well. If batter appears too dry, add reserved juice or 1/4 to 1/3 cup milk.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake 1 hour.
Let loaves cool completely.
Serve with fruit butter.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: dump cake
directions: Put layer of cherries in bottom. Drain juice off pineapple and put over cherries. Put layer of powdered cake mix. Slice butter and put on in layer. Spread coconut over top of cake. Sprinkle on walnuts. Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or well done.

title: yorkshire gingerbread
directions: Grease and line a 12 x 8-inch pan.
Preheat the oven to 350°. Gently heat margarine, sugar and syrup until just melted.
In a bowl, sift the flour, ginger and cinnamon; mix well until evenly colored.
Stir in the melted mixture.
Beat the eggs into this mixture.
Warm the milk until lukewarm; add the bicarbonate of soda.
Beat well until smooth and even (mixture will be very soft).
Pour mixture into greased pan and bake for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
