Leave in the baking pan for about 10 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: apricot smooch
directions: Line pie
plate
with
1/2 cup of the crushed wafers or crackers.
Cream
butter
and
sugar thoroughly.
Add egg yolk and almond
extract
and cream some more.
Spread over crumbs. (For easier
spreading,	dip knife in egg white.) Put apricots in blender
or
food
processor
and
mince fine.
Spread over mixture.
Cover with whipped cream, beaten stiff, and top with 1/4 cup crumbs.
Let chill in refrigerator at least 4 hours.

title: strawberry - banana pie
directions: Mix lemonade, cream cheese and lemon juice in electric mixer until well blended.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: golden glazed chicken
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat in saut pan.
Add honey, mustard, curry powder and salt; mix well to blend.
Place chicken in baking dish and cover with the butter-honey mixture.
Bake, uncovered, basting often at 350° for 1 hour or until fork-tender.

title: diet red applesauce salad
directions: Heat applesauce.
Dissolve jello in hot applesauce.
Let cool. Add cold water and stir.
Set in refrigerator.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper. Pound into steak.
Brown meat and onion in hot fat.
Add tomatoes. Cover and cook over low heat or in oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: melanie's apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat oil and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes in
a 9 x 13-inch pan. Frost with icing.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain off the fat.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Put 2 cups of cabbage in a 2-quart casserole dish; top with half the meat sauce.
Cover with remaining cabbage; pour meat sauce over top.
Cover with casserole lid or foil; bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 45 minutes.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: mint juleps
directions: Combine crushed mint and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove and discard mint. Add sugar; return to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Remove from heat and set aside.
For each serving, fill a glass with 1 cup crushed ice.
Add 1/4 cup bourbon and 1 tablespoon mint syrup, stirring gently.
Garnish with a fresh mint sprig.
Yields 48 servings.

title: sweet and savory ribs
directions: Place onion in 5-quart cooker; top with the ribs.
Combine the barbecue sauce, syrup, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over the ribs.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 9 hours or until the meat is tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pig licking cake and icing
directions: Mix until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker fruitcake
directions: Crush all honey graham crackers.
Mix with pecans and raisins. Melt marshmallows in milk over low heat.
Allow mixture to cool. Stir in crackers, pecans and raisins.
Pour into cake pan and place in refrigerator 4 to 6 hours.

title: nana's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift flour and add slowly to mixture, beating constantly. Add cream (not whipped) and vanilla.
Grease and flour tube pan. Put cake in cold oven and set at 325°.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook sausage, then place on top of bread evenly.
Mix together eggs, milk, salt, mustard and pepper.
Pour this over bread and sausage evenly.
Top with 8 ounces shredded cheese.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Put crackers in blender 2 at time to make crumbs.
Add margarine.
Shape into an 8-inch pie pan (bottom only).
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.
Make pudding to directions, then add peanut butter to pudding.
Pour in pie pan and refrigerate for 1 hour. Makes 4 servings.

title: cold weather soup
directions: Cook cabbage until half done. Add all ingredients and cook slowly until done.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Melt butter and add flour, seasonings and milk.
Cook this 3 minutes and stir in cheese and heat until melted.
Add macaroni and beef; heat 5 minutes.
Pour into casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and broil until lightly browned.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat the eggs and add the remaining ingredients in this order: sugar, flour, salt, syrup, butter, vanilla and nuts. Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: mom's slick dumplings
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Add more flour just until you create a soft, moist dough.
Flour a counter top and put dough in center.
Using a floured rolling pin, roll dough to approximately 1/8 inch to 1/4 inch thick.
Taking a sharp knife, cut the dough into rectangles approximately 2 inches x 3 inches. Take roast drippings and add enough water to make about 3 inches of broth in bottom of large saucepan.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
If you are short on drippings and the water dilutes it too much, add beef bouillon cubes to make extra fluid or canned beef broth.
Gently peel dumplings from counter.
Add them to boiling broth one at a time and immerse them totally before adding the next dumpling.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Use previous recipe with following change:
use 1/3 cup firmly packed brown sugar.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix; put in large iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add alternately with milk.	Bake in a tube pan at 275° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: christmas eve seafood delight
directions: In large saucepan, brown finely diced or crushed garlic and onions with olive oil.
Add cans of tomatoes and tomato puree. Cook 20 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, basil, fine cut celery leaf, marjoram and parsley.
Cook for 1 hour and add water, if evaporating.
Clean and wash all fish.
Scrub clam shells and crab legs.
Cut snapper and flounder in half.
Place in sauce (shrimp, scallop, calamari).
Cook 5 minutes.
Add crab legs, snapper, mushrooms and clams.
Cook another 5 to 10 minutes.
Add wine and sugar.
Cook 3 minutes.
Boil macaroni until tender, not soft; drain.
Pour seafood sauce over and serve.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt together and serve with raw vegetables or chips.

title: finger licking cake
directions: Grease pan with butter and line bottom of pan with marshmallows.
Drain pineapple (save juice).
Mix cake as directed.
Use pineapple juice in mix.
Pour the mixture over the marshmallows.
Spread the crushed pineapple over the mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cube.
Mix Pepperidge Farm dressing according to directions on package.
Save 1/3 mixture for topping.
Combine cubed chicken with soup, milk, mushrooms and onions.
Mix well. Put 2/3 package of dressing on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; add chicken mixture.
Top with the remaining 1/3 dressing.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp or clam dip
directions: Beat with mixer until smooth.
If needed, add milk or mayonnaise to thin.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugars and shortening together.
Add egg.
Add flour, oats, salt, soda, vanilla and nuts.
Mix at medium speed until well mixed.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar.
Cover cranberries with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add walnuts and bake for 15 minutes. Stir in orange marmalade and lemon juice.
Chill.

title: richmond maids of honor(english tarts)
directions: Heat the oven to 375°.
Grease a muffin pan.
Fit a biscuit into the bottom of each muffin cup.
Place a spoonful of jam over each biscuit.
Beat together the sugar, margarine, egg and almond extract.
Stir in almonds.
Spoon some of this mixture into each muffin cup.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Remove the biscuits from the pan.
Cool.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium saucepan; cook until it forms a ball over medium heat, stirring constantly.
It will go fast.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large covered saucepan, cook onions in butter over low heat about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover and add salt, sugar and flour.
Stir well.
Add beef broth and Worcestershire sauce; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Place one slice of bread in oven-proof bowl and pour soup over bread.
Place 1 slice of cheese over each bowl.
Place in broiler until cheese is light brown and bubbling, about 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin crunch cream pie
directions: Pour milk into mixing bowl.
Add pie pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes. Blend in pumpkin, spices, almonds, chips and 2 of the whipped toppings.
Spoon into pie crust.
Chill 4 hours.
Just before serving, garnish with remaining whipped topping.

title: quick baked pasta - family style
directions: Bring 4 quarts of water to a boil.
Heat a large frying pan and add the oil, beef and garlic.
Saute until the meat is tender and then drain excess fat.
Add all remaining ingredients except the Mozzarella or Swiss topping cheese and the pasta.
Simmer the mixture while the pasta cooks according to package directions until just barely tender.
Drain the pasta and mix it with the sauce.
Pour all into a 3-quart glass, rectangular baking dish and top with the remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly hot.
Serves 6.

title: beef medley soup
directions: Cook meat in margarine 2 to 3 minutes, breaking up.
Add next 6 ingredients and 1 1/2 quarts water.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients (vegetables) and simmer 1 hour longer.
Enjoy.

title: orange-coconut balls
directions: Crush wafers to fine crumbs.
Add next 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Form into balls.
Roll in flaked coconut.
Freeze.
Serve frozen.
I find it delicious without sugar.

title: creamed asparagus on toast
directions: Cook the asparagus with salt until tender.
Pour milk over vegetables.
Add thickening with cornstarch.
Butter toast.
Pour over toast.
Dribble bacon bits over top; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup and Velveeta.
Cook until vegetables are tender (about 30 minutes).
Add soup and cheese, stirring constantly over medium heat just until cheese melts.

title: anchovy and cottage cheese dip
directions: Put cottage cheese through a sieve.
Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Saute onion.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, onion, sour cream and salt.
Add potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lea ann's pork chop bake
directions: Brown pork chops in lightly greased skillet.
Season with salt and pepper; set aside.
Combine soup, milk and sour cream.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan (spray with Pam).
Arrange pork chops over potatoes, Bake, covered, for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 more minutes.

title: baked potato skins
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly and prick several times with a fork. Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Allow to cool to touch. Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving about 1/4-inch thick shells, reserving pulp for other uses.

title: chinese salad
directions: Saut 1/2 or 1 cup sesame seeds, and 1/2 to 1 cup slivered almonds and add to mixture.

title: ham, potato, and green bean casserole
directions: In large saucepan place items in layers.
Season.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Add cheese and mix well.

title: raisin squares
directions: Cover raisins with water and simmer until plump. Add applesauce and simmer for a few minutes more. Add flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well. Cool and make a rich pie crust.
Line cookie sheet with crust.
Put raisin mixture on crust and spread.
Cover with the rest of the crust.
Perforate crust with fork. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When done, sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: apiece cakes
directions: Put eggs in 1 cup; fill with milk.
Mix dry ingredients like pie dough.
Add milk and eggs last.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls (uncooked)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Try rolling into dry cereal, wheat germ or coconut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pizza pronto
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Spread pizza sauce over crust to within 1-inch of edge.
Sprinkle with three quarters of cheese.
Place in oven according to package directions.
Bake for 7 minutes. Meanwhile, in 12-inch skillet over medium high heat, heat oil. Add zucchini, pepper and salt.
Cook uncovered for 3 minutes until zucchini are almost tender, uncovering to stir twice.
Remove pizza from oven, maintaining oven temperature.
Using slotted spoon, spoon zucchini over pizza, alternating with pepperoni slices.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and chopped roasted red pepper.
Bake for 3 to 4 minutes until cheese melts.

title: chicken breast with wine sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients but chicken.
Pour over chicken breasts in baking dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 90 minutes. Baste often.

title: cookie pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars, margarine, vanilla and egg. Stir in flour and baking soda (dough will be stiff).
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread or pat dough in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan or on cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown; cool.
Just before serving, spread cookie with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with walnuts, coconut and chocolate candies.
Cut into wedges.
Refrigerate any remaining cookie.
Makes 16 servings.

title: old settler beans
directions: Brown bacon, onion, hamburg and kielbasa together.
Drain most of grease off.
Mix sugars, ketchup, dry
mustard, salt and pepper.
Add to meat mixture.
Combine with beans in 3-quart casserole and bake, covered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients together.
Put into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Makes about 4 dozen appetizers after slicing.

title: creme puffs
directions: Bring water and Crisco to boil	and add flour and salt. Keep stirring until it won't stick
to
pan,
about
1 minute; cool. Add
eggs, one at a
time,	beating
after	each
one. Grease cookie sheet; put heaping
teaspoon
of dough on sheet. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 400°.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Cut top off baked dough; fill with
cooked
custard.	Put top back on and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together, using the cornbread mix dry.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
The last 10 minutes remove from oven and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: rice consomme
directions: Place rice in a baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Cook, covered, at 350° for about 45 minutes or until liquid has boiled out.
Do not overcook.

title: custard on top of stove
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, pinch of salt, milk and vanilla.
Put in double boiler, sprinkle with nutmeg.
Put lid on and cook on medium heat 21 minutes or until when you insert knife blade will come out clean.

title: colonial seed cake
directions: Combine poppy seed and milk in a large bowl.
Let stand at room temperature 3 to 4 hours.
Let butter and eggs warm to room temperature.
Grease and flour large loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Add butter, eggs, sugar, vanilla, baking powder and flour to bowl.
Beat at medium speed with mixer for 1 minute, scraping side of bowl with plastic spatula.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until center springs back when lightly pressed.
Cool on wire rack 5 minutes.
Loosen around edges; turn out of pan to cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add zucchini and flour that has been sifted with the other dry ingredients.
Stir well and add nuts.

title: parfait perfection
directions: Drain tropical fruit salad. Combine cottage cheese, yogurt and raisins. In 4 parfait glasses or glass bowls, layer cottage cheese mixture, fruit salad and granola. Serves 4.

title: strawberry trouffle
directions: Prepare angel food (Time Saver: use store prepared angel food cake).
Blend pudding mix with milk; fold in Cool Whip.
(Save 1 cup for top layer.)
Layer into trouffle bowl: cake, pudding mix, strawberries and kiwi and repeat.
Top with Cool Whip and strawberries or decorate as desired with kiwi.

title: clam sauce
directions: Heat oil; saute garlic.
Add tomatoes.
Cook until tender, but so tomatoes retain some shape.
Add water, seasonings and parsley. Add clams.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm over 1 pound thin linguine or capellini.

title: granny's forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil (ungreased).
Beat egg whites until foamy; add cream of tartar. Very slowly add sugar.
When mixture is stiff, add pinch of salt, nuts, chips, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Mix well.
Drop mixture on foil by scant teaspoon.
Place in oven; turn off heat at once.
Do not open door until morning or at least 8 hours.

title: apple glazed sweet potatoes
directions: In a 3-quart oblong baking dish, arrange drained sweet potatoes.
In a small bowl, combine glaze, nuts and vanilla; spoon evenly over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring once during baking.

title: double maple muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in oatmeal. Add egg, milk and syrup.
Stir only until moistened. Divide dough into 12 greased muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: spinach dip
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish:

title: lit'l link wraps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unwrap cornbread dough.
Separate along perforated edges and cut each section in half to make 32 short pieces.
Wrap each Lit'l Smokie with a piece of dough, pinching ends to seal.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased baking sheet at 350° until golden.

title: rocky road chocolate silk pie
directions: Prepare crust. Stir in marshmallows and nuts. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 1 hour. Garnish. Makes 8 servings.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Crush Doritos chips slightly in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Place cooked chicken pieces on top of chips.
Combine rest of ingredients except cheese.
Cook.
Pour over chicken and cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(This can be prepared and refrigerated the day before serving.)

title: layered salad
directions: Tear lettuce by hand and make a 1 to 2-inch layer in the bottom of a clear glass salad bowl.
Follow with a layer of celery, pepper, onion and mushrooms.
Make sure peas are thawed; pat dry with paper toweling and add to top of salad.

title: rich chocolate pudding(four servings)
directions: Coarsely chop the chocolate.
Set aside.
Stir sugar and cornstarch together in small saucepan until thoroughly blended. Gradually stir in milk until blended.
Add chopped chocolate. Cook, stirring over medium, until chocolate is melted and mixture begins to boil.
Cook, stirring, until thickened, about 5 minutes. Stir in vanilla and salt.
Pour into four custard cups.
Cool at room temperature before serving.
Whip the cream, if used.
Add a spoonful to each.
Dust with cocoa powder or garnish.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and put into oblong pan.
Beat the eggs, oleo and powdered sugar with electric beaters for no less than 15 minutes.

title: pork and bean bread
directions: Beat sugar and oil. Add eggs, beans and boiling water.
Beat well. Add flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and baking powder which has been sifted together.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Bake in greased pans at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 1 real loaf or 3 small ones.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix as usual for
cake.
Bake in 1 loaf pan at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes. Recipe may be doubled.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs well.
Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in flour, baking powder and salt.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture into a greased and floured tube pan.

title: lemon cake
directions: Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool and poke holes in the top of the cake with a fork.

title: clam fondue
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread.
Have ready round loaf of bread. Slice a lid off the top and hollow out the center just enough to fill with the fondue.
Put on the lid and wrap in foil. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Serve as is with dipping pieces.

title: vera's vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
It's better if refrigerated overnight.

title: ham quiche
directions: Brown pie shell first and pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
This is good for a quick meal.
Make ahead and freeze.
Just make a salad.

title: scallops and vegetables
directions: Brown bacon in nonstick skillet.
Remove to paper toweling to drain.
Drain off all but 1 tablespoon of fat from skillet.
Add onion and scallops; cook, stirring, until scallops are white, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove.
Add mushrooms and snow peas to skillet; cover and cook 3 minutes.

title: unfried fries
directions: Preheat oven at 425°.
Toss potatoes with oil and cayenne. Grease baking sheet with Pam.
Bake 40 minutes, turning once. Sprinkle with parsley, garlic and salt.
Toss. Bake 5 minutes.

title: texas trash
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat, onion and pepper until vegetables are tender.
Drain off any fat.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper; heat through.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix with remainder of ingredients.
Put in refrigerator.

title: pineapple cheese
directions: Place pineapple and juice in a 6 x 10-inch or 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cut oleo into flour and mix into pineapple.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Top should be golden.
Serves 8.
May be served with ham.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: jello fluff(kids' favorite)
directions: Put pudding and tapioca in pan.
Add 3 cups water.
Cook until thick.
Remove from fire.
Add Jell-O and stir until mixed.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool one hour in fridge.
Add Cool Whip and mandarin oranges.
Mix well.
Put in fridge two hours before serving.

title: whipped frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until it thickens.
Set aside to cool. Beat butter, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Pour into flour and milk mixture; beat.
Add vanilla.

title: peach cream cake
directions: Cut cake into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange 1/2 of the slices in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In large mixer bowl, mix condensed milk, water and extract until smooth.
Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill for about 5 minutes, then blend in whipping cream. Pour 1/2 mixture over cake, then 1/2 peaches, then layer cake, cream mixture and end with peaches.
Cool for at least 4 hours. Cut into squares and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until thick and lemon color.
Add zucchini, flour, baking soda, salt cinnamon, baking powder, walnuts and raisins.
Stir until moist. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix and put in Bundt cake pan and bake for 1 hour at 325°. Eat with cream cheese or frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: chocolate caramel layered squares
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup milk in pan.
Stir constantly until caramels are completely melted.
Remove from heat.
Combine dry cake mix, remaining 1/3 cup milk and butter; stir until dough holds together.
Press 1/2 of cake mixture into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels over crust. Pour caramel mixture over chocolate morsels, spreading evenly. Crumble remaining cake mixture over caramel mix.
Return to oven for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool.

title: orange pineapple bread
directions: Combine jam, honey, egg and vanilla.
Add pineapple.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix pretzels and butter to make crust.
Put in pan.
Bake crust 8 - 10 minutes until light brown.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together and put on crust.
Mix jello with water, directions on pkg.
Add strawberries to jello and mix together. Put on top.
Chill overnight.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Mix jello, water and juice.
Heat to dissolve.
Cool; add other ingredients.
Mold.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Saute garlic and onion in olive oil.
Add green beans with liquid to mixture.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add artichoke hearts and cook for 5 more minutes, mixing well.
Add bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Place in a covered casserole and cook in oven for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: peach cobbler supreme
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch shallow baking dish.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add milk and stir well.
Pour this mixture into baking dish; do not stir.
Top with peaches that have been drained a little.
Sprinkle nutmeg, cinnamon and lemon peel over top; do not stir.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with Cool Whip or ice cream. Cobbler will form crust while cooking.

title: easy roast beef
directions: Place the roast in a white plastic bag and pour in the marinade.
Marinate for night or for 1 day in the refrigerator. Wipe off the marinade and crack the peppercorns.
Sprinkle the cracked pepper over the roast and smooth with the back of a spoon. Preheat oven to 400° and place the roast in the oven for 30 minutes.
Continue roasting at 325° until internal temperature is 170°.

title: chop suey
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Blend flour and meat in skillet until meat is browned.
Combine onion and celery, stirring constantly, for 10 minutes.
Add water, salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Mix thoroughly to a boil (or when veggies are softened), then add bean sprouts.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Serve over chow mein noodles.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt.
Stir in buttermilk and well beaten egg yolks.
Mix well.
Add melted butter and beat until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff (not dry). Fold into batter very gently (if batter is too thick, add a small amount of buttermilk).

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Saute beef in oleo.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt; stir.
Add Italian sauce and stir.
Simmer over low heat for 5 minutes.

title: frozen chocolate brickle dessert
directions: Crush Oreos and mix with 1/3 cup melted butter.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover cookie mixture with melted ice cream.
Cover with plastic.
Freeze.
Heat and boil for 3 minutes, chocolate, milk, 1/4 cup butter, sugar and salt.
Cool.
Pour on top of ice cream.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: hot fudge walnut pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, stir together 3/4 cup granulated sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk, butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour batter into 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Stir together remaining 1/2 cup granulated sugar, brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle mixture evenly over batter.
Pout hot water over top; do not stir.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Top with walnuts and whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peggie's pina colada cake
directions: Prepare as on box (one 6 ounce package coconut to batter). Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from oven.
Take fork and punch holes in hot cake. Pour cream of coconut over hot cake. Cool for a few hours and frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with remaining coconut. Nuts are optional. Enjoy.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pudding mix with all ingredients, except Cool Whip; mix thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill 4 to 6 hours or overnight before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and mix well.
Add milk, then gradually add onion, mustard and cheese.
Add potatoes; bring to a boil.
Boil seven minutes.
Put in a casserole or baking dish. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or microwave about 15 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
May add 1 1/2 to 2 pounds of cubed ham instead of cheese.
Add salt if not using ham.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all together and bake until firm.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Scrub ham with a stiff brush.
Soak overnight in cold water. Pour water off.
Put in a pot, large enough to be able to cover ham with water all of cooking time.
Cover with cold water and bring to boiling point.
Reduce heat so that it will simmer (never cover while cooking).
Add water, as necessary, to keep ham covered with water.
Cook until temperature reaches 160° on meat thermometer or 25 minutes per pound.
Remove from water at once. Remove skin and score fat.
Sprinkle with black pepper.
Put in oven at 350°
to 400° and bake until fat is browned, about 10 minutes.

title: ice cream sandwich cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together cookie mix, butter flavor packet, egg and water.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Soften ice cream slightly.
Make sandwiches with 2 cookies and ice cream. Wrap each in plastic wrap and store in freezer.

title: sole thermidor
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 1-quart saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter; brush over sole.
Sprinkle with seasoning.
Roll up each fillet and place seam side down in greased shallow baking pan. Melt milk, 3 tablespoons butter and flour and stir.
Pour 1/2 cup of mixture over fillets and bake for 25 minutes.
Melt cheese, sherry and paprika and stir; after baking fish, pour the remaining milk mixture into cheese mixture and pour over fish, broiling until brown.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken, chilies and chili sauce and mix sour cream and salt with it.
Fry tortillas 5 seconds on each side so that they're limp.
Fill with chicken mixture.
Roll and spread sour cream and then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Just before serving, add 1 quart of 7-Up.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Marinate chicken for at least 2 hours or overnight in garlic, barbecue sauce and liquid smoke.
When ready to cook, brush cooking oil over chicken and bake in oven until tender, about 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.
A few minutes before it is done, brush barbecue sauce and honey on each piece.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Roll out wafers until floury.
Melt butter and sugar together. Add eggs and wafers.
Add coconut and pecans.
Add milk and vanilla extract.
Pam a Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Melt butter in a heavy 12-inch skillet over moderate heat.
Add onion and cook, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
Add the mushrooms and cook 2 to 3 minutes or until tender.
Add the half and half to the skillet. Raise heat to high; bring to a boil, reduce heat to moderate and simmer for 6 to 8 minutes or until the sauce thickens.

title: orange fluff
directions: Boil together water, pudding and Jell-O until clear, about 4 or 5 minutes.
Refrigerate overnight.
With electric mixer, mix in Cool Whip.
Add oranges or strawberries.

title: glazed carrots and turnips
directions: Peel the vegetables and cut into 3-inch julienne strips. Cook in a saucepan with the apple juice and 2 cups of water until tender. Drain and discard the liquid. Add the butter, honey, lemon juice, milk, nutmeg and pepper. Cook, uncovered, for 3 minutes more over medium heat, stirring to glaze.

title: ten minute barbecue sauce
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan and saute onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover over low heat for about 10 minutes.
Makes 2 cups.

title: cookies and cream
directions: Smooth 1/2 inch of Cool Whip in bowl or baking dish.
Dip cookies, one at a time, in milk for 2 seconds, then place on Cool Whip.
When cookies have covered one layer, put Cool Whip on top for 1/2 inch.
Continue making layers until all cookies are used. Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill until served.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter and cheese.
Add soup and sour cream; mix with potatoes.
Put in large baking dish.
Cover with crushed cracker crumbs.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Chunks of ham may be added.

title: fruit cookie pie
directions: In medium bowl beat together sugars and butter until light and creamy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually blend into butter mixture until moistened.
Press dough evenly into 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove and cool.
Spread with the pudding, leaving 1 inch all around the edge.
Arrange fruit decoratively on the pudding.

title: scripture cakes
directions: For those who would rather avoid the research.

title: heavenly milk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the pie crust.
Pour into the unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, or until lightly browned.
Cool before serving.

title: cheese ring
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup pecans in oiled 7-cup mold.
Press cheese mixture into mold. Chill until firm.
Unmold and put remaining nuts on top.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix well and press in bottom of 12 x 8-inch glass dish.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add spaghetti sauce, water, sugar and salt.
Simmer a few minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put a layer of uncooked noodles, warmed sauce and cottage cheese. Repeat layers, putting sauce on top.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top of sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting.

title: dirty rice
directions: Chop onions, garlic and bell pepper.
Mix in all ingredients that are left.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 325° in oven. Remove from oven in 15 minutes.
Stir, then place back in oven for about 20 minutes or until done.
Cover with foil.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix first nine ingredients and cook on Medium-low for 15 minutes.
Add last two ingredients, a dab at a time, until desired thickness.
Cook until potatoes are soft.

title: killer cookies
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese and sugar. Beat in egg yolk and vanilla. Add food coloring to portions of dough if desired. Gradually add flour, stirring well. Scoop dough onto waxed paper and press into disc. Wrap dough and chill at least 2 hours. (will remain fresh refrigerated for 2 days). Preheat oven to 300 degrees, form chilled dough into small balls (smaller than walnuts). Set
balls 1 in. apart on ungreased cookie sheets and flatten with bottom of glass dipped in flour. Decorate as desired. Bake 18 - 24 min.
edges should be brown, but not the bottoms. Cool before serving.

title: health juice
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and cover.
Run on liquefy until smooth.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and add sugar. Stir in cool whip and vanilla. Pour in pie shell, spread blueberry pie filling over the pie. Refrigerate.

title: zingy italian meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, sausage, onion, garlic, bread crumbs, parsley, Italian seasonings, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Add the eggs, tomato juice and wine; mix thoroughly.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: In one pot, add cauliflower to water.
Cook until tender.
In second large pot (must be large enough to hold contents of both pots), saute diced onions and celery in butter.
Onions are done when they become transparent.
Slowly add flour to butter, onions and celery.
Stir well to remove any lumps.
When cauliflower is boiling, pour entire contents of that pot into butter-flour mixture.
Be sure to stir rapidly; a wire whip works best and get close to the edge of pot.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Add half and half slowly, stirring until desired consistency is reached.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and bake on a lightly greased cookie sheet in oven at 350° until cookies are lightly brown.
Will make about 36 cookies.

title: carrots au gratin
directions: Boil carrots in salted water for 5 minutes and drain.
Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Slowly add flour, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix egg whites, cream cheese, mustard, oregano, pepper, garlic and parsley in large bowl.
Add rutabaga, onion, parsnip and potatoes.
Mix well.
Coat a 3-quart baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour ingredients into dish. Bake 1 1/2 hours or until top is brown and crisp.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
After removing from oven, roll in mixture of confectioners and granulated sugar.
Yield depends on size of cookie.

title: cream of anything soup
directions: In large pot, melt butter.
Add vegetables and scallions and cook, stirring often, until vegetables are soft but not browned (about 20 minutes).
Add chicken stock, wine, parsley, lemon juice, tarragon and sugar.
Simmer, covered, about 30 minutes until vegetables are very soft.
Puree soup in blender or food processor and transfer to large bowl.
Add heavy cream and stir thoroughly.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: rum balls
directions: Crush wafers and nuts in blender.
Add syrup and rum slowly, just until ingredients hold together.
Shape in small balls and dust in powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Combine everything except the chocolate chips.
Press ingredients onto cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on top.
Cut before chocolate gets too hard.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat crescent roll dough into an ungreased cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes or until brown. Cool.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot.
Simmer until hot.
Stir frequently as stew will stick to bottom of pan.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese, and sugar.
Add eggs alternately with flour.
Add vanilla.
Place in large greased and floured tube pan in cold oven.
Turn oven to 300° and bake 1 1/2 hours, sometimes 10 minutes longer.
Cake must be started in cold oven. Let cake stand for 5 minutes before inverting pan.
Do not open oven door at any time until cake is done.

title: bul-go-ki
directions: Marinate the meat in the ingredients for 1 hour, stirring the meat at least twice during marination.

title: sweet roll dough
directions: Combine ingredients (follow basic directions for white bread). Divide for desired rolls.
Shape and let rise.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken, onion and celery until tender.
Debone and cut chicken into small pieces.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine mushroom soup and sour cream.
Combine all other ingredients.
Pour soup and sour cream over potato mixture and mix well, but gently.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese when in casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Can be frozen.

title: cauliflower greek style
directions: Remove outer leaves and stalks from cauliflower.
Trim off any blemishes on head.
Separate head into flowerets.
Wash cauliflower well; drain.
Heat oil in large skillet over low heat. Add onions, carrots and garlic; cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add wine, water, lemon juice, tomato paste, bay leaves, coriander seed, salt and pepper; bring to boiling.
Add cauliflower; simmer for 15 minutes, or until cauliflower is just tender.
Transfer cauliflower to serving dish with slotted spoon. Heat liquid until the volume is reduced to about 1 1/2 cups; remove bay leaves.
Pour over cauliflower in serving dish.
Chill several hours.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: shrimp and okra gumbo
directions: In oil, cook okra, tomato and onions until okra is no longer ropy, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Add water, salt, black pepper and cayenne pepper and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and continue to cook another 10 minutes; serve in soup bowls over cooked rice. Yields 6 servings.
Tastes better if refrigerated and eaten on 2nd day.

title: pepper beef
directions: In a large skillet heat oil.
Add beef.
Cook until browned. Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Stir-fry 5 minutes.
Add hot water, beef flavor and soy sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: hurry up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip, together in a bowl. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: congealed chicken salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and water over hot water or in microwave. Add all ingredients.
Congeal.

title: basic cream cheese
directions: Combine creams and sugar and scald.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve rennet in 1 tablespoon water and stir into cream mixture. Add the buttermilk.
Pour into a large, glass bowl; set in cool (not the fridge) place for 4 to 5 hours until set.
Line colander with cheesecloth or muslin.
Spoon in the cream mixture, tie the ends together and hang over the sink or bowl to drain at least 2 days.
Turn out into a bowl, place in containers and refrigerate.

title: diet buttermilk salad
directions: Mix fruit, dry pudding and buttermilk.
Fold in Cool Whip last.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pearl tapioca pudding
directions: Drain water off of tapioca and put in milk.
Add salt and cook until balls are soft.
Put sugar in beaten eggs and add to milk. Cook until mixture thickens.
Add vanilla.
When cool, add a small amount of Cool Whip.

title: drumsticks
directions: Heat the oven to 425°.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper in bowl.
Dip chicken legs into cooled margarine; roll in flour mixture to coat.
Arrange in an ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Bake uncovered until done, 50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach pasta salad
directions: Rinse and dry spinach.
Cook pasta according to package directions; do not overcook!
Rinse and set aside.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onions, celery and mushrooms in butter.
Add cheese and soup.
Separate, cook and drain broccoli and add to mixture. Serve with crackers or potato chips.

title: chocolate sundae cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Put large marshmallows (sliced in fourths) on each cookie.
Put back in oven until marshmallow melts.
Frost with the frosting recipe.

title: more casserole
directions: Brown meat. Add salt, pepper, soup, sauce and pepper sauce, if desired.
Stir in macaroni, green pepper, onion and corn.
Put in casserole. Arrange cheese slices on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 2 baking sheets with nonstick cooking spray.
Coat eggplant slices with egg white, then bread crumbs.
Arrange on prepared baking sheets; bake 30 minutes.
Turn slices over; bake until browned on both sides, 10 minutes or longer.
Remove from oven; leave oven on.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bone; dice meat. Place in lightly greased dish.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, pepper and milk; beat until smooth.
Pour over chicken and Veg-All.
Combine chicken soup and chicken broth in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken mixture.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, combine onion and butter.
Cook at High for 2 minutes until tender, stirring once.
Stir in tomatoes, chili peppers and salt.
Cover and cook at High for 5 minutes.
Add cheese, a little at a time, stirring until melted. Stir in a little milk, if mixture becomes too thick.
Cook on High for 45 minutes.
Stir.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Combine crackers with milk, egg and soup.
Mix well.
Add scallops and melted butter.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 hour.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven and sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Arrange peach slices in rows over sugar.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a large bowl.
Add shortening, milk, vanilla and eggs. Beat at low speed, just until mixed.
Beat at high speed for 4 minutes or until very smooth and fluffy.
Spoon batter over peaches, covering completely.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until center springs back when lightly pressed with fingertip. Cover pan with plate, invert, shake gently and then lift pan. Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: no frost cupcakes
directions: Melt butter and chocolate; stir until blended.
Cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
Fill muffin tins with approximately 1/4 cup of batter.
(Foil cupcake liners are great.)
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Clean and block carrots; cut peppers and onions and cook with carrots in salt water 10 minutes (until tender).
Bring to boil vinegar, oil and sugar; add tomato soup, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce and pour over drained carrots and corn.
Cook slowly just long enough to stir about 3 or 4 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps indefinitely.
Very good.

title: skillet squash
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserve 1 tablespoon drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute squash and onion in reserved drippings 6 minutes or until tender.
Stir in sour cream and seasonings.
Spoon into serving dish; sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Yields 8 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream
sugar
and shortening together.	Add applesauce, flour, spices and soda.
Add raisins and vanilla.
Grease and flour an 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: Place the berries, sugar and water in a 4-quart saucepan; bring to a boil. Dip off 1/2 cup juice. Add enough water to make 3/4 cup.
Mix flour and juice to make a soft dough.
Drop by teaspoon into boiling berries.
Cook until dough is done in the center. Serve with cream or Cool Whip.

title: sweet meatballs
directions: Mix meat with eggs, bread crumbs and garlic.
Form in balls. Simmer ketchup and 2/3 jar grape jelly. Drop meatballs in and simmer, covered, 30 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together and roll out on flour board.
Makes two 9-inch pie crusts.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, sugar and margarine.
Press into rectangular Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: raspberry-chocolate bars
directions: Mix raspberries, orange juice and cornstarch in 1-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Cool 10 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over crust. Spoon raspberry mixture over chocolate chips; spread carefully.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon, separate and drain grease.
Add all other ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir and cook 4 to 5 hours on low or bake uncovered in 350 degrees for 2 hours.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix the sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Alternate with flour and melted margarine.
It will be soft dough.
Chill about 1 hour or until firm.
On wax paper, sprinkle flour.
Use about 1/3 of the batter.
Sprinkle with flour; knead, roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes for soft cookies, 15 minutes for brittle cookies.
They burn easily (be careful!).

title: meatball vegetable soup
directions: Mix beef, egg, bread, 1/4 cup onion and salt.
Shape into 36 meatballs.
In large saucepan, brown meatballs and cook remaining onion in the shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add other ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 cups.

title: breakfast hash
directions: Using a large skillet, brown the potatoes in melted butter. Season with salt and pepper, then stir in sausage and green pepper.
Beat the eggs until light.
Pour over mixture and cook, stirring frequently, until eggs are thickened but still moist. Makes 4 servings.

title: mississippi corn bread
directions: Mix together.
Bake in an iron skillet at 425° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken, onion and celery.
Keep broth.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, onion, celery and pimento.
Cut 12 slices of Velveeta cheese into small pieces.
Tear chicken into small pieces and add with other ingredients.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth (keep broth).
Add noodles and stir until completely mixed.
Add broth as needed to make stirring easier.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix together and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Top with an 8 ounce tub of Cool Whip.
Drain can of Mandarin oranges and place on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until served.
May also be frozen, but thaw before serving.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring milk to a boil. Add sugar; boil until a small amount of liquid dropped in cold water makes a soft ball. Add oats (if not thick, a few more oats may be added). Drop on waxed paper to cool.

title: reeces candy
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine and powdered sugar.
Use your hands or spoon to mix ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Chill small rolled up balls for 3 hours or overnight.
Melt semi-sweet chips in double boiler.
If chocolate chips become to thick add cap full of oil.
Stir.
Insert toothpick in top of candy mixture and dip in chocolate.
Tap candy against spoon to get excess off candy. Then place on wax paper.
Refrigerate.

title: great-gramma's chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients into a large bowl.
With a wire whisk, beat in last 3 ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 10 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Done when a toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Chop and cook celery and onion together.
Pour enough turkey for chicken stock over ingredients to soften to a stiff batter. Bake in greased pan at 400° until brown.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine and sugar in food processor. shape into 1-inch balls. Let stand a minute until dry.
Dip into melted coating.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer until smooth. This is a great dip for Pringles.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Cover zucchini, onion, green pepper, red pepper and celery with cold water.
Add pickling salt.
Let stand overnight.
Next day drain and rinse in cold water.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook 30 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: aunt polly's pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Sift flour with salt, soda, powder and spices.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pasta supper
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate. Serve on bed of chopped lettuce.

title: quick hamburger goulash
directions: Place the hamburger in a large skillet with a tight-fitting cover; brown the meat until it loses its reddish color.
Add the onion and cook until they are transparent.
Stir in the remainder of the ingredients and let simmer for about 40 minutes.
Keep tightly covered all the while it is cooking.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Add the egg and beat well.
Add the molasses and vinegar.
Mix in the flour, which has been combined with the salt and the spices.
Dissolve the baking soda in the boiling water and add.
You should have a soft dough.
If necessary, add a bit more flour.
Drop by spoonful onto a greased cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fresh vegetable tray
directions: Wipe mushrooms clean, cut small wedges out of the heads and remove stems.
Add 1 tablespoon vinegar and 1/2 teaspoon salt to 2 cups water.
Simmer mushrooms for 3 minutes.
Remove and let cool. When cooled, add 1 bottle Italian dressing.
Marinate mushrooms overnight.
Remove from dressing before serving.
Rinse broccoli and cauliflower and cut into flowerets.
Keep iced.

title: boiled pot roast
directions: Cut roast into 4 or 5 pieces.
Place in Dutch oven or large soup pot.
Cover with cold water and add soy sauce, onion, pepper and garlic powder.
Cover and cook on medium-low heat.
After 3 hours, peel carrots.
Cut into 2 to 3 pieces.
Add to pot; stir and re-cover.
After another 30 minutes, peel and quarter potatoes. Add to pot and re-cover.
After 1 1/4 hours, add optional frozen vegetables.
Cook 15 minutes more.
Scoop onto platter and serve with fresh bread or rolls.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine warm sweet potatoes with 1/4 cup margarine, milk, 2 eggs, 1 cup sugar and vanilla in mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth. Spoon into shallow baking dish.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and flour with 1/2 cup melted margarine in mixer bowl and mix well.
Add pineapple and 1 egg; mix well.
Spread over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix well; if too thick, add more milk.
Also, if tastes too tart of mustard, add 1 tablespoon sugar.

title: beef and rice stuff
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in rice, soup, water, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on medium-low for 25 minutes.
As plates are served, top with cheese.

title: cookies while you sleep
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites and salt until they hold peaks.
Add sugar and beat until very stiff.
Fold in chocolate and pecans.
Cover large cookie sheet with aluminum foil and spray foil with an aerosol cooking spray.
Drop 1 teaspoon of mixture per cookie onto the foil approximately 1/2-inch apart.
Turn oven off and put cookies into the oven on a middle spaced rack.
Do not open oven for 6 hours.
After 6 hours or overnight, cookies will be done and can be stacked into cookie tins.
Yields approximately 2 1/2 dozen.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla pudding mix, margarine, egg and 1/2 cup milk.
Place sliced peaches over batter. Cream together the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons milk and place on top of peaches.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: hawaiian stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix hot water and margarine in bowl.
Stir in stuffing mix, pepper, half the pineapple and syrup.
Spoon evenly on chicken.
Roll tightly; secure with toothpicks.
Place in a 9-inch square pan.
Mix remaining sugar, pineapple and syrup; spoon over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until thoroughly cooked.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Chop tomatoes and let stand overnight; drain off water. Add as much hot water as you drain off and 2 tablespoons salt; cook 20 minutes; drain and add other ingredients.
Put apples, tomatoes, and suet through
grinder.
Put
in jars boiling hot and it will keep for years.

title: bob's baked alaska
directions: Cut pound cake into 4 rounds, using 3-inch diameter cookie cutter or a glass.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except poppy seed; beat for 10 minutes. Add poppy seed.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Delicious plain or topped with glaze.

title: aunt ethel's tuna chow mein casserole
directions: Mix tuna, peas and chopped onion.
Blend soup, flour and mayonnaise to make a sauce.
Cook over low heat; use flour as needed.
Pour over tuna mixture and mix well.
Place half of the noodles in baking dish.
Add mixture of tuna.
Place remaining noodles over top.
Bake 25 minutes at 300°.

title: baked chicken with mustard
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, mustard, melted butter and Pepperidge Farm dressing; roll chicken in mixture. Place in a buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered, then 1/2 hour more uncovered.

title: no crust quiche
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into greased casserole. Sprinkle bacon, broccoli and cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well. Add cookies alternately with milk.
Fold in vanilla, pecans and coconut.
Bake in greased tube pan 40 minutes to an hour at 350°. Cool and remove from pan.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Pour green beans and onions into pan and bring to a boil. Drain and arrange in baking dish (save juice). Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper.
Mix 1/2 cup bean liquid and soup. Add all of the cheese except 1/4 of it.
Pour mixture over beans. Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar.
Cover with crumbled crackers and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grilled brats in beer
directions: In skillet, put brats, onion and beer; simmer, uncovered, for about 30 minutes.
Mix butter and onion salt together; spread on buns.
Remove brats from beer; fill slit with cheese and place in buns.
Broil 4 inches from heat, until cheese melts.
Watch closely.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook for 1 hour on high and 1 hour on low; or 3 to 4 hours on low.
Serves 12.

title: peg's company cole slaw
directions: Soak the shredded cabbage in icy salt water no less than one half hour.
Add all of the ingredients.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate.
This keeps well.
After a few days, you may want to drain off some of the excessive moisture.
Stir.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: yummie cheese squares
directions: Save egg white for topping.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk and set aside.
Spray glass or metal pan with Pam.
On bottom layer use 1 package crescent rolls.
Put filling over rolls then put second package crescent roll on top.
Bread with egg white.
Bake 25 minutes or until light brown at 350°.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Bring to boil, then simmer 15 minutes.
Can and seal tightly.

title: old fashioned cornbread
directions: Old Fashioned Cornbread has a flavor and texture all it's own.
Easy to make.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Cook beef and onion over medium heat (5-6 minutes), stirring often until beef is browned.
Drain.
Quarter and core the cabbage, cut cross-wise into inch wide strips, add to meat mixture, cover and cook over medium heat 5-7 minutes, stirring occasionally until cabbage wilts.
Stir in tomatoes, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer, stirring occasionally 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender. Serve over rice.

title: weight watchers carrots a la francaise
directions: In a small bowl, combine carrots and garlic.
In a small jar with tight fitting cover or small bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Cover and shake well or stir to mix thoroughly.
Pour lemon mixture over carrot-garlic mixture and toss to coat.
Makes 2 servings.
Each serving provides 1 vegetable exchange, 1/2 fat exchange.
Per serving contains 51 calories, 1 g protein, 3 g fat, 7 g carbohydrate, 20 mg calcium, 234 mg sodium and 0 mg cholesterol.

title: swedish pickled cucumbers
directions: Place cucumbers and onion in a dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers and onion.
Marinate in the refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well and pour into shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecued baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a heavy skillet, saute the onion and garlic in small amount of water or Pam, cooking until the onion is transparent, but not browned.
Transfer the onion and garlic into a mixing bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients and combine well. Pour the mixture into a 2-quart baking dish and bake, uncovered, for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serves 4.

title: sheila's banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together sugar and shortening in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and mix until smooth.
Combine dry ingredients.
Alternate dry ingredient mixture with bananas into sugar-shortening-egg mix.
Stir this mixture only enough to make finished batter moist.
Add nuts.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Mix chicken, onion and cream cheese together.
Put 1 tablespoon of mixture in each crescent roll at wide end and roll up.
Place in baking dish.
Mix soup and broth and pour over chicken roll-ups.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until brown on top.
Cover with foil for first hour.
Last 30 minutes, uncover so they will brown.

title: chicken and dressing bake
directions: Cook almonds and 1 tablespoon margarine in small glass dish for 2 to 3 minutes, or until toasted, on Full power, stirring once.
Stir in bread crumbs and 1 teaspoon parsley.
Set aside.

title: cracker spread
directions: Dice beef and onions.
Blend in cream cheese and taco blend cheese, reserving enough taco cheese to sprinkle on top.
Serve with a variety of crackers.

title: rapid mix rolls
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast in saucepan until warm.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat on high 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Thaw shrimp if frozen.
Chop shrimp.
Heat tomato soup and cream cheese in the top of double boiler until cream cheese melts. Cool slightly.
Stir in gelatin; mix well.
Add shrimp, mayonnaise, celery, green onion, green pepper, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour into a well-greased 1 1/2-quart mold.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Unmold onto platter.
Serve with wafers.
Makes approximately 5 1/2 cups.

title: mulligatawny soup
directions: In a heavy kettle, saute in oleo, carrot, onion, celery, green pepper, apple and chicken.
Stir occasionally until onions are tender.
Stir in gradually, flour, curry powder, stock, mace, whole cloves, tomatoes, parsley and salt and pepper to taste. Simmer, covered, for 1/2 hour.
Vary amounts of vegetables and chicken to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: george's simple barbecue sauce
directions: Squeeze juice from lemon into a bowl.
Add brown sugar, a little at a time, and stir until consistency of syrup.
Add bottle of catsup.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce over catsup until it forms a thin layer.
Mix well.

title: special pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the last two.
Toss with sour cream and sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 6.

title: seven day slaw
directions: Slice cabbage in a dish.
Cut onion on top.
Bring to a boil sugar, vinegar, celery seed, salt, mustard and oil.
Pour over cabbage.
Will keep up to 7 days.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Let simmer until onion is tender. Drain and add other ingredients except beans.
Pour beans into 2-quart casserole.
Pour ground beef mixture over beans.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and cherry juice.
Mix drained pineapple with marshmallows.
Mix all together.
Whip the whipping cream and fold into fruit.
Put in refrigerator to cool for several hours.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add flour, sugar, nutmeg and salt. Stir in rice, milk and vanilla.
Cook slowly in heavy pot until thickened.
May serve warm or cold.
May add raisins for variation.

title: saucy chops cincinnati
directions: Brown both
sides
of chops slowly in hot oil.	Combine applesauce, soy
sauce,
onion and cinnamon.
Arrange chops in single layer in shallow baking dish.
Spoon applesauce mixture evenly over
chops.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove
foil.
Turn chops over and baste.
Return to oven. Bake uncovered for 15 minutes longer or until chops are tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: 2 crust pie shell
directions: Wipe milk over top crust and sprinkle with sugar.

title: spicy sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and spices in heavy saucepan.
Mix in sweet potatoes, corn syrup and 3 tablespoons oleo.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Boil, stirring constantly until slightly thickened, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in beaten eggs.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Toss pecan halves with 1 tablespoon melted oleo until evenly coated.
Arrange on top of sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° until set and knife inserted in center of mixture comes out clean, about 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: shape snack
directions: Cut cheese slices into triangles.
Eat on round, square or rectangular crackers.
Practice saying the names of the shapes as you eat them.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt the caramels and 1/3 cup milk; set aside.
Combine the cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup milk and nuts.
Pat 1/3 of batter into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Spread the chips over the baked base.
Pour caramel mixture over chips.
Pat remaining batter over caramel layer.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool slightly and put in refrigerator to set caramels.
When set, remove.

title: tomato-beef casserole
directions: In saucepan, brown beef and cook onion until tender; stir to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Stir in 3/4 cup cheese and remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Stir and top with remaining cheese.

title: corn ala southern
directions: Chop pepper; mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into buttered pudding dish and bake slowly until firm.
Fresh corn, cut from the cob, may be used in the same manner.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Saute ground beef until browned, stirring to crumble. Drain off grease. Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar. Heat. Place each biscuit in a greased muffin cup, pressing to cover bottoms and sides. Spoon meat mixture into cups and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown. Yields 12 servings.

title: one dish dinner
directions: Put rice in the bottom of roaster.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Mix soups and water together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes and cook in boiling salted water to cover 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cook completely.
Peel and cube potatoes.
Combine potatoes, eggs and celery in a large bowl; toss gently.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, salad dressing, lemon juice, salt and pepper in a small bowl; stir well.
Pour over potato mixture, tossing gently.
Cover and chill thoroughly. Just before serving, add relish and pimento; toss gently.
Serve on lettuce leaves if desired.

title: cheese bread
directions: Roll out 1 can of rolls onto lightly floured wax paper.
Leave the other can in refrigerator.
Place dough onto cookie sheet. Combine all other ingredients, except egg white.
Put white in a small cup and whip slightly with fork until just a little runny. Spoon filling on top of first can of rolls.
Next roll out other can.
Place on top of filling mixture. Be sure to cover entire filling with dough that is very nicely rolled out. Spoon whites on top of remaining dough. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Tastes wonderful warm.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Adjust quantities according to taste, size of family and size of cooking pot.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture with sour milk.

title: beaver (or any small game) hash
directions: Grind or finely chop up the meat.
Saute onions and celery in oil.
Add the meat and cook until all is browned.
Mix in canned tomatoes and rice.
Simmer over low heat for 5 minutes or until rice is done.
Season with Worcestershire sauce, garlic, salt and pepper.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients together and boil 1 minute.
Cool thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and leave overnight.
Just before serving, you can add bananas and if you need more juice, add some of the pineapple juice.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix milk and sugar in saucepan.
Heat slowly.
Mix cornstarch with water.
Add slowly to first mixture.
Add beaten eggs.
Stir constantly until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Set aside to cool to room temperature or refrigerate overnight.
Fold in 3 heaping tablespoons Cool Whip.
Save rest of Cool Whip for topping.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Put coconut and pecans in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix cake mix as directed and pour over 1st mixture.
Mix cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla and drop by tablespoon onto top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oil pastry
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Pour salad oil and cold water or milk into measuring cup (but do not stir).
Add, all at once, to the flour mixture.
Stir slightly with a fork.
Form in ball; flatten slightly.
Roll between two 12-inch squares of waxed paper.
(First, dampen table slightly so waxed paper won't slip.) When dough is rolled to the edges of paper, it will be the right thickness for the crust.
Peel off top sheet of paper and fit dough, paper side up, into pie plate.
Remove paper.
Finish pie shell, following directions for single or double crust pies. Makes enough for one 8 or 9-inch double crust pie.

title: chewy chocolate cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts if desired.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 9 minutes.
Don't overbake, cookies will be soft, they will puff during baking, flatten during cooling.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Mix and then form into small log the size of your index finger. Pinch off a tablespoon or less and put on cookie sheet.
Flatten a little, then bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes until the sides are light brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when out of the oven and cooling.

title: halibut heaven
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan and heat.
Pour over fish in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican butterball cookies
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt and coffee together.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed ingredients; blend in nuts if desired.
Shape into balls, walnut size.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Dust with powdered sugar while warm.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Blend in blender.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato black walnut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: quick ham quiche
directions: Sprinkle the first 6 ingredients in a casserole dish.
Mix the Bisquick, milk, eggs, salt and pepper and pour the batter over the ingredients in the casserole dish.
Bake at 375° or 400° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: potato puffie omelet(makes 1 serving)
directions: Mix eggs, potato and yogurt very gently.
Allow to stand for 1 to 2 minutes.
Coat nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray. Pour in egg mix and top with veggies.
Cook over low heat until nearly set and lightly browned on the bottom.
Turn and cook another minute or two.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Sprinkle over cake and swirl with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter and Crisco. Sift together the sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture along with 1 cup of milk.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Add vanilla flavoring.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: low-fat cheesecake
directions: Combine ingredients and press onto the bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan.

title: baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and wine or milk. Spoon over chicken; sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: stuffed cornish hens with apricot brandy sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash hens inside and out.
Pat dry. Cook rice according to box directions. Stuff hens with cooked rice.
Tie legs together.
Rub Vegit liberally onto hens.
Place hens in a foil lined pan (easier clean up) and bake for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes or until hen juices run clear. Baste occasionally.

title: icing
directions: Prepare icing before cake has finished baking. Melt oleo; add cocoa and milk. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Beat well. Spread on cake while still warm.

title: chocolate icebox dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and melted butter; press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Add the cream cheese which has been softened and blend well.
Pour this over the crumb mixture and bake for 20 minutes at 350°. After taking this from the oven, prepare pudding and pour over cheese topping; allow to cool.
Chill overnight.
Top with Cool Whip the next morning.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns. Combine cream of chicken soup and margarine. Heat. Add cheese, sour cream and onion.
Mix salt and pepper with potatoes.
Pour sauce over potatoes and mix well.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Mix together marshmallows, pineapple, coconut and oranges. Blend in sour cream.

title: waffle sundaes
directions: For each serving, top 1 waffle with 1 scoop of ice cream. Arrange banana slices around ice cream.
Spoon preserves over ice cream.
Garnish with whipped topping.
Quick and fun for kids.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar and beer just until blended.
Spoon into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Pour margarine over top.
Bake at 350° until evenly browned, about 40 minutes.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together and spread in 2-quart oven-safe casserole. Bake 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serves 8 or more.

title: west virginia pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except buttermilk and beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Add milk and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Bake at 325° for 70 minutes in greased and floured tube pan.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Put into 2-inch foil baking cups; one wafer on the bottom, then 1 tablespoon of the cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top with the pie filling of your choice.

title: mom mom mickey's mayonnaise cake(out of this world!)
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Dissolve baking soda in water and add to first mixture.
Add flour and Miracle Whip.
Mix with electric mixer until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
May use two round pans for layer cake.

title: barbecue sop
directions: Heat all ingredients together until blended. Baste on turkey, chicken or beef.
Yummy!

title: carrot ring
directions: Combine all, put in buttered 1 1/2-quart mold.
Set mold in water, cook for 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve with mushroom sauce.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Season chicken.
Cover with water and cook with onion and celery for about 1 hour.
Let cool.
Cut up chicken and add mushrooms and olives with juices.
Let stand while spaghetti is cooking in the chicken broth.
Add chicken and tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cheddar cheese may be added to casserole also if desired.

title: dave's hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Mix remaining ingredients in casserole dish; add browned beef and onion.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great for cookouts.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Brown cubed
steak in oleo.
Stir in onion soup mix and undrained
mushrooms.
Add
sufficient
water to barely cover. Simmer about
minutes
or until meat is done.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Cream shortening, vanilla and sugars.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter and then sifted dry ingredients.
Form into tiny balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press with back of fork dipped in water.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend eggs, milk and salad oil together.
Add dry ingredients, all at once, and mix, just until moistened.
Stir in apple sticks.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in air-tight container.

title: minute egg dressing
directions: Cut bread into tiny cubes.
Place butter in iron frying pan over lowest heat.
Add bread; cook until crisp, stirring occasionally to prevent burning.
Put egg into bowl; mince garlic and add.
Beat well with rotary beater.
Add oil, a little at a time; continue beating until mixture begins to thicken.
(In order to get the mixture to thicken, it may be necessary to use a little less or a little more than 1/2 cup oil.)
Add cheese, red pepper and salt; beat well.
Add vinegar; beat well.
Just before serving, add bread cubes.
Pour over lettuce; toss well.
Serves 4.

title: ultra chocolate buttercream pie
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar (sifted).
Add eggs, vanilla and Frangelica; mix.
Melt chocolate with whipping cream.
Pour chocolate mix into butter mix.
Stir and pour into chocolate pie shell and chill.

title: fajita roll-ups
directions: Place 12-inch skillet over high
heat.
Add margarine and melt.
Add chicken breasts, smooth sides down.
Cook without turning for 3 minutes until browned.
Turn breasts over.
Add water, milk and soup mix.
Stir to blend.
Sprinkle noodles over top; stir to cover with liquid.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 7 to 9 minutes, stirring twice until breasts are no longer pink inside and noodles are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: scotch oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook raisins and water for 5 minutes; drain and measure 3 tablespoons of juice.
Combine with soda.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy; beat in eggs.
Stir in oats, salt and raisins that have been drained.
Add juice/soda mixture and stir into flour.
Drop on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Mix together and pour in pie crust.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.
Gets thick as it cools.

title: merry christmas cookies
