directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg, honey and flavoring thoroughly. Measure flour by dip method and blend flour, salt and soda.
Stir in and chill dough.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough 1/4 inch thick and cut into Christmas shapes.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool, ice and decorate.
Makes 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Wash and skin chicken breasts.
Mix ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sloppy muffins
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and carrots.
Drain well and put in medium size bowl.
Mix in the tomato paste, chili powder, salt and dry mustard; mix well.
Return to the stove to heat thoroughly.
Toast the English muffins and put on serving plates. Top with the ground beef mixture and top with the shredded Mozzarella cheese.
If desired, put under a broiler for a minute to melt the cheese.

title: baked apple a-la-mode(10% total fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Arrange apples in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Drizzle honey over apples.
Mix lemon juice with 1/2 cup water.
Pour over apples.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Cover and bake 1 hour or until liquid boils and apples soften.
Remove cover and bake an additional hour, until apples are golden and tender. Remove from oven and cool 15 minutes.
Serve with 1/4 cup ice milk or frozen yogurt.
Serves 4.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl; pour just enough milk to moisten so they will stick together. Mix and drop by spoonfuls into hot grease. Cook until brown.

title: corn relish
directions: In medium saucepan mix corn (undrained), vinegar, sugar, onion, salt, celery seed, mustard seed and hot pepper sauce. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and boil gently, uncovered, 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in pimiento, red pepper or green pepper.
Transfer to a covered container and store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 cups.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper the pork chops.
Press graham cracker crumbs firmly on both sides.
Place in a well-greased, shallow pan in a single layer.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour.
Turn after baking 30 minutes.

title: super meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except the catsup and mix well.
Shape into loaf and place in 10-inch skillet, covered.
Spread a thin layer of catsup on top of loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: cauliflower and olive salad
directions: Put first 7 ingredients in salad bowl.
Toss well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Just before serving, add greens and toss. Serves 6.

title: french bread roast
directions: Place roast in crock pot.
Cover with water.
Add seasonings then cover.
Cook high 3 to 4 hours, low 7 to 8 hours.
Serve on hard rolls, use juice for dipping.

title: no flour peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Scoop level tablespoonful batter; roll into ball.
Press down with fork.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 350° for about 18 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute cut up onion in skillet.
Add ground beef and fry until brown.
Remove excess grease.
Add the can of soup and mix.
Place in a 3 quart casserole dish.
Then drain water from can of corn. Put corn on top of beef mixture in casserole.
Add cream cheese, butter salt, pepper and milk to boiled potatoes.
Put the potatoes on top of the corn in casserole dish.
Put casserole in oven for 20 to 30 minutes until potatoes start to brown (350° oven).
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli-onion bake
directions: Cook chopped broccoli until almost tender.
Drain.
Gently mix mayonnaise, cheese and onions with broccoli.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until heated through and bread crumbs are lightly browned, about 20 minutes.

title: honey apple pie
directions: Use your own favorite crust.
Combine first 5 ingredients until you have paste-like mixture.
Fold into sliced apples in large bowl.
Mix well.
Place mixture in bottom of unbaked pie crust.
Dot with butter.
Place second crust on top and flute edges.
Cut 4 or 5 slits in top of crust.
Take a little milk and brush over top crust.
Bake for approximately 1 hour.
Apples may be any kind in season.

title: black walnut drops
directions: Grease a cookie sheet and set it aside. In a small bowl beat egg whites until a soft peak forms. Gradually add sugar, beat until a stiff peak forms. Toss nuts with flour, then fold into egg mix. Drop by tsp. 1 1/2 inches apart on the greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, orange juice, vinegar and oil.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Add nuts, bananas and cranberries.
Pour into 5 (6-inch) loaf pans and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
This freezes well to use for Christmas gifts.

title: broccoli-cheese cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown. Let cool.
Serve warm.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Remove all unpopped kernels from the bowl of popped corn.
In a saucepan, mix together sugar, syrup and cream of tartar.
Bring it to a boil and cook without stirring to a hard cook test or 242° on a candy thermometer.
Add butter, soda, flavoring and coloring if desired.
Pour quickly over the popped corn.
Stir with a wooden spoon and then mold into large firm balls in the palms of your hands.
Place on waxed paper to dry.
You may make a face on the popcorn ball by using bits of cherry or raisins for eyes and mouths.
They will look more attractive if covered with clear cellophane.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Gradually add flour and blend good. Scoop on ungreased cookie sheet with potato masher lightly dipped in flour.
Press cookie down.
Bake at 375° until they are lightly browned.
Cool on rack (don't remove from cookie tray for about 10 minutes), then place on toweling to cool.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt, then combine all dry ingredients and add strawberry mixture.
Stir together and mix thoroughly.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
A very delicious moist sweet bread.

title: onion casserole
directions: Make 2 layers each in this order in greased casserole:
onions, cheese and potato chips.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over all. Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake at 350° until onions are done.

title: pinwheels
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients for filling. Spread thin layer of filling on each tortilla. Roll up and wrap in plastic wrap. Chill overnight. Slice each roll and serve with salsa for dipping.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain.
Add ingredients except crackers. Crumble crackers on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil beets until tender.
Slip skins off in cold water.
Keep beets hot in warm oven.
Heat liquid to boiling.
Pack beets in hot jars, pour liquid over and seal.

title: caramel cake
directions: Mix pudding according to directions. Mix cake mix with egg and pudding mix. Pour into 13 x 9 cake pan. Pour butterscotch morsels over cake mixture. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: english cheese straws
directions: Grease 2 large baking sheets.
Set aside.
Sift flour into large bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
With your fingers, rub butter into flour until mix is crumbly.
Mix in cheese and egg yolk.
Add enough cold water, a little at a time, to make a stiff dough.
Break off 1/3 of dough and set aside.

title: busy day beef casserole
directions: Brown beef in deep skillet.
Add onion and cook until tender. Drain off excess fat.
Add tomatoes, water, noodles and seasonings.
Stir to moisten noodles.
Cover, bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in corn and mushrooms.
Heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with cheese.
If desired, place under broiler to melt cheese.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: jumble brownies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add in all other ingredients except nuts and coconut.
Beat well.
Blend in nuts and coconut.
Pour in well greased 13 x 9-inch pan (or double recipe and use a cookie sheet and 8-inch round pan).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cut while warm.

title: peanut pork
directions: Slice pork lengthways into about three fillets, then slice into bite-sized pieces.
Place unsalted peanuts in food processor with knife blade; process until they are the consistency of flour.
Be careful not to make peanut butter.
Mix peanut flour with all-purpose flour (half and half).
Add salt and pepper to taste, set aside.
Beat one egg and add as much water.
Dip meat in egg wash, then into peanut flour.
Drop into hot grease and fry until golden brown and crispy.

title: deep dish tuna pie
directions: Prepare pie crust mix according to package directions, except do not roll out.
Cover dough and set aside.

title: zippy zucchini
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well. Spread evenly in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle top with extra Parmesan cheese after it is removed from the oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: Prepare unbaked pie shell for 10 1/2 inch pie plate. Beat eggs and sugar together until well blended. Add butter, corn syrup, salt, vanilla, and chopped pecans. Mix thoroughly. Pour into prepared unbaked shell. Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours-until filling is set. Cover with foil if top gets too brown before filling is set. Serve warm or cold. Garnish with whipped cream and pecan halves.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread crumbs (cubes) in bottom of a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish; set aside.
Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble; drain well.
Combine sausage, eggs, milk, cheese and salt in a large bowl.
Stir well.
Pour over bread cubes.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown and set.
Remove from oven and garnish.
Cut into squares to serve.
Yields 12 servings.

title: crab cakes
directions: Flake crabmeat if necessary.
Cook chopped onion in 1/4 cup butter until limp.
Add bread crumbs and mix well.
Beat eggs thoroughly and add to crabmeat along with crumb mixture, salt, mustard, chopped parsley and cream.
Shape into 8 flat patties; coat with flour and saute in remaining butter until delicately browned on both sides.
Yields 4 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and wash in colander.
Place beans and chopped onion in pot with water to cover.
Cook 1 hour; remove from heat and drain.
Melt garlic cheese, oleo and cream of mushroom soup in boiler.

title: chocolate cool whip treat
directions: Mix 2 cups crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted margarine.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up cauliflower, broccoli and red onion.
Mix mayonnaise or Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar until blended.
Add to vegetables and chill overnight.
Add bacon before serving.

title: quick cajun chicken & rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Sprinkle chicken with thyme, salt and pepper to taste.
In a large skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer covered for 20 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: easy potato-onion dish
directions: Wash and peel potatoes and onions.
Melt butter in casserole dish.
Slice potatoes and onions into butter and mix well.
Season with pepper and salt; cook until potatoes are tender.

title: wonder bars
directions: Place graham cracker crumbs in a 9 x 9 inch or 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Melt butter and pour over top of graham cracker crumbs.
Spread walnuts over crumbs.
Top walnuts with chocolate chips and then coconut.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over the coconut.
Bake at 325 degrees for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: creamy thai dip(great for dipping artichokes!)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Makes 3/4 of a cup.

title: honey hearts
directions: Will also need a heart shaped cookie cutter.

title: virginia's pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Mix sugar, spice and salt to eggs.
Add pumpkin and milk and really beat well.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over mixture.
Spoon melted butter over mix and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick sherbet
directions: Freeze can until solid.
Place under hot water 1 minute.
Open can; put chunks in blender until sherbet consistency.
Return to freezer if necessary until time to serve.
Makes 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: baked seafood rice salad
directions: Cook rice; stir in all ingredients and place in 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: jello pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzel sticks to peanut consistency.
Add butter or margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Mix together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.

title: old time sugar cookies
directions: Mix the flour and margarine.
Mix the sugar, soda, milk, vanilla and eggs, then mix all together.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Cream butter and white sugar.
Add eggs, salt, pineapple and cubed bread.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole for 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: molded chocolate mousse
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, stir sugar, gelatin and salt until well mixed; gradually stir in
milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until gelatin is dissolved.
Add chocolate chips and stir constantly until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat.
In a medium bowl with fork, beat yolks slightly.
Gradually beat in hot mixture.
Refrigerate until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine drained juice from pineapple and oranges with pudding mix.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Cool.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Fold in bananas and marshmallows.
Garnish with cherries, as desired.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Cook beans. I use a pressure cooker; cover with enough water, 3-inches above beans, and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain excess water.
Blanch carrots and squash. Cut into cubes.
Chop tomatoes. Combine. Can use as salsa or as filling for burritos.
Combine with rice if desired.

title: tea cakes
directions: Put into large mixing bowl and beat on medium speed.
Cream sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add oil and vanilla and beat until well mixed.
Now, gradually add all dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Beat until well mixed.
Chill several hours in refrigerator, then take out and shape into 1-inch rolls.
Wrap in wax paper.
Now, cut in small pieces and put on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: rice custard
directions: Stir eggs, sugar, salt and spices together thoroughly.
Add milk, vanilla and rice; mix well.
Turn into a buttered baking dish and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a food processor fitted with a metal blade, process all ingredients except onion and salsa until pureed.
Pour mixture into a bowl; stir in onion and salsa.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Makes 1 cup.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind vegetables, using coarse blade. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt and let stand overnight. Rinse and drain. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetable mixture. Heat to boiling and simmer 3 minutes. Pack in jars and seal. Makes about 8 pints.

title: fruit salad
directions: Take 2 cups juice and cook pudding to boil.
Mix fruit in a large bowl.
Pour cooked pudding over fruit.
Stir well.
Chill before serving.

title: ranee csigay's english toffee
directions: *Freezing chocolate makes grating easier.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter in a double boiler.
Mix all ingredients together and put in flat pan.
Set in refrigerator and let chill, cut in squares and serve.
It's the chilling that does the job.
Looks dry before.
This is really good and easy to make.

title: microwave chops
directions: Trim fat off chops.
In oval or round dish, combine oil and garlic; spread evenly.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Combine broth, soy sauce, sugar and pepper in bowl.
Add chops to dish, turning over in garlic oil.
Pour sauce mixture over chops and cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes, turning chops and dish once after 2 minutes.
Keep covered.
Microwave on Medium power 12 to 15 minutes or until meat is tender and no pink remains.
Place chops in serving dish.
Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir into pan juices.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes until thickened.
Leave uncovered and stir once.
Pour sauce over chops.
Serves 4.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Mix margarine, sugar and eggs. In separate bowl blend dry ingredients.
Add to margarine mixture. Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7-9 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Almost all at once add 1 beaten egg, milk and oil.
Mix quickly but don't over mix. Put on hot griddle.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat on low heat until it crumbles.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook on low for about 2 hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown chuck, onion and bell pepper.
Drain chuck.
Mix in large bowl all ingredients except cheese.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Cover with foil; cook at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cowboy beans(top of stove baked beans)
directions: Brown sausage and onions; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients with sausage; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Adjust molasses or brown sugar to how sweet you like the beans.
These are very good!

title: caponata(salad)
directions: Cut eggplant into 3/4-inch cubes (about 5 cups).
Heat 1/2 cup water (salted if desired) to boiling.
Add eggplant.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes or until tender; drain.
Place eggplant and onion in medium glass or plastic bowl.
Mix vinegar, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic. Pour vinegar mixture over eggplant mixture; toss.
Stir tomato and parsley.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours.
Just before serving, stir in oil.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix the oleo, brown sugar and syrup and cook for about 5 minutes. Add the salt and soda. Stir well. Coat or stir slowly into popcorn, stirring as you pour mixture over the popcorn. Preheat oven to 200° and bake 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Place in plastic bags or containers to keep from drawing moisture.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; refrigerate until chilled.

title: almond and sesame milk formula
directions: Soak the almonds and seeds overnight in the refrigerator. Blend for 3 minutes at high speed and strain.

title: quester's cookies
directions: Mix and form balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: ham and cheese bake
directions: Trim off crusts and cut bread into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Place 1/2 bread cubes on bottom of lightly greased 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Cover with 1/2 cheese, then 1/2 ham.
Repeat the 3 layers. Combine eggs, milk and salt.
Beat well.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Drizzle melted butter over the top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Place in a pan (9 x 13-inch works) 3/4 full of water.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Uncover casserole last 15 minutes of baking time.
Test for doneness as for custard.
You can add broccoli and mushrooms if desired.
This is a great casserole for holiday when serving a large breakfast crowd.

title: friendship cake
directions: Day One:
Mix apple juice concentrate and 3 cans hot water in 2-quart plastic or glass container with a lid.
Add sugar, lemon juice, yeast and cherries; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cover and let stand at room temperature, stirring twice more that day.

title: pancakes at whitehouse's
directions: Mix batter in bowl.
Add milk last; add slowly to desired consistency.
Use 350° setting on grill.
If desired, add fruit topping after cooking.
Recipe makes 8 pancakes.

title: zeula's watergate salad
directions: Combine dry pudding mix with pineapple.
Stir in cool whip, marshmallows and nuts.
Place in serving bowl and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: amy's presbyterian chicken
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with chicken breasts.
Mix together celery soup and sour cream.
Spread evenly over chicken breasts.
Follow directions for Stove Top stuffing and spread evenly over soup and sour cream mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until it begins to bubble through dressing.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix milk and mayonnaise together.
Grease a large baking dish. Mix together jello and hot water, let dissolve, then add rest of ingredients in order.
Beat heck out of it with electric beater (use large bowl).
Put in pan and let set up in refrigerator.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and extracts together and set aside.
Mix flour, baking powder and milk into mixture.
Mix well.
Add poppy seed.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Loaves will crack at top.
Check with toothpick or inserted knife.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Add the ingredients (except pecans) and mix thoroughly.
Shape into 2 cheese balls. Roll with pecans and refrigerate.
Serve anytime after ball becomes hard with favorite crackers.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except pecans.
Shape into a ball and then roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: mary j.'s coca-cola salad
directions: Drain and press juice from fruit.
Reserve juice.
Using a sharp knife, quarter cherries.
Mix pineapple and cherry juice in a pan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Add cola and stir.
Add crushed pineapple and chopped cherries and nuts.

title: frosted meat loaf
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients in bowl in order listed; mix well.
Shape into loaf in loaf pan.
Mix catsup, brown sugar, nutmeg and mustard in small bowl; pour over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until cooked through.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place a layer of meat on the bottom of a glass baking dish. Mix the soups, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture over the meat.
Spread asparagus (or broccoli), mushrooms and onions over the mixture.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour remaining soup mixture over vegetables.
Sprinkle grated cheese and slivered almonds on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-30 minutes.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Place basil leaves, garlic, nuts and oil in a blender.
Blend until leaves are pulverized.
Add cheese.
Blend a little longer. Yields 1 1/2 cups pesto sauce.

title: millionaire cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix according to package directions.
Cool for 30 minutes.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix the dates, nuts, salt, sugar, flour and baking powder in a mixing bowl.
Then put the brown sugar into bread pan and pour the boiling water over it.
Pour the date mixture over the sugar and water.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pepperoni calzones
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain, squeezing out excess liquid.
Chop pepperoni.
Combine spinach, eggs, pepperoni, 1/4 cup of the pizza sauce, the 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, basil and garlic powder.
Unroll refrigerated dough.
Press into a 15 x 10-inch rectangle.
Cut into quarters.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese onto half of each quarter.
Spoon spinach mixture atop. Fold dough over mixture.
Seal edges.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Brush with oil.
Sprinkle with the 1 tablespoon Parmesan. Cut small slits on top of each.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Heat and pass remaining pizza sauce. Serves 4.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half; slip out yolks.
Mash with a fork.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Refill whites with yolk mixture.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Put all in large saucepan and cook for 5 or 6 hours or until beef falls into shreds.
The mixture should be of a consistency for serving on buns.
(Butt end of fresh pork can be used in this recipe.)
Serves 20.

title: pumpkin apple streusel muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Set aside.
In medium bowl combine egg, pumpkin and oil.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Stir in apples.
Spoon batter into greased or paper lined muffin pan.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil sugar and water; cool.
Add the first 4 ingredients. Freeze in ice cube trays.
Add chopped maraschino cherries, 1 to a cube.
Put 3 or 4 cubes in a glass.
Pour 7-Up or ginger ale over cubes.
Serve with straw.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Cut up butter and rub it in with your fingers.
Add the milk and eggs (beaten) until a nice smooth consistency.
Knead lightly on a floured surface and shape. Bake at 375° for one hour (depending on your oven).
Enjoy!

title: grandma's goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together; drain grease off.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat.
Cook macaroni; add to beef mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese when serving.

title: curried black-eyed peas
directions: In
medium nonstick skillet, melt margarine.
Add onion and ginger and cook, stirring frequently, until golden.
Stir in coriander,
curry
and cumin; cook 5 minutes.
Add peas and 1/2 cup water;
cook 2 to 3 minutes until liquid is reduced by half. Can
be
served
warm
or
cold.
Top
with teaspoon of low-fat yogurt.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain fruit well and mix together.
Add sour cream. Chill.
Do not whip.

title: chinese sponge cake(gai don go)
directions: Beat egg whites until slightly foamy, then add 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Beat again to stiff foam.
Sift together flour, baking powder and sugar, then add to egg yolks.
Then add water, oil and vanilla and beat until creamy.
Pour over egg whites gently; fold until well blended.
Bake at 350°, in 9 x 13-inch pan approximately 20 minutes and in tube pan 35 to 40 minutes.
Invert tube pan upside down to cool.

title: chinese barbecued spareribs
directions: In a bowl, combine soy sauce, honey, vinegar, ginger and garlic.
Marinate the ribs in the mixture for 2 hours basting and turning frequently.
Drain and reserve marinade.
Place ribs on rack in shallow roasting pan.

title: grandma jennings cauliflower soup
directions: Peel and cut vegetables.
Place in a pot.
Cover with just enough water to barely cover the vegetables.
Season with salt and pepper; add butter.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add canned milk and soup.
Simmer until hot.

title: hildegarde aiken's snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.

Add dry ingredients. Chill. Roll into balls the size of a small walnut. Roll balls into the mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Place about 2-inches apart on cookie sheet and bake at 400°.

title: alfredo pasta and crab
directions: While pasta cooks, heat butter and cream in small saucepan until butter melts.
Stir in cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir constantly until cheese melts.
Stir in crab meat.
Serve over pasta immediately.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt with 1/4 cup milk.
Heat 1 1/2 cups milk and stir in flour mixture.
Cook on low heat until mixture begins to thicken.
Add beaten egg yolks and cook 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Top with meringue or whipped cream.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese; place in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Cover with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart baking dish, layer all ingredients and drizzle bread with butter.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemonade.
Add lemon juice and Cool Whip.
Make crust by recipe on box.
Pour mixture into crust and chill.

title: fresh potato rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir until dissolved.
Combine the milk, shortening, potatoes, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour; mix well.
Cover; let rise for 1 hour.
Stir in enough flour to make stiff dough.
Knead on lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; refrigerate.
Shape into balls.
Grease in butter.
Let rise for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: potato chowder
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
In a large skillet, saute bacon with onion.
Add potatoes, celery, carrots, water, bouillon and seasonings. Cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Add warmed milk and continue cooking. Mix flour in butter and whisk into soup mixture. Cook until desired thickness. Makes 2 quarts.

title: spicy apple muffins
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Combine egg, milk, melted shortening and apples.
Add dry ingredients and mix, stirring only enough to blend.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: apple-spice muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin pan (or spray with Pam). Prepare Streusel.

title: creamy onion dip
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise or salad dressing, onion soup mix and parsley; cover.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cut butter into brown sugar and flour, save 1/2 cup of crumbs for top.
Mix all ingredients with sugar mixture and pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
May top with Cool Whip when serving.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Dip chicken in margarine.
Mix other ingredients and roll chicken in mixture. Place in dish.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, until tender.
Serves 6.

title: glazed grahams
directions: Place grahams on large greased cookie sheet. Bring all other ingredients to a boil and cook for 3 minutes. Pour over grahams and sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Do not overcook. Remove and cool slightly. Then transfer to wax paper. Break into smaller pieces (will resemble peanut brittle).

title: wild rice blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Paper line 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups. Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt in large bowl.
Whisk together applesauce, egg whites and milk in small bowl.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour mixture over blueberries in small bowl; toss to coat.
Fold applesauce mixture into flour mixture.
Fold blueberries and rice into flour mixture (batter will be stiff).
Spoon evenly into prepared muffin cups.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Serve warm or cool completely on wire rack.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend on cake speed until well mixed.
Pour into 1-pound coffee cans, greased with oil; fill 1/2 full.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Let cool and cover with plastic lids.

title: olden days cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and crumbled crackers and fold in.
Fold in rest of ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch well-greased pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Dissolve coffee crystals in water; set aside.
In bowl beat margarine and shortening on medium speed 30 seconds.
Add brown sugar, cinnamon and baking powder.
Beat until combined.
Beat in coffee mixture, egg and vanilla.
Beat in as much of the flour as you can with the mixer.
Stir in any remaining flour.
Divide dough in half.
Cover; chill 3 hours or until easy to handle.
Use cookie cutter or drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 16 to 18 cookies.

title: aunt frances' chocolate cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add cocoa and vanilla.
Alternately add flour, buttermilk and baking soda in water last.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes for layer cake or 40 to 45 minutes for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and seal in tightly covered container.
Mix 2 to 3 teaspoons of mix per cup of hot water to serve.

title: punch
directions: Melt Jell-Os in hot water.
Pour into a gallon container.
Add grapefruit juice and pineapple juice.
Add lemon juice.
Add water to make 1 gallon.
Freeze.

title: sticky buns
directions: Break 1 loaf of bread dough into 16 balls.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add vanilla pudding, cinnamon, milk and vanilla.
Sprinkle nuts and raisins over bread in cake pan.
Break 2nd loaf of bread into 16 balls. Place over 1st loaf.
Cover with a towel and let rise until pan is filled.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.
Turn out onto plate immediately.
Soak baking pan right away.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat eggs at high speed until foamy (about 3 minutes).
Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Beat in softened butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until center is set and top is golden brown.
Cool. Serve warm or cold.
Whipped cream is great as a topper!

title: crab crostini
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the crabmeat, bell pepper, mayonnaise, parsley, chives, lime juice, mustard, cheese and hot pepper sauce.
Blend well.
Spread about a tablespoon of the crab mixture on each slice of bread.
Place the bread on a broiler pan and broil for 5 to 6 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chantilly mandarin sauce
directions: Whip chilled cream, gradually adding the sugar until it is almost double in volume.
Add Mandarin Napoleon.
Fold in drained mandarin peel.
This is an elegant sauce for warm pie or chilled mousse.
Makes 4 cups.

title: mama's corn pudding
directions: Mix together. Pour into casserole dish and bake until browned and firm.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in cup of hot water.
Place in refrigerator to partially thicken.
Cream the cream cheese with 1 cup sugar; stir thoroughly into jello mixture.

title: real men's quiche
directions: Prepare pie crust for 9-inch pie pan.
Prick crust with fork and then bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Mix cream, milk, eggs, salt, pepper and cheese.
Place sauteed onion, crumbled bacon and spinach in pie crust.
Pour egg mixture over onion/bacon/spinach.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook vegetables.
Mix rest of ingredients together and add to hot vegetables.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Beat with mixer until smooth. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes. Insert toothpick in center to test for doneness.
When done, cool in pans 10 minutes, the add glaze.

title: johnie's 30 minute meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly hamburger, oats, egg, tomato juice, onion, salt and pepper.
Make into a large ball.
Put into a 2-quart baking dish.
Shape away from sides of dish.
Cover top with catsup.
Lay bacon on top.
Cover with microwave plastic wrap.
Bake on High in microwave for 20 minutes or until done.
Make sure you seal the plastic wrap down tight as this is the secret to good meat in microwave.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Melt chocolate and shortening together.
Add remaining ingredients to chocolate. Mix in dry ingredients.
Let mixture stand 10 minutes.
Drop from a teaspoon onto greased sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°. Frost with powdered sugar icing.
May add chopped nuts to batter if desired.

title: pepper steak
directions: Mix soy sauce, garlic and oil and let stand one hour.
Add the rest of ingredients and cook 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: easy zucchini sausage bake
directions: Remove sausage from casing (I don't remove); cook with onion in 10-inch skillet until sausage loses redness.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Saute zucchini in skillet drippings until transparent.
Cover; cook 5 minutes or until almost done and reserve.
Combine half of tomato sauce with rice and sausage mixture.
Add salt and mix well.
Put in 7 1/2 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange slices of zucchini over top.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan; spoon remaining tomato sauce over all. Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: julie's turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Put 1/2 of the batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and cool.
Melt together milk, caramels and butter.
Pour over cooled cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour remaining batter over cake and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve with ice cream.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles, uncovered, in boiling water 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Drain. Combine soup, milk, water and Cheddar cheese in a 3-quart saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until cheese melts and sauce is hot. Stir in cooked noodles, turkey, peas, carrots and pimento.
Spoon mixture into greased 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley. Sprinkle over top. Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 30 minutes or until hot.
Makes 6 servings.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the water.
Stir in egg, salt, sugar and oil.
Gradually add flour.
Mix thoroughly, set aside to rise. When doubled in size, shape into rolls, brush with melted butter and let rise again.
Bake at 450° until golden brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Beat eggs; stir in milk and oil.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 400° until golden brown (approximately 35 minutes).

title: molasses cookies
directions: Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: grilled fish with garlic mayonnaise
directions: Place garlic, paprika, red pepper and salt in blender and add 1/4 cup mayonnaise.
Blend until garlic is minced and mixed into sauce.
Add remaining mayonnaise and process until smooth.

title: delicious pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops a little in a frying pan.
Drain fat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in crock-pot.
Cover with soup.
Cook on slow setting for 7 to 8 hours, on high for 4 to 5 hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off fat and add to the other ingredients.
Cook in microwave 15 minutes on High or bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve over chips, rice, potatoes or noodles.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Sift the flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar into a large mixing bowl. Add the butter and rub into the flour (your best tools for this job are your thumb and forefinger) until the butter lumps have disappeared. Add the buttermilk to the dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. Turn out onto a floured surface and knead 8 or 10 times. The dough will be soft. (Sprinkle just a little additional flour, if necessary, to aid in handling the dough.) Form the dough into a ball and place on floured baking sheet. With a sharp knife, cut a deep cross into the top of the loaf. Dust top of loaf lightly with flour. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 375° and bake an additional 25 minutes. Makes one large loaf approximately 9-inches in diameter.

title: michael's favorite strawberry delight
directions: Pinch cake apart; layer into pan or bowl.
Alternate strawberries, glaze and Cool Whip on cake.
Finish top layer with Cool Whip and garnish with strawberries.

title: peanut bars
directions: In double boiler, melt peanut butter chips and milk.
Fold in Marshmallow Creme.
Place 1 jar peanuts in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour cream mixture over peanuts.
Add other jar of peanuts on top and press down.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: angel flake biscuits (rolls)
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients
together.
Cut into shortening. Dissolve
yeast
in
warm
water and add yeast and milk to dry ingredients.
Stir with fork until soft dough is formed.
Turn out on
lightly
floured
board
and knead briefly.
Store in tightly closed
plastic
bag in refrigerator.
Use as needed. Pat dough out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Do not let rise at any time. Bake on greased cookie sheet in preheated 450° oven for
10 minutes.
This
dough lasts a week and yields 12 biscuits per day.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix and blend well all of the ingredients.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
You can sprinkle crushed corn flakes on top before baking.

title: branded fruit cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs; set aside!
Add all dry ingredients and fruits; fold in creamy mixture.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken delight casserole
directions: Boil fryer and pick from bones.
Spread on bottom of baking pan.
Mix soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over chicken mixture. Melt butter with broth.
Pour over dressing mix.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Cover and let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Toss and serve.

title: orange oat-bran muffins(makes 24 muffins.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan with Pam or Baker's Joy.
In a mixing bowl or food processor, blend pureed bananas with 1/2 cup of the sugar, vanilla and oil; mix until well combined.
Stir in dates and nuts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the three soups with chicken.
Melt margarine in bottom of baking dish.
Add 1/2 of Pepperidge Farm herbal mix. Pour soup mixture over dressing.
Top with remaining dressing mix. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes covered.

title: spinach noodle casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Melt margarine.
Stir all ingredients except for eggs.
Beat eggs and stir in mixture.
Grease pan. Bake for 1 hour, using medium oven (375°).

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Let boil until sticks together in a ball in cold water.
Add jar of regular peanut butter and beat until creamy.
Pour into greased dish.

title: sweet potato pie(custard)
directions: Combine sieved potatoes, melted butter, sugar and salt with beaten eggs. Mix well.
Add milk and lastly stir in lemon juice and nutmeg.
Pour into large unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes on bottom shelf of oven at 450°.
Move to center of oven and bake 45 minutes longer at 350°.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash dried beef.
Chop dried beef (fine).
Mix all ingredients well.
Put into a Corning Ware container.
Cook in 350° oven for approximately 20-30 minutes. Serve with Frito Chips.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In oven, melt margarine in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Lightly brown both sides of the pork chops in the margarine.
Remove from baking dish.
Mix onion soup mix with hot water.
Add the mushroom soup and mix well.

title: cinnamon honey crisp
directions: Spread graham crackers in baking sheet.
Mix butter, margarine and sugar.
Bring to boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers. Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
When cool, break and serve.

title: string bean bundles
directions: Put about 6 or 8 whole beans together and wrap a piece of bacon around the beans.
Put the bundles in a casserole dish and pour French dressing over them.
Bake at 350° until bacon is done.

title: hot dogs
directions: Put the hot dog in the oven on hot.
Take it out.
Put the peanut butter and jelly sandwich in the toaster.
When it pops up, put the hot dog in it.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef with onion and garlic in oil in large frying pan. Drain.
Season with salt.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, chili powder, oregano, crushed red pepper and water.
Cover tightly and simmer for 1 1/2 hours in crock-pot.
Add green pepper and kidney beans and continue cooking for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle servings with cheese and onions, as desired.
For added flavor, put corn chips on bottom of bowl before chili.
